# RDFS Schema for Business: Agriculture

@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix ind: <http://datamodel.lakehouse.org/business/agriculture#> .

# --- Root Business Class ---
ind:Business rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label 'Business' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Root class for all business entities' .

# --- Specific Business: Agriculture ---
ind:Agriculture rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Business ;
    rdfs:label 'Agriculture' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Agriculture is a global industry encompassing crop cultivation, animal husbandry, and food production, providing essential supply chain solutions from farm to table for food manufacturers and consumers worldwide.' .

# --- Domain Classes ---
ind:Crop rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Crop' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core operational domain governing the full crop production lifecycle — from crop planning, seed selection, and planting schedules through cultivation, IPM-based pest and disease management, irrigation (ET-driven), VRA prescriptions, and NDVI-monitored field health. Manages field-level agronomic data, crop varieties, yield metrics (YPM, BU/acre), PHI and REI compliance, and FMIS integration with systems such as Climate FieldView, Trimble Ag Software, and SAP S/4HANA PP. Serves as the SSOT for all agronomic activity aligned with GAP standards.' .

ind:Livestock rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Livestock' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages all animal husbandry and breeding operations including herd and flock records, animal identification (RFID/ear tag), breeding programs, health and veterinary treatment logs, feed ration and nutrition planning, vaccination schedules, growth performance, and animal welfare compliance. Serves as the SSOT for animal lifecycle data from birth through harvest, supporting APHIS regulatory requirements, FSIS compliance, and antibiotic/withdrawal period tracking.' .

ind:Land rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Land' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authoritative domain for all land and soil asset data including field boundaries (GIS/ArcGIS-mapped), parcel ownership and lease records, soil health profiles (pH, EC, OM, CEC, NPK), soil sampling history, conservation practices, land use planning, and environmental monitoring. Integrates with Esri ArcGIS and John Deere Operations Center for RTK-accurate field mapping and GPS positioning. Supports BMP and ISO 14001 environmental compliance for sustainable land management.' .

ind:Equipment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Equipment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all agricultural equipment and fleet assets including tractors, combines, planters, sprayers, and irrigation systems. Tracks asset registration, telematics data (John Deere Operations Center), OEE metrics, preventive and corrective maintenance schedules (PM/CMMS), CAPEX/OPEX cost allocation, parts inventory, and precision agriculture hardware integration (GPS/RTK receivers, VRA controllers). Supports operational efficiency and asset lifecycle management aligned with ISO 55000.' .

ind:Supply rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Supply' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Orchestrates end-to-end agricultural supply chain and logistics from farm inputs through storage, processing, and delivery to food manufacturers and retailers. Manages TMS-driven transportation planning, shipment tracking (BOL, AWB), route optimization, cold chain management, carrier and 3PL relationships, and traceability lot (LOT) tracking with RFID. Ensures compliance with FSMA transportation rules for food safety. Integrates with Manhattan Associates WMS and SAP S/4HANA MM for inbound and outbound logistics.' .

ind:Inventory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Inventory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all agricultural inventory positions across grain bins, cold storage, warehouses, and field stockpiles. Tracks commodity lots (LOT/GRN), quantities in CWT, BU, and MT, storage location assignments, FIFO/FEFO rotation, shrinkage, expiration dates (PHI), stock rotation, and WMS-driven cycle counts. Manages seed, chemical, fertilizer, and harvested commodity stock levels with SAP S/4HANA MM and Manhattan Associates WMS integration. Ensures GRN processing and inventory accuracy for supply chain continuity.' .

ind:Quality rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all quality assurance and food safety compliance data across production and supply chain. Manages COA records, HACCP critical control point logs, MRL testing results, GAP/GMP audit findings, GFSI certification status (SQF, BRC, IFS), FSMA compliance records, inspection programs, testing protocols, non-conformance tracking, and corrective actions. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA QM module and supports USDA, FDA, and FSIS regulatory reporting. Maintains certification readiness for GLOBALG.A.P. audits.' .

ind:Weather rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Weather' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures meteorological and climate data critical to agricultural decision-making including historical and forecast weather station data, precipitation, temperature, humidity, wind, evapotranspiration (ET) calculations, frost/freeze alerts, growing degree day (GDD) accumulations, and climate risk indicators. Integrates with IoT field sensors, DTN weather feeds, WASDE reports, and Climate FieldView. Supports irrigation scheduling, planting windows, spray windows, pest pressure prediction, and crop insurance documentation.' .

ind:Customer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Customer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for all customer identities and relationship data — covering food manufacturers, distributors, wholesalers, retailers, cooperatives, and direct consumers. Manages customer profiles, account hierarchies (B2B enterprise accounts and B2C individual buyers), contact records, segments, relationships, preferences, and COOL (Country of Origin Labeling) preferences. Supports CRM integration with Salesforce for sales pipeline and partner management. The single authoritative source for WHO the business serves.' .

ind:Product rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for the agricultural product and commodity catalog — defining all sellable and transferable items including crop commodities (grains, produce, fiber), livestock products (meat, dairy, eggs), processed goods, seed/input products, and value-added products. Manages SKU/PLU/UPC codes, GMO status, organic certification flags (NOP), grading standards, MRL thresholds, product hierarchy classifications, COA and labeling (COOL) requirements aligned with USDA commodity codes. Supports organic, non-GMO, and conventional product lines.' .

ind:Sales rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Sales' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages the commercial revenue cycle from farm-gate to customer delivery — encompassing sales orders (SO), quotes, contracts, pricing strategies (spot, forward, futures-linked), FOB/CIF terms, BOL generation, COOL compliance, and revenue opportunities. Tracks sales pipeline, customer negotiations, seasonal demand forecasting, distribution channel performance, and partner/broker relationships. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA SD module and Salesforce CRM for opportunity management and market pricing signals from DTN/WASDE feeds.' .

ind:Invoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for all billing, invoicing, payments, and revenue recognition. Manages accounts receivable (AR), payment terms, credit management, financial settlements, and invoice lifecycle from generation to payment. Integrates with GL for revenue accounting per GAAP/IFRS standards. Supports agricultural-specific billing scenarios including commodity-based pricing, weight-ticket reconciliation, and seasonal payment terms.' .

ind:Procurement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Procurement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages sourcing and purchasing of all agricultural inputs including seeds, fertilizers (NPK), crop protection chemicals (AI, MRL compliance), feed ingredients, fuel, parts, and operational supplies. Governs PO lifecycle, GRN processing, vendor qualification, contract terms (FOB, CIF), supplier performance, and spend analytics. Ensures SDS documentation and EPA/APHIS regulatory compliance for chemical and biological inputs. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA MM and Oracle NetSuite for AP processing.' .

ind:Research rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Research' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Governs agricultural R&D data including variety trial results, seed performance benchmarks, soil amendment experiments, IPM efficacy studies, GMO trait evaluations, and precision agriculture technology pilots. Manages experimental designs, trial plot assignments, field trial metadata, statistical analysis outputs, and IP/patent records. Supports USDA APHIS biotech regulatory submissions, crop improvement programs, sustainable farming practices, and internal innovation pipeline tracking.' .

ind:Workforce rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Workforce' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages all human capital data for the agricultural enterprise — including seasonal and permanent employee records, farm workers, agronomists, technicians, and administrative staff. Tracks payroll, benefits, H-2A visa and migrant labor compliance, OSHA safety certifications, pesticide applicator licenses, training records (GAP, HACCP, safety), and workforce planning. Integrates with SAP SuccessFactors for HR, talent management, and labor cost allocation across farm operations and processing facilities.' .

ind:Finance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Finance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all enterprise financial data including general ledger (GL), cost center accounting, accounts payable (AP), crop enterprise budgeting, CAPEX/OPEX tracking, COGS allocation by commodity, EBITDA reporting, ROI analysis, and financial controls per SOX requirements. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA FI/CO and Oracle NetSuite. Ensures GAAP/IFRS compliance for consolidated financial statements and regulatory filings.' .

ind:Sustainability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Sustainability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages environmental sustainability data including carbon footprint tracking, greenhouse gas emissions, water stewardship metrics, soil carbon sequestration, biodiversity assessments, and ESG reporting for the agricultural enterprise. Covers compliance with emerging sustainability regulations and voluntary certification programs.' .

ind:Compliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Agriculture ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Centralized domain for regulatory compliance management across all agricultural operations — including USDA, FDA, EPA, FSIS, state agriculture department filings, environmental permits, pesticide applicator licenses, and cross-border trade compliance. Manages compliance calendars, regulatory change tracking, and audit readiness.' .

# --- Data Product Classes (Tables) ---
ind:Opportunity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Opportunity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Sales opportunity record tracking the full pipeline from lead qualification through close — capturing commodity type, estimated volume (BU/MT/CWT), target price, pricing strategy (spot, forward, futures-linked), probability of close, expected close date, assigned broker/sales rep, pipeline stage, and competitive intelligence. SSOT for revenue opportunity management in the agricultural commercial cycle. Integrates with Salesforce CRM for pipeline visibility and SAP S/4HANA SD for order conversion.' .

ind:Quote rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Quote' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal price quotation issued to a customer or broker for agricultural commodities or products — capturing quoted price per unit (FOB/CIF basis), commodity grade, total volume, validity period, pricing basis (spot vs. forward vs. futures-linked DTN/WASDE), incoterms, and quote status. Contains individual line items each specifying commodity code, grade/class, quantity (BU/MT/CWT), unit price, pricing basis, applicable MRL/PHI compliance flags, GMO status, and COOL origin designation. Supports multi-commodity quotes common in agricultural trading where a single quotation covers multiple grain types or product grades. Linked to SAP S/4HANA SD quotation and Salesforce CRM opportunity.' .

ind:Order rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authoritative sales order (SO) record aligned with SAP S/4HANA SD module — capturing order number, customer, order date, requested delivery date, incoterms (FOB/CIF), payment terms, total order value, currency, order type (spot, contract, forward), delivery location, and order status lifecycle. SSOT for confirmed commercial sales transactions from farm-gate to customer delivery.' .

ind:OrderLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Order Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual line item on a confirmed sales order specifying a single commodity or product — capturing commodity code, crop year, grade/class, quantity ordered and confirmed (BU/MT/CWT), unit price, pricing basis (spot/forward/futures), lot number, GMO status, COOL country of origin, MRL compliance flag, PHI clearance status, and line-level delivery schedule. Supports multi-commodity orders and per-line regulatory compliance tracking common in agricultural commodity sales.' .

ind:Contract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Long-term or seasonal agricultural sales contract governing the commercial relationship between the enterprise and a buyer — capturing contract number, contract type (forward, futures-linked, fixed-price, basis), commodity, total contracted volume, price formula, crop year, incoterms, GLOBALG.A.P. certification requirements, FSMA compliance obligations, and contract status. Includes the planned delivery call-off schedule (delivery windows, scheduled volumes per call-off, delivery locations, pricing fixation dates, basis levels, and fulfillment status) enabling tracking of contract execution against committed delivery obligations across the crop marketing season. SSOT for both commercial contract terms and delivery execution planning.' .

ind:PriceAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Price Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Customer-specific or channel-specific pricing agreement defining negotiated price levels, volume tiers, basis adjustments, and discount structures for agricultural commodities and products — capturing effective date range, commodity, grade, pricing basis (FOB elevator, CIF port, DTN market reference), volume thresholds, and approval status. Supports spot, forward, and futures-linked pricing strategies.' .

ind:MarketPrice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Price' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Daily or intraday commodity market price reference sourced from DTN, CME futures, WASDE reports, and local elevator bids — capturing commodity code, price date, price type (cash, futures, basis, FOB, CIF), market location or exchange, unit of measure, bid/ask/settlement values, crop year, and data source. Primary reference for sales teams performing pricing validation, basis calculation, quote generation, and revenue benchmarking. Also consumed by procurement and finance for cost benchmarking and margin analysis.' .

ind:DeliveryOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Delivery Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Delivery instruction issued against a confirmed sales order or contract — capturing delivery order number, ship-from location (farm, elevator, warehouse), ship-to customer location, scheduled shipment date, commodity, grade, quantity (BU/MT/CWT), transport mode, carrier assignment, BOL reference, and delivery status. Bridges the sales order to physical logistics execution.' .

ind:Broker rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Broker' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for agricultural commodity brokers and independent sales agents who act as intermediaries in the sales channel. Captures broker code, name, brokerage firm, license number, USDA registration, commodity specializations, commission rate structure, geographic territory, and relationship status. Includes commission transaction management: calculation rules, earned amounts per sales order/contract, payment status, settlement periods, and commission history. Brokers facilitate transactions between the enterprise and buyers but are neither customers nor suppliers. SSOT for broker identity, performance, and commission lifecycle.' .

ind:DemandForecast rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Demand Forecast' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Seasonal and forward-looking demand forecast for agricultural commodities by customer segment, channel, and geography. Captures forecast period (crop year, quarter, month), commodity, grade, forecasted volume and revenue, pricing assumptions, forecast basis (WASDE outlook, customer commitments, historical trends), version, and accuracy metrics. Drives sales planning, inventory pre-positioning, and contract negotiation strategy.' .

ind:OriginDeclaration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Origin Declaration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Country of Origin Labeling (COOL) compliance declaration record associated with a sales order or shipment — capturing declaration ID, commodity, country of origin, production method (domestic, imported, mixed), applicable USDA COOL regulation reference, declaration date, certifying party, and compliance status. Required for USDA COOL regulatory compliance on covered commodities sold in the US market.' .

ind:CustomerAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Customer Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Volume allocation record assigning available commodity inventory or anticipated production to specific customers or contracts during supply-constrained periods — such as drought, poor harvest, or logistics disruptions. Captures crop year, commodity, grade, allocated volume (BU/MT), allocation basis (contract priority, customer tier, channel strategy), fulfillment status, and reallocation history. Critical for managing delivery commitments when supply falls short of contracted volumes and for maintaining customer relationship equity during shortages.' .

ind:ReturnOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Return Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Sales return order capturing customer-initiated product returns or rejections — including return reason (quality rejection, grade dispute, MRL exceedance, over-delivery), returned commodity, quantity, original sales order reference, return authorization number, disposition instruction (regrading, reprocessing, disposal), credit memo trigger, and return status. Supports quality dispute resolution and reverse logistics in the agricultural supply chain.' .

ind:Territory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Territory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Sales territory master defining geographic and customer-segment-based sales coverage areas — capturing territory code, territory name, geographic boundaries (state, county, region, export zone), assigned sales representative, commodity focus, channel coverage, annual volume target, and active status. Supports sales force alignment, performance tracking, and market coverage planning.' .

ind:GrowingSeason rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Growing Season' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines each agricultural growing season (e.g., Spring 2024 Corn, Fall 2024 Soybean) including season type (spring, fall, double-crop, cover crop), start and end dates, target crop, associated field zones, and season status (planned, active, completed). Acts as the temporal anchor for all crop production activities — planting, cultivation, harvest, and loss events — and links agronomic plans to financial crop enterprise budgets. Supports multi-crop and double-crop scenarios common in southern US and tropical operations. Aligns with FMIS season management in Climate FieldView and Granular.' .

ind:FieldCropPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Field Crop Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Comprehensive agronomic plan for a specific field and growing season, serving as the single operational blueprint for all planned crop activities. Consolidates all sub-planning disciplines into one authoritative document. Captures: (1) Crop selection — intended crop variety, target planting population (seeds/acre), row spacing, tillage method. (2) Nutrient management — target NPK removal rates, soil test baseline (pH, NPK, CEC, OM), recommended fertilizer products and rates, application timing windows, environmental setback zones, EPA nutrient management compliance. (3) Irrigation strategy — ET-deficit and soil moisture trigger thresholds, target application depth (acre-inches), water allocation limits, irrigation system type. (4) IPM program — target pests and diseases, economic threshold levels, monitoring frequency, preferred intervention hierarchy (biological, cultural, chemical), approved agrochemicals, responsible agronomist. (5) Yield target — expected yield (BU/acre or YPM), benchmark comparisons. Integrates with Trimble Ag Software and Climate FieldView for VRA prescription generation. Supports EPA nutrient management compliance, BMP documentation, GLOBALG.A.P. crop protection standards, and IPM guidelines.' .

ind:PlantingEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Planting Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an actual planting operation executed on a field, capturing planting date, operator, equipment used, seed lot number (LOT), actual seeding rate (seeds/acre), row spacing achieved, planting depth, soil temperature at planting, and GPS-tracked field coverage. Sourced from John Deere Operations Center and Climate FieldView planting data. Supports GAP traceability and PHI/REI compliance tracking.' .

ind:SeedLot rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Seed Lot' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each seed lot (LOT) received and used in planting operations, including crop variety reference, supplier, lot number, germination rate, purity percentage, seed treatment details (fungicide/insecticide coating, treatment date), GMO trait stack, test weight, and storage location. Provides full seed traceability from procurement through planting to harvest. Supports FSMA seed traceability, USDA seed certification compliance, and AOSCA seed labeling requirements.' .

ind:FertilizationEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Fertilization Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of a fertilizer application event on a field, capturing application date, product applied (NPK formulation), application rate (lbs/acre or gallons/acre), application method (broadcast, banded, fertigation), equipment used, operator, and VRA prescription reference. Tracks actual vs. planned nutrient application for agronomic compliance and environmental reporting (EPA nutrient management). Sourced from John Deere Operations Center and Trimble Ag.' .

ind:ProtectionEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Protection Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of a pesticide, herbicide, fungicide, or insecticide application event, capturing application date, agrochemical product reference (EPA registration number, active ingredient), application rate, target pest or disease, application method, equipment used, operator certification number, weather conditions at application, and GPS-tracked coverage area. Includes PHI (Pre-Harvest Interval) compliance tracking: PHI days required, calculated earliest harvest date, REI (Restricted Entry Interval) hours required, field re-entry clearance date, compliance status, and responsible agronomist sign-off. Supports IPM program execution, FSMA compliance, EPA pesticide recordkeeping, MRL verification, and GLOBALG.A.P. pesticide audit trails.' .

ind:IrrigationEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Irrigation Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an irrigation application on a field or zone, capturing irrigation date, method (drip, pivot, flood, sprinkler), water volume applied (acre-inches), ET-based trigger value, soil moisture reading at time of application, water source, pump station reference, and duration. Supports ET-driven irrigation scheduling, water use reporting, and BMP compliance. Integrates with IoT soil moisture sensors and John Deere Operations Center.' .

ind:ScoutingObservation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Scouting Observation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Field observation record capturing crop health assessments from both in-person scouting and remote sensing sources. In-person scouting captures: agronomist or scout identity, pest identification and pressure rating, disease incidence and severity, weed species and density, nutrient deficiency symptoms, crop growth stage (BBCH scale code), GPS coordinates, photo references, and recommended action. Remote sensing captures: NDVI values, vegetation health classification, anomaly detection flags, seasonal baseline comparison, sensor platform (satellite, drone, aerial), and imagery date. Includes observation method type, priority classification, and recommended follow-up actions linking to crop protection events or VRA prescriptions. Sourced from Trimble Ag Software crop scouting module, Esri ArcGIS, and Climate FieldView. Drives IPM decision-making, crop protection event triggers, and variable rate intervention decisions.' .

ind:VraPrescription rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Vra Prescription' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Variable Rate Application (VRA) prescription map generated for a specific field and input type (seed, fertilizer, or crop protection), defining spatially variable application rates across field management zones. Captures prescription creation date, agronomist author, input product, rate units, zone map reference, target application window, and upload status to equipment controller (RTK-enabled). Links to source data (soil sampling results, scouting observations, yield history) that informed zone delineation. Post-application, actual vs. prescribed rate variance is reconciled through linked fertilization_event or protection_event records. Sourced from Trimble Ag Software and Climate FieldView. Enables precision agriculture, input cost optimization, and environmental compliance documentation.' .

ind:YieldRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Yield Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for all yield and harvest performance data at the field-season-variety level. Captures individual harvest operation details: harvest date, combine/equipment used, operator, load ticket references, moisture content at harvest, test weight, grain quality grade, GPS-tracked harvest area, and field coverage. Aggregates production metrics: total production (BU, MT, CWT), average yield per acre (YPM), moisture-adjusted yield, quality grade distribution, and variance against the field crop plan\'s yield target. Each harvest pass on a field is recorded as a yield_record entry, with season-level rollups computed for financial and agronomic reporting. Sourced from John Deere Operations Center and Climate FieldView harvest data. Serves as the authoritative yield SSOT for financial crop enterprise accounting, grain receipt (GRN) creation, sales contract fulfillment, crop insurance (USDA RMA) documentation, and agronomic benchmarking. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA PP and Granular Farm Management.' .

ind:AgrochemicalProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Agrochemical Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all registered agrochemical products (pesticides, herbicides, fungicides, insecticides, fertilizers) used in crop protection and nutrition programs. Captures EPA registration number, active ingredient (AI), formulation type, MRL limits by crop, PHI, REI, SDS reference, restricted use status, and approved application methods. Serves as the SSOT for agrochemical compliance data supporting FSMA, EPA, and GLOBALG.A.P. requirements.' .

ind:RotationPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Rotation Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Multi-year crop rotation plan for a field or farm unit, defining the planned sequence of crops and cover crops across growing seasons to optimize soil health, break pest and disease cycles, manage nutrient cycling, and support conservation compliance. Captures rotation cycle length (years), crop sequence by season, cover crop species and termination timing, tillage system transitions, and agronomic rationale for each rotation choice. Supports NRCS Conservation Stewardship Program (CSP) documentation, GAP soil health certification, and long-term land productivity management within Granular Farm Management.' .

ind:LossEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Loss Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of a crop loss or damage event affecting a field or portion thereof, capturing loss date, cause (hail, drought, flood, frost, pest, disease, wind), estimated yield impact (BU/acre or % loss), affected acreage, loss assessment method (visual, drone survey, adjuster inspection), adjuster reference, crop insurance claim number, policy reference, and final indemnity determination. May be triggered by scouting observations identifying severe damage or by weather event alerts. Supports crop insurance (USDA RMA) claim processing, MPCI and crop-hail policy documentation, financial loss reporting, and agronomic risk management. Integrates with USDA RMA ADM system for electronic claim submission.' .

ind:StockPosition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Stock Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master record of current inventory positions across all agricultural storage locations (grain bins, cold storage, warehouses, field stockpiles). Tracks on-hand, reserved, and available-to-promise quantities in CWT, BU, and MT by material, commodity lot, and location. Includes stock type (unrestricted, quality inspection, blocked), valuation class, unit price, total value, and valuation method (standard cost, moving average, FIFO). Supports period-end valuation snapshots capturing valuation date, quantity, unit price, total value in USD, price variance, and SAP accounting document reference for GAAP/IFRS inventory valuation, COGS calculation, and commodity position reporting. Serves as the SSOT for real-time stock levels, inventory valuation, and period-end financial inventory reporting. Supports GS1 GTIN and SSCC identifiers for global supply chain interoperability. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA MM and Manhattan Associates WMS.' .

ind:CommodityLot rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Commodity Lot' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each commodity lot (LOT/GRN) tracked through the agricultural supply chain. Captures lot number, GRN reference, GS1 SSCC for pallet/container-level tracking, commodity type (grain, produce, feed), crop year, origin field, GMO status, organic certification flag per USDA NOP, grade, moisture content, test weight, and expiration management (PHI date, best-before date, manufacture date, expiration status, days to expiry, disposition action). Supports FIFO/FEFO rotation logic with expiration-driven lot selection, quarantine/hold management, and full traceability from farm to table per FSMA Section 204, EU General Food Law Regulation 178/2002, and Codex Alimentarius traceability guidelines.' .

ind:StorageLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Storage Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all physical storage locations including grain bins, cold storage units, refrigerated warehouses, dry warehouses, and field stockpile areas. Captures location code, GS1 GLN (Global Location Number), facility name, storage type, capacity in BU/MT/CWT, temperature range, humidity controls, GIS coordinates, WMS zone assignment, and regulatory compliance certifications (USDA, FDA, EU food safety). Integrates with Manhattan Associates WMS location master.' .

ind:MaterialMaster rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Material Master' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all inventory-managed materials including seeds, fertilizers (NPK), crop protection chemicals (AI/MRL-classified), feed ingredients, harvested commodities, and packaging materials. Captures SAP material number, SKU, GS1 GTIN, SSCC for pallet/container tracking, UPC/PLU codes, unit of measure (BU, CWT, MT, KG), material group, commodity class, GMO indicator, SDS reference, MRL limits per EU Regulation 396/2005 and Codex Alimentarius standards, REI/PHI values per EPA WPS, storage condition requirements (temperature range, humidity, hazmat class), and organic certification reference per USDA NOP. Sourced from SAP S/4HANA MM material master.' .

ind:InventoryGoodsReceipt rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Inventory Goods Receipt' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all goods received into inventory including supplier deliveries (GRN processing), harvest intake from field operations (capturing crop season, variety, harvest date, field/parcel of origin, elevator ticket number, gross/tare/net weight), customer returns, and inter-facility transfers. Captures GRN number, PO reference, receipt type (purchase, harvest, return, transfer), vendor/supplier, material with GS1 GTIN/SSCC for shipment-level tracking, quantity received in CWT/BU/MT, receiving location, assigned storage bin, lot assignment, quality inspection status, COA reference, moisture reading at intake, test weight, grade determination, and SAP goods movement document (MIGO). Supports FSMA Section 204 traceability, EU General Food Law Regulation 178/2002, FIFO/FEFO lot assignment at receipt, and links field harvest events to inventory stock positions and commodity lot creation.' .

ind:GoodsIssue rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Goods Issue' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all inventory withdrawals and outbound goods movements including shipments to customers, internal consumption, field application of agricultural inputs (seeds, fertilizers NPK, crop protection chemicals, feed), livestock feed issuance, and production orders. Captures goods issue document number, movement type (shipment, consumption, field_application, feed_issuance, production), material with GS1 GTIN/SSCC, lot, quantity in CWT/BU/MT, issuing location, destination or field/pen of application, operator, equipment used, VRA prescription reference, application rate, REI/PHI compliance flag per EPA WPS, cost center, sales order or production order reference, and SAP movement document. Serves as the SSOT for all inventory consumption including field input application. Supports FIFO/FEFO depletion, IPM tracking, MRL compliance per EU Regulation 396/2005 and Codex Alimentarius, and COGS allocation.' .

ind:StockTransfer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Stock Transfer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of inventory movements between storage locations, bins, warehouses, or facilities. Captures transfer order number, source location, destination location, material with GS1 GTIN/SSCC, lot, quantity in CWT/BU/MT, transfer type (bin-to-bin, plant-to-plant, warehouse transfer), WMS transfer order reference, BOL number for inter-facility transfers, carrier, estimated transit time, and transfer reason. Integrates with Manhattan Associates WMS transfer order management and SAP MM stock transport orders.' .

ind:CycleCount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Cycle Count' ;
    rdfs:comment 'WMS-driven cycle count event record capturing scheduled and ad-hoc physical inventory counts at the storage location and bin level. Captures count document number, count date, counter assigned, location/bin counted, material with GS1 GTIN, system quantity vs. physical count quantity in CWT/BU/MT, variance quantity, variance percentage, recount flag, count status, and root cause code for variances. Integrates with Manhattan Associates WMS cycle count module and SAP MM inventory management. Supports inventory accuracy KPI tracking and triggers inventory_adjustment records for confirmed variances.' .

ind:Adjustment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Adjustment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all inventory quantity and value adjustments including shrinkage events (moisture loss/drying shrink, handling loss, storage deterioration, pest damage, quality downgrade), cycle count variance corrections, damage write-offs, and reclassifications. Captures adjustment document number, adjustment type (shrinkage, variance, damage, downgrade, reclassification), material, lot, location, original quantity, adjusted quantity, variance quantity in CWT/BU/MT, shrinkage type and percentage, cause code, adjustment reason code, corrective action taken, approver, cost impact, estimated value impact, shrinkage event date, and SAP accounting document reference. Serves as the SSOT for all shrinkage tracking, shrinkage trend analysis and benchmarking by storage type, commodity, and season. Supports COGS accuracy for commodity accounting and provides complete audit trail for all inventory corrections.' .

ind:BinLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Bin Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular WMS bin-level location master within a storage location, representing individual grain bin cells, rack positions, cold storage bays, or floor stack positions. Captures bin code, bin type, storage section, maximum capacity in BU/MT/CWT, current utilization, temperature zone, hazmat compatibility flag, RFID tag, and WMS bin status. Enables precise slot management and bin-level inventory tracking within Manhattan Associates WMS.' .

ind:StockReservation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Stock Reservation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of inventory reservations that earmark stock for planned consumption — including production orders, sales orders, and field application plans. Captures reservation number, material, lot, reserved quantity in CWT/BU/MT, reservation type (production, sales, transfer), requirement date, originating order reference, fulfillment status, and expiry date. Prevents double-allocation and supports supply chain continuity planning.' .

ind:ReorderPolicy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Reorder Policy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master configuration record defining reorder and replenishment policies for inventory-managed materials including seeds, chemicals, fertilizers, and feed. Captures material, storage location, reorder point quantity, safety stock level in CWT/BU/MT, maximum stock level, economic order quantity (EOQ), lead time days, preferred supplier reference, and seasonal demand flag. Drives automated purchase requisition creation in SAP MM MRP.' .

ind:WarehouseTask rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Warehouse Task' ;
    rdfs:comment 'WMS-generated operational task record for physical warehouse activities including putaway, picking, replenishment, consolidation, relabeling, and cycle count execution. Captures task number, task type, assigned operator, source bin, destination bin, material, lot, quantity, task status (open, in-progress, confirmed, cancelled), priority, creation timestamp, completion timestamp, and execution duration. Sourced from Manhattan Associates WMS task management. Supports warehouse labor productivity tracking and operational efficiency measurement.' .

ind:QuarantineHold rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Quarantine Hold' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record managing inventory holds and quarantine status for lots or stock positions pending quality inspection, regulatory review, or food safety investigation. Captures hold number, material, lot, location, quantity on hold in CWT/BU/MT, hold type (quality, regulatory, safety, recall, customer_complaint), hold reason, initiating event reference (COA failure, HACCP deviation, MRL exceedance per EPA/EU Regulation 396/2005), hold start date, expected release date, actual release date, disposition decision (release, rework, destroy, return), and approver. Integrates with SAP QM usage decision and supports FDA/USDA recall response procedures, EU RASFF (Rapid Alert System for Food and Feed) notifications, and Codex Alimentarius food safety standards.' .

ind:Station rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Station' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for meteorological observation stations including fixed field stations, portable IoT sensor nodes, and DTN network reference points. Stores station identity, GPS/GIS coordinates, elevation, installation date, operational status, data provider (DTN, Climate FieldView, on-farm IoT), associated field or farm unit linkage, and complete sensor/instrument inventory with calibration history (sensor identifier, calibration date, method, pre/post calibration readings, acceptable tolerance range, calibration technician, next scheduled calibration date, out-of-tolerance flag). SSOT for station identity, instrument health, sensor calibration traceability, and data quality assurance referenced by all observation, forecast, and derived weather products. Supports regulatory and insurance documentation of measurement accuracy.' .

ind:Observation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Observation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Time-series transactional record of actual meteorological measurements captured at a weather station or IoT field sensor. Stores instantaneous or interval readings for temperature (min/max/avg in °F/°C), precipitation (rainfall/snowfall in inches/mm), relative humidity (%), wind speed (mph) and direction, barometric pressure (inHg/hPa), solar radiation (W/m²), dew point, and leaf wetness duration (hours). Timestamped to ISO 8601 with configurable interval (5-min, 15-min, hourly, daily). SSOT for all raw weather measurements; feeds GDD calculation, ET computation, irrigation scheduling, spray window determination, and crop insurance documentation.' .

ind:Forecast rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Forecast' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Meteorological forecast record sourced from DTN, NOAA NWS, or Climate FieldView for a specific geographic location or field polygon. Captures forecast horizon (hourly, daily, 7-day, seasonal), predicted temperature range, precipitation probability and amount, wind speed/direction, humidity, ET forecast, and confidence interval. Supports planting window decisions, spray window scheduling, and WASDE-aligned seasonal outlooks.' .

ind:GrowingDegreeDay rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Growing Degree Day' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Growing Degree Day (GDD) accumulation record tracking heat unit accumulation for a specific crop, field, and growing season. Stores daily GDD calculated from min/max temperature against crop-specific base and upper threshold temperatures, cumulative GDD to date, target GDD milestones (emergence, silking, maturity), and deviation from historical norms. Critical for crop development stage prediction, PHI compliance, and harvest timing decisions.' .

ind:Evapotranspiration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Evapotranspiration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Evapotranspiration (ET) calculation and weather-driven water balance record for a field or irrigation zone. Computed using the Penman-Monteith or Hargreaves method from observed or forecast weather inputs. Stores reference ET (ETo), crop ET (ETc) adjusted by crop coefficient (Kc), soil water deficit, ET deficit, soil moisture target, precipitation credit applied, recommended irrigation volume (acre-inches), irrigation method suitability (drip, pivot, flood), and scheduled irrigation date/time when weather-driven scheduling is active. SSOT for weather-derived water balance calculations and ET-based irrigation recommendations that feed irrigation scheduling systems (John Deere Operations Center, Trimble Ag VRA) and water resource management compliance reporting.' .

ind:FrostAlert rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Frost Alert' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Frost and freeze event alert record generated when forecast or observed temperatures fall below crop-specific critical thresholds. Captures alert type (advisory/watch/warning), predicted low temperature, frost probability, affected field or geographic zone, crop vulnerability rating, recommended protective actions (frost cloth, irrigation frost protection), and alert source (DTN, NWS). Supports crop protection decision-making and insurance loss documentation.' .

ind:PrecipitationEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Precipitation Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Discrete severe weather event record capturing precipitation, hail, and high-wind episodes at field or station level. Stores event start/end timestamps, total precipitation amount, peak intensity, storm type (convective, frontal, orographic), hail stone size (inches) and density (stones/sq ft), peak wind gust speed (mph), sustained wind speed, wind direction, Beaufort scale classification, crop lodging risk flag, spray drift risk level, structural damage risk indicator, runoff estimate, soil saturation index, estimated crop damage severity (none/light/moderate/severe), affected acreage, storm track path, and insurance claim trigger flag. SSOT for all field-level severe weather event documentation including precipitation, hail, and wind damage. Used for irrigation adjustments, trafficability assessment, spray window invalidation, crop insurance documentation, USDA disaster reporting, and FSIS compliance.' .

ind:SprayWindow rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Spray Window' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Calculated time window record defining meteorologically permissible periods for pesticide, herbicide, or fertilizer application at field level. Stores window start/end datetime, wind speed range, temperature range, humidity range, inversion risk flag, delta-T value, REI (Restricted Entry Interval) compliance status, and EPA/state drift regulation constraint flags. Weather domain SSOT for application-window meteorological feasibility; integrates with crop protection planning workflows for label-compliant scheduling.' .

ind:PlantingWindow rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Planting Window' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Calculated time window record identifying optimal periods for field planting operations based on soil temperature thresholds, soil moisture levels, air temperature forecasts, and precipitation outlook. Stores window start/end dates, soil temperature at 2-inch and 4-inch depth, field trafficability score, frost risk probability, GDD accumulation outlook, and recommended crop types for the window.' .

ind:ClimateRiskIndicator rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Climate Risk Indicator' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Seasonal and long-range climate risk assessment record for a geographic zone or farm unit. Captures risk type (drought, flood, heat stress, late frost, hail, excessive wind), risk severity index, probability of occurrence, affected crop types, historical frequency, ENSO phase influence, and WASDE seasonal outlook alignment. Supports crop insurance underwriting, enterprise risk management, and long-term capital planning for climate adaptation investments.' .

ind:DroughtIndex rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Drought Index' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Drought monitoring index record tracking soil moisture deficit and drought severity for a field or geographic region. Stores Palmer Drought Severity Index (PDSI), Standardized Precipitation Index (SPI), Crop Moisture Index (CMI), NDVI-derived vegetation stress indicator, drought category (D0–D4 per USDM), and consecutive dry days count. Feeds irrigation scheduling, crop insurance claims, and USDA disaster designation documentation.' .

ind:SoilTemperature rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Soil Temperature' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Soil temperature measurement record captured at defined depths (2-inch, 4-inch, 6-inch, 12-inch) from in-field IoT sensors or weather station probes. Stores reading timestamp, depth (inches/cm), temperature (°F/°C), sensor calibration status, and EC (Electrical Conductivity) co-reading where available. Critical for planting window determination, seed germination prediction, and soil biological activity assessment.' .

ind:Zone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Zone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master geographic zone definition used to aggregate weather observations and forecasts for agricultural planning. Stores zone identifier, zone type (NWS forecast zone, county, watershed, irrigation district, farm unit polygon), GIS boundary coordinates (ArcGIS-compatible), climate classification (Köppen), average annual precipitation, frost-free days, and hardiness zone (USDA Plant Hardiness Zone Map). SSOT for weather geographic aggregation.' .

ind:ClimateNormal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Climate Normal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Long-term climate normal record representing 30-year statistical baselines (WMO standard) for a weather zone or station. Stores monthly and seasonal averages for temperature (min/max/mean), precipitation, ET, frost dates (average first/last), GDD accumulation norms, and extreme event frequencies. Used as baseline for anomaly detection, crop variety selection, and WASDE yield estimation inputs.' .

ind:IrrigationSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Irrigation Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Weather-driven irrigation scheduling record generated from ET calculations, soil moisture readings, and precipitation forecasts for a specific field or irrigation zone. Stores scheduled irrigation date/time, recommended application volume (acre-inches), irrigation method (drip, pivot, flood), ET deficit being addressed, soil moisture target, and precipitation credit applied. Integrates with John Deere Operations Center and Trimble Ag VRA irrigation prescriptions.' .

ind:Alert rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Alert' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Official weather alert, warning, and frost/freeze advisory record issued by NWS, DTN, or internal farm management systems for a weather zone or field. Stores alert type (tornado, severe thunderstorm, flash flood, heat advisory, winter storm, high wind, frost/freeze advisory, wildfire smoke), alert severity (advisory/watch/warning/emergency), issuance and expiration datetime, affected geographic zone, predicted low temperature for frost events, frost probability, crop-specific vulnerability rating, recommended protective actions (including frost cloth, irrigation frost protection), alert source, and acknowledgment status. SSOT for all weather alert types including frost/freeze events, consolidating all alert lifecycle management in a single product.' .

ind:InsuranceRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Insurance Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Certified weather data record compiled for crop insurance claim substantiation and USDA RMA (Risk Management Agency) reporting. Stores policy-linked weather event documentation, certified precipitation totals, temperature extremes, GDD deviation from normal, drought index values, hail event records, and adjuster-verified observation data. Supports FCIC (Federal Crop Insurance Corporation) compliance and indemnity claim processing.' .

ind:SensorCalibration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Weather ;
    rdfs:label 'Sensor Calibration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Calibration and maintenance record for IoT field weather sensors and weather station instruments. Stores sensor identifier, calibration date, calibration method, pre/post calibration readings, acceptable tolerance range, calibration technician, next scheduled calibration date, and out-of-tolerance flag. Ensures data quality and traceability for regulatory and insurance documentation purposes.' .

ind:Asset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all agricultural equipment and fleet assets including tractors, combines, planters, sprayers, irrigation systems, and precision agriculture hardware. Captures asset identification (serial number, VIN, asset tag), make, model, year, asset class/category reference, acquisition date, acquisition cost (CAPEX), current book value, depreciation method, operational status (active/standby/decommissioned), assigned farm/field, GPS/RTK integration flag, telematics device ID (John Deere Operations Center), ISO 55000 lifecycle stage, salvage value, and regulatory compliance certifications. SSOT for all equipment identity, registration, and financial summary data. Central master record referenced by all transactional products in the equipment domain.' .

ind:AssetCategory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Category' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference classification hierarchy for agricultural equipment types and categories. Defines the taxonomy of equipment classes (e.g., tillage, planting, spraying, harvesting, irrigation, precision ag hardware, livestock handling, transport fleet) with category codes, parent-child hierarchy for rollup reporting, OEE benchmark targets per category, standard depreciation life, and applicable regulatory inspection requirements. Used for CAPEX/OPEX budgeting and fleet planning.' .

ind:TelematicsReading rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Telematics Reading' ;
    rdfs:comment 'High-frequency telemetry records streamed from John Deere Operations Center, Trimble, and other IoT-enabled agricultural equipment. Captures machine hours, engine RPM, fuel consumption rate, ground speed, PTO engagement, hydraulic pressure, GPS coordinates (RTK-corrected latitude/longitude), heading, NDVI sensor readings, implement depth/width, load weight, fault codes (DTC), operational status (field working/transport/idle/parked), geofence zone, RTK correction status, field boundary match flag, data source identifier, and timestamp. SSOT for all equipment telemetry including fleet position tracking — latest-reading queries provide current fleet position for dispatch dashboards, field coverage monitoring, theft detection, and operator hours-of-service compliance (replacing standalone fleet_position). Supports OEE calculation, predictive maintenance triggers, precision agriculture VRA audit trails, and fleet dispatch. One record per telemetry event per asset.' .

ind:WorkOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Work Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Corrective and preventive maintenance work orders for agricultural equipment managed through CMMS (e.g., SAP PM). Header captures work order number, order type (PM/CM/inspection), priority, asset reference, fault description, reported fault code, assigned technician, planned and actual start/end dates, labor hours, total maintenance cost (OPEX), work order status (open/in-progress/completed/cancelled), and sign-off details. Embedded parts consumption line items (replacing standalone parts_usage) capture part number, quantity used, unit cost, total cost, issue date, issuing warehouse/bin, and technician ID — SSOT for actual material consumption data supporting OPEX cost tracking, inventory replenishment triggers, and maintenance cost analysis by asset and crop enterprise. Core CMMS transactional record for all maintenance activities. Integrates with SAP MM goods issue and SAP CO cost allocation.' .

ind:MaintenancePlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Maintenance Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Preventive maintenance (PM) schedules and plans for agricultural equipment assets. Header defines maintenance strategy (time-based, usage-based, condition-based), maintenance cycle (e.g., every 250 engine hours, annually), applicable asset categories, and compliance requirements (OSHA, EPA, local equivalents). Embedded task list line items (replacing standalone maintenance_item) specify individual maintenance tasks including task type (lubrication, calibration, filter replacement, inspection, adjustment), task description, standard labor hours, required skill level, safety precautions (REI/OSHA), required tools, required parts/materials with quantities, and completion status. SSOT for all PM task definitions and maintenance scheduling. Linked to CMMS maintenance plans. Drives automatic work order generation and ensures equipment readiness for planting and harvest seasons.' .

ind:Fault rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Fault' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of equipment faults, breakdowns, and diagnostic trouble codes (DTC) detected via telematics or reported by operators. Captures fault code, fault description, severity level, detection source (telematics/operator/inspection), asset affected, field/location at time of fault, downtime start/end, estimated production impact (acres lost, yield impact), root cause classification, and corrective action taken. Feeds into OEE availability calculations and reliability-centered maintenance (RCM) analysis.' .

ind:PartsInventory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Parts Inventory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Inventory master for spare parts, consumables, and replacement components held for agricultural equipment maintenance. Captures part number (material number), part description, OEM part number, compatible asset models/categories, unit of measure, current stock quantity, reorder point, reorder quantity, storage location (bin/warehouse), unit cost, total stock value, lead time from supplier, and criticality classification (critical/non-critical). Supports MRO (Maintenance, Repair, and Operations) inventory management, prevents equipment downtime due to parts stockouts during planting and harvest seasons, and integrates with procurement for automated replenishment.' .

ind:OeeRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Oee Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Overall Equipment Effectiveness (OEE) measurement records calculated per asset per operational shift or day. Captures availability rate (planned vs. actual uptime), performance rate (actual vs. theoretical throughput), quality rate (acceptable output vs. total output), composite OEE percentage, planned production time, unplanned downtime minutes, planned downtime minutes, total acres covered, and benchmark OEE target from asset category. Supports fleet performance management, CAPEX justification for equipment replacement, and operational efficiency KPI reporting aligned with ISO 55000.' .

ind:EquipmentFieldOperation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Equipment Field Operation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of field-level equipment operations including planting, spraying, tillage, harvesting, and irrigation runs. Captures operation type, asset used, operator, field/parcel reference, start/end datetime, total area covered (acres), application rate (for VRA operations), product applied (seed/chemical/fertilizer), pass efficiency, GPS track file reference (Trimble/Climate FieldView), fuel consumed, and operation status. SSOT for as-applied and as-planted records supporting FSMA traceability and precision agriculture audit trails.' .

ind:PrecisionDevice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Precision Device' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of precision agriculture hardware devices attached to or integrated with equipment assets. Includes GPS/RTK receivers, VRA controllers, NDVI sensors, yield monitors, flow meters, section control modules, and ISOBUS terminals. Captures device type, manufacturer, model, serial number, firmware version, calibration date, calibration status, accuracy specification (RTK sub-inch), communication protocol, parent asset assignment, and activation status. Supports precision agriculture hardware lifecycle management and calibration compliance.' .

ind:CalibrationEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Calibration Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of calibration activities performed on precision agriculture devices and equipment sensors. Captures calibration date, device/sensor calibrated, calibration type (GPS accuracy check, flow meter calibration, yield monitor calibration, sprayer nozzle check), technician performing calibration, calibration standard used, pre-calibration reading, post-calibration reading, pass/fail result, next calibration due date, and certificate reference. Ensures measurement accuracy for VRA prescriptions, yield data integrity, and regulatory compliance.' .

ind:AssetInspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Scheduled and ad-hoc inspection records for agricultural equipment assets covering safety, regulatory, and operational readiness checks. Captures inspection type (pre-season, OSHA safety, EPA emissions, DOT roadworthiness, insurance), inspection date, inspector identity, asset inspected, checklist items evaluated, pass/fail per item, overall inspection result, deficiencies noted, corrective actions required, re-inspection due date, and regulatory certificate issued. Supports OSHA compliance, insurance requirements, and ISO 55000 asset condition monitoring.' .

ind:AssetAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of equipment asset assignments to farm operations, fields, operators, and cost centers over time. Captures asset reference, assigned-to entity type (field, farm unit, operator, crop enterprise), assignment start date, assignment end date, primary operator, backup operator, assigned cost center (SAP CO), assignment purpose (planting season, harvest, custom hire), and utilization hours during assignment period. Enables CAPEX/OPEX cost allocation by crop enterprise and supports fleet scheduling across multiple farm locations.' .

ind:RentalLease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Rental Lease' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of external equipment agreements including rentals, leases, and contract farming services (custom hire) for agricultural machinery. Covers equipment obtained from external providers, leased out to third parties, and contract services where external operators perform field operations or the enterprise provides equipment/operators to others. Captures agreement type (operating lease/finance lease/rental/custom hire inbound/custom hire outbound), agreement number, counterparty identity, asset or equipment description, service type for custom hire (planting, spraying, harvesting, hauling), lease terms (start/end dates, payment schedule, mileage/hours cap, return conditions, early termination), rate structure (per acre, per hour, monthly, seasonal), total agreement value, field/acreage covered, quality/performance metrics, insurance requirements, invoice reference, and SAP FI lease accounting reference (IFRS 16). Supports fleet cost optimization decisions between owned, leased, rented, and custom-hired equipment, revenue recognition for outbound contract services, and CAPEX/OPEX planning.' .

ind:WarrantyClaim rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Warranty Claim' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of warranty claims submitted to equipment manufacturers or dealers for defective parts, premature failures, or manufacturing defects. Captures claim number, asset reference, part/component claimed, failure description, failure date, hours at failure, dealer/manufacturer claim submission date, claim status (submitted/approved/rejected/paid), approved repair cost, reimbursement amount received, and OEM case reference. Supports warranty cost recovery tracking and informs procurement decisions on equipment reliability.' .

ind:Vendor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all approved agricultural input suppliers and service providers including seed companies, fertilizer distributors, agrochemical suppliers, feed ingredient vendors, fuel suppliers, and equipment parts dealers. Captures vendor identity (tax ID, DUNS number), qualification lifecycle (pending, approved, conditional, suspended, disqualified), GLOBALG.A.P. and GFSI certification numbers and expiry dates, EPA/APHIS registration numbers, SDS documentation compliance flags, payment terms, FOB/CIF contract defaults, bank details, and SAP S/4HANA vendor master integration keys. Qualification attributes: qualification date, re-qualification due date, SQF/BRC/IFS certification status, FSMA SVCP compliance status, audit score, and approved input categories. Performance metrics (periodic): on-time delivery rate, fill rate, quality acceptance rate, invoice accuracy, regulatory compliance score, overall scorecard rating, and corrective action tracking. SSOT for supplier identity, qualification status, and performance within the procurement domain.' .

ind:PurchaseOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Purchase Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core transactional record representing a formal PO issued to a vendor for agricultural inputs including seeds, NPK fertilizers, crop protection chemicals, feed ingredients, fuel, spare parts, and operational supplies. Header: PO number, vendor reference, delivery terms (FOB/CIF), incoterms, requested delivery date, total PO value, currency, approval status, SAP MM document number (EKKO), Oracle NetSuite PO reference, and FSMA/EPA compliance flags. Line items: material/SKU code, commodity description, quantity (BU, MT, CWT, or unit), unit of measure, agreed unit price, line total, requested delivery date, plant/storage location, crop season, lot tracking requirement flag, MRL compliance flag, PHI/REI requirements, and GMO status indicator. SSOT for all PO header and line-level data. Maps to SAP MM EKKO (header) and EKPO (item).' .

ind:ProcurementGoodsReceipt rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Procurement Goods Receipt' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Goods Receipt Note (GRN) record capturing the physical receipt and inspection of agricultural inputs at farm, warehouse, feed mill, or processing facility. Header: GRN number, PO reference, vendor delivery note number, receiving location, receipt date/time, overall receipt status, and SAP MM goods movement document number (MIGO). Line items: received quantity vs. ordered quantity, unit of measure, accepted quantity, rejected quantity with rejection reason code, lot/batch number assigned, storage bin/silo assignment, quality inspection status, COA received flag, SDS on file flag, temperature at receipt (for biologicals, vaccines, and cold-chain feed ingredients), and temperature exceedance flag. SSOT for all GRN header and line-level data. Triggers AP invoice three-way match workflow and inventory update. Feeds quality inspection workflow for COA verification and MRL testing.' .

ind:VendorContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal procurement contract governing the supply of agricultural inputs between the enterprise and a qualified vendor. Captures contract type (framework, spot, annual supply agreement), commodity or input category covered, contracted volume (BU/MT/CWT), delivery terms (FOB/CIF), contract start and end dates, auto-renewal flag, penalty clauses, force majeure provisions, GLOBALG.A.P. compliance requirement, EPA registration requirement for chemical inputs, and SAP MM outline agreement document number. Pricing terms: price type (fixed, formula-based, WASDE-indexed, spot), base price, price adjustment formula, volume tier thresholds, minimum order quantity, currency, and effective/expiry dates. SSOT for all contractual agreements and negotiated pricing with vendors — no separate price agreement product exists.' .

ind:PurchaseRequisition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Purchase Requisition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Internal request to procure agricultural inputs initiated by farm operations, agronomy, livestock, or maintenance teams before a formal PO is raised. Captures requisition number, requesting department/cost center, input category (seed, fertilizer, agrochemical, feed, fuel, parts), material description, required quantity and UOM, required delivery date, estimated unit cost, budget availability flag, approval workflow status, approver chain, and SAP MM purchase requisition document number (BANF/EBAN).' .

ind:Rfq rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Rfq' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Request for Quotation issued to one or more qualified vendors for agricultural inputs during competitive sourcing. Captures RFQ number, input category, detailed specifications (crop protection AI concentration, NPK grade/analysis, seed variety and GMO/non-GMO status, feed ingredient nutritional profile), required quantity and UOM, delivery location (farm, warehouse, feed mill), crop season applicability, response deadline, evaluation criteria weights (price, lead time, certification status, quality history), and RFQ status (draft, issued, responses received, evaluated, closed). Supports competitive bidding for spot purchases, seasonal input procurement, and contract renewals. Maps to SAP MM RFQ document (EKKO with document type AN).' .

ind:VendorQuotation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Quotation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Vendor response to an RFQ providing pricing and delivery terms for agricultural inputs. Captures quotation number, vendor reference, quoted unit price, price basis (fixed/spot/index), quantity offered, lead time, delivery terms (FOB/CIF), validity period, certification compliance confirmation (GLOBALG.A.P., EPA registration), and quotation status (received, evaluated, accepted, rejected). Feeds PO creation and contract negotiation workflows.' .

ind:ProcurementApInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Procurement Ap Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable invoice record received from a vendor following delivery of agricultural inputs. Captures vendor invoice number, invoice date, PO reference, GRN reference, invoiced line items with quantities and amounts, tax amount, currency, payment terms (net 30/60/90, early payment discount percentage), due date, three-way match status (PO-GRN-invoice), match discrepancy details, and Oracle NetSuite AP document reference. Includes dispute management: dispute type (quantity discrepancy, price variance, quality rejection, duplicate invoice, missing COA/SDS), disputed amount, resolution status, credit note reference, and root cause category. Procurement-side SSOT for vendor invoice processing and three-way match validation. BOUNDARY: Procurement owns invoice receipt, three-way match validation, and dispute resolution. Finance domain owns payment disbursement, AP ledger posting, and cash management. Three-way match failures escalate within procurement; payment failures escalate to finance.' .

ind:InputCatalog rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Input Catalog' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all procurable agricultural inputs including seeds (variety, GMO/non-GMO, treated/untreated), fertilizers (NPK grades, micronutrients, organic), crop protection chemicals (herbicides, insecticides, fungicides with AI and MRL data), feed ingredients, fuel types, spare parts, and operational supplies. Captures material code, input category, unit of measure, EPA registration number (for chemicals), APHIS permit category (for biologicals), SDS required flag, PHI/REI values, MRL limits, and preferred vendor list.' .

ind:ChemicalCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Chemical Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Regulatory compliance record for each procured crop protection chemical and biological input, including associated Safety Data Sheet (SDS) documentation. Captures EPA registration number, APHIS import permit number, active ingredient (AI) name and concentration, MRL values by commodity and market, PHI (Pre-Harvest Interval) in days, REI (Restricted Entry Interval) in hours, restricted use pesticide (RUP) flag, state-specific registration status, label compliance confirmation, and FSMA preventive controls applicability flag. Includes SDS attributes: SDS document number, revision date, GHS hazard classification, signal word, hazard and precautionary statements, first aid measures, storage requirements, disposal instructions, PPE requirements, emergency contact, and SDS expiry/review date. Required for OSHA HazCom compliance, EPA regulatory reporting, GAP certification, and HACCP compliance.' .

ind:VendorAudit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'On-site or remote audit record for vendor qualification and ongoing compliance verification. Captures audit type (initial qualification, annual surveillance, for-cause), audit date, auditor name and organization, audit scope (food safety, GAP, GMP, HACCP, EPA compliance), findings count by severity (critical, major, minor), overall audit result (pass, conditional pass, fail), corrective action required flag, corrective action due date, and re-audit required flag. Supports FSMA SVCP and GFSI supplier audit requirements.' .

ind:DeliverySchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Delivery Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Planned delivery schedule for agricultural inputs under a vendor contract or blanket PO, aligned with seasonal crop planting calendars and livestock feeding programs. Captures schedule line number, PO or contract reference, input material, planned delivery date, scheduled quantity, delivery location (farm gate, grain elevator, warehouse, feed mill, fuel tank), transport mode (truck, rail, barge), carrier reference, bill of lading (BOL) number, estimated arrival window, and schedule status (planned, vendor-confirmed, in-transit, received, delayed, cancelled). Supports just-in-time delivery of perishable biologicals, seasonal fertilizer pre-positioning, and feed ingredient supply continuity planning.' .

ind:Budget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Procurement budget allocation record by input category, cost center, farm enterprise, and fiscal period. Captures budget period (annual/quarterly), input category (seed, fertilizer, agrochemical, feed, fuel, parts), allocated budget amount, committed spend (derived from open POs), actual spend to date, remaining budget, variance amount and percentage, budget owner, and last revision date. Enables OPEX control, CAPEX vs. OPEX classification for agricultural inputs, and spend analytics by category, season, and farm enterprise. Sourced from Granular Farm Management and SAP CO.' .

ind:Animal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Animal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master record for every individual animal in the herd or flock. Serves as the SSOT for animal identity across the full lifecycle from birth through harvest, sale, or disposal. Captures RFID tag, ear tag, electronic ID (EID), species, breed reference, sex, birth date, birth weight, dam/sire references (self-referencing lineage), origin (born on farm vs. purchased), current herd assignment, current location (pen/pasture), production class, production group assignment, GMO status, current lifecycle stage, and disposition status. Supports APHIS traceability requirements, USDA NAIS/RFID compliance, and COOL country-of-origin documentation.' .

ind:Herd rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Herd' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining a managed herd or flock grouping — the primary operational unit for livestock management. Captures herd name, species, production type (beef, dairy, swine, poultry, sheep, etc.), home location (farm/facility), responsible manager, target head count, current head count, herd classification (breeding, finishing, nursery, etc.), and certification status (organic, GAP, GLOBALG.A.P.). Acts as the organizational anchor for all animal-level records.' .

ind:PenLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Pen Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for physical housing and containment units within the livestock operation — pens, paddocks, pastures, barns, feedlots, farrowing rooms, milking parlors, and processing facilities. Captures location name, facility reference (FK to land domain for parent facility/premises), GPS coordinates, area (acres/sq ft), capacity (head count), housing type, ventilation type, flooring type, biosecurity zone designation, current occupancy, and operational status. Enables spatial tracking of animal movements, feed delivery targeting, welfare audit location references, and biosecurity zone management. Owned by the livestock domain because pen-level granularity is livestock-operational — pen attributes (capacity, biosecurity zone, housing type, ventilation) are livestock-specific and not managed at the land-parcel level. Cross-references the land domain for parent premises/facility identification.' .

ind:BreedingEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Breeding Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for the breeding program — encompassing both breeding activities and semen/embryo inventory management. For breeding activities: captures breeding date, female animal ID, sire ID or semen lot reference, breeding method (natural service, AI, embryo transfer), technician, conception check date, conception result, expected parturition date, and breeding program reference. For semen/embryo inventory: captures sire ID, sire name, breed, genetic registration number, EPD values (calving ease, birth weight, weaning weight, yearling weight, milk, marbling, REA), genomic-enhanced EPD flag, semen supplier, collection date, lot number, quantity on hand (straws/embryos), storage tank ID, storage location (canister/goblet/cane), conception rate history, cost per unit, and quality grade (post-thaw motility). Record type discriminator (breeding_activity vs semen_inventory) separates the two concerns. Supports genetic improvement tracking, EPD analysis, reproductive performance KPIs, AI program planning, and breeding cost accounting.' .

ind:ParturitionRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Parturition Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each birth or calving/farrowing/lambing/kidding event. Records dam ID, sire ID, birth date, birth time, number of offspring, individual offspring IDs, birth weight per offspring, birth type (single, twin, triplet), ease of birth score, colostrum administration, dam body condition score at birth, and attending staff. Initiates the animal master record for newborns and feeds into herd performance reporting.' .

ind:HealthTreatment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Health Treatment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of every veterinary treatment, medical intervention, vaccination, and health protocol template for individual animals or groups. Captures treatment date, animal ID, record type (treatment_instance or protocol_template), treatment type (therapeutic, prophylactic, vaccination, metaphylaxis, arrival processing, parasite control), diagnosis code, clinical signs, drug/product name, active ingredient (AI), dosage, route of administration, withdrawal period (PHI/REI), booster due date (for vaccinations), vaccine manufacturer lot number, treated-by (veterinarian or farm staff), prescription/VFD reference, protocol reference (self-referencing FK for treatments following a protocol template), trigger criteria (temperature threshold, morbidity rate for protocol templates), treatment outcome, re-treatment flag, withdrawal status, earliest eligible harvest date, and veterinarian approval date. Serves as the consolidated SSOT for all animal health interventions and standardized health management procedures. Critical for FSIS antibiotic withdrawal period compliance, FDA VFD documentation, HACCP records, USDA residue avoidance programs, APHIS disease surveillance, GLOBALG.A.P. animal health certification, and herd health protocol management.' .

ind:VaccinationRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Vaccination Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of each vaccination administered to an individual animal or group. Captures vaccination date, animal or group ID, vaccine product name, manufacturer lot number, dosage, route, booster due date, administering technician, veterinary prescription reference, and compliance status against the herd vaccination schedule. Supports APHIS disease surveillance, FSIS pre-harvest food safety, and GLOBALG.A.P. animal health certification.' .

ind:WeightMeasurement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Weight Measurement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of individual or group weight measurements taken at defined production checkpoints (weaning, backgrounding, feedlot entry, pre-harvest). Captures measurement date, animal ID or group ID, scale ID, body weight (lbs/kg), average daily gain (ADG) since last measurement, body condition score (BCS), frame score, measurement method (individual scale, load cell, weigh tape), and operator. Feeds into growth performance tracking, feed conversion ratio (FCR) calculations, and harvest readiness assessment.' .

ind:FeedRation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Feed Ration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for feed nutrition management — encompassing both ration formulations (master) and feed delivery events (transactional). For formulations: captures ration name, version number, target species and production class, formulation date, nutritionist reference, ingredient list with inclusion rates (percent as-fed and DM basis), calculated nutrient profile (crude protein, TDN, NEm, NEg, calcium, phosphorus, trace minerals, vitamins), dry matter basis, target daily intake (lbs/head/day), cost per head per day, mixing instructions, and approval status. For delivery events: captures delivery date and time, pen/group ID, ration reference, quantity delivered (lbs/kg as-fed and dry matter), delivery method (TMR mixer, bunk feeder, automated system), operator, refusal amount, and feed bunk score. Record type discriminator (formulation vs delivery) separates the two concerns. Serves as the SSOT for feed formulation and delivery, supporting NRC nutritional compliance, feed cost allocation per animal, FCR tracking, and ration plan management.' .

ind:FeedDelivery rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Feed Delivery' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of each feed delivery event to a pen or group. Captures delivery date and time, pen/group ID, ration ID, quantity delivered (lbs/kg as-fed and dry matter), delivery method (TMR mixer, bunk feeder, automated system), operator, refusal amount recorded, and feed bunk score. Enables feed cost allocation per animal, FCR tracking, and nutritional compliance verification against prescribed rations.' .

ind:AnimalMovement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Animal Movement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of every animal or group movement between pens, pastures, facilities, or external premises. Captures movement date, animal or group ID, origin location, destination location, movement reason (weaning, backgrounding, feedlot placement, sale, harvest, death), head count moved, transport vehicle ID, driver, and USDA premises ID for inter-premises moves. Supports APHIS traceability, COOL compliance, and biosecurity zone management.' .

ind:AnimalDisposition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Animal Disposition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing every terminal animal lifecycle event — including harvest (slaughter), natural death, euthanasia, condemnation, and sale for salvage. Records disposition date, animal ID, disposition type, cause of death (for mortality events), necropsy results, carcass disposition, and regulatory reporting status.' .

ind:AnimalWelfareAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Animal Welfare Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of periodic animal welfare evaluations conducted at the pen or herd level. Captures assessment date, location, assessor identity, welfare protocol used (e.g., Five Freedoms, PAACO feedlot audit), scored indicators (body condition, lameness score, cleanliness, injury prevalence, mortality rate), overall welfare score, corrective actions required, and certification body reference. Supports GLOBALG.A.P., SQF, and retailer animal welfare audit requirements.' .

ind:SemenInventory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Semen Inventory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record tracking the inventory of semen straws and embryos held for artificial insemination (AI) and embryo transfer (ET) programs. Captures sire ID, sire name, breed, genetic registration number, EPD values (calving ease, birth weight, weaning weight, yearling weight, milk, marbling, REA), genomic-enhanced EPD flag, semen supplier, collection date, lot number, quantity on hand (straws/embryos), storage tank ID, storage location (canister/goblet/cane), conception rate history, cost per unit, and quality grade (post-thaw motility). Supports genetic selection decisions, AI program planning, and breeding cost accounting.' .

ind:VeterinaryPrescription rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Veterinary Prescription' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for veterinary prescriptions and Veterinary Feed Directives (VFDs) issued by a licensed veterinarian for use on the operation. Captures prescription date, issuing veterinarian (DVM license number), drug or medicated feed product, approved species and indication, dosage instructions, withdrawal period, quantity authorized, expiration date, VCPR (Veterinarian-Client-Patient Relationship) reference, and regulatory filing status. Required for FDA VFD compliance and FSIS antibiotic stewardship documentation.' .

ind:AnimalTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Animal Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all livestock transfer events — both purchases (inbound) and sales (outbound) — between the operation and external parties. Captures transaction date, transaction direction (purchase/sale), counterparty premises ID (vendor for purchases, buyer for sales), species, breed, head count, weight (purchase weight or sale weight), price per head or per CWT, total transaction value, transaction channel (direct, auction, video auction, formula), origin state/country, health certificate number, brand inspection certificate, import permit (if applicable for purchases), quarantine period required (for purchases), receiving pen assignment (for purchases), transport carrier, BOL reference, grade and yield basis (for sales), and COOL chain-of-custody documentation. Purchase-specific attributes (quarantine period, receiving pen, import permit) are populated only for purchase transactions. Sale-specific attributes (grade/yield basis, sale channel) are populated only for sale transactions. Serves as the consolidated SSOT for all livestock commercial transfers. Supports livestock cost basis accounting, revenue recognition, enterprise profitability analysis, COOL compliance, and APHIS traceability. Distinguished from procurement/sales domain records by being animal-specific with livestock traceability attributes (health certificates, brand inspections, premises IDs) that generic commercial transaction records do not carry.' .

ind:ProductionGroup rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Production Group' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining a managed production group or lot — a cohort of animals managed together through a defined production phase (e.g., feedlot pen placement, farrowing group, broiler flock, dairy string). Captures group ID, group name, species, production phase (receiving, backgrounding, finishing, lactating, dry, nursery, grow-finish), placement date, placement head count, current head count, target closeout date, target market weight, assigned herd, assigned pen/location, feed ration plan reference, health protocol plan reference, and performance targets (ADG, FCR, mortality rate, feed cost/head). Serves as the operational unit for group-level performance tracking, feed delivery, and closeout cost accounting.' .

ind:MilkProductionRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Milk Production Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of milk yield measurements for individual dairy cows or groups, captured at each milking event or DHIA test-day. Captures milking date, animal ID, milking session (AM/PM/3x), milk yield (lbs/kg), milk fat percentage, milk protein percentage, somatic cell count (SCC), linear score, milk urea nitrogen (MUN), days in milk (DIM), lactation number, and milking parlor/robot ID. Supports DHIA enrollment, milk quality compliance, and dairy enterprise performance management.' .

ind:HealthProtocol rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Health Protocol' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining standardized herd health protocols and treatment guidelines established by the operation\'s veterinarian. Captures protocol name, target species and production class, protocol type (arrival processing, metaphylaxis, vaccination schedule, parasite control), drug products authorized, dosages, administration routes, withdrawal periods, trigger criteria (temperature threshold, morbidity rate), and veterinarian approval date. Serves as the SSOT for standardized health management procedures referenced by treatment and vaccination records.' .

ind:Field rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Field' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each agricultural field or paddock — the foundational spatial and operational entity of the land domain. Captures RTK-accurate GIS boundary geometry (polygon/multipolygon from Esri ArcGIS) with versioned boundary history, field name, code, total area, irrigated area, GPS centroid, elevation, slope, aspect, drainage class, status (active/fallow/retired), sub-field management zones (VRA zones delineated by EC/yield/NDVI), and integration keys to John Deere Operations Center and ArcGIS feature IDs. Supports boundary change tracking for FSA compliance and temporal field geometry. SSOT for all field-level spatial identity, boundary history, and precision management zone definitions.' .

ind:Parcel rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Parcel' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legal land parcel (cadastral unit) as defined by county assessor or land registry records. Stores APN (Assessor Parcel Number), legal description, section-township-range (PLSS), county, state, country, total deeded acres, zoning classification, land use designation, FSA farm/tract number, CLU (Common Land Unit) identifier, and USDA FSA administrative data. One parcel may contain multiple fields and belongs to a farm_unit for operational management. Links to land_ownership for title chain, to lease for tenant agreements, to easement for encumbrances, and to water_right for entitlement tracking. SSOT for legal land identity and government-assigned identifiers.' .

ind:Ownership rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Ownership' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Ownership record linking parcels to legal owners (individuals, entities, trusts, LLCs, partnerships). Captures owner name, ownership type (fee simple, joint tenancy, tenancy in common, life estate, trust, LLC membership), ownership percentage share, deed reference number, deed book and page, recording date, effective date, expiration date (for term interests), title insurance policy number, and ownership status (current/historical/disputed). Supports multi-owner parcels with fractional interest tracking and ownership chain history. Note: land valuation and acquisition financial transactions are owned by the finance domain — this product captures legal ownership records only. SSOT for who legally owns each parcel and the chain of title.' .

ind:Lease rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Lease' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Agricultural land lease agreement record capturing the contractual relationship between landowner and farm operator/tenant for use of agricultural parcels. Stores lease type (cash rent, crop share, flex rent, custom farming agreement), lease start date, lease end date, annual cash rent rate ($/acre), crop share percentage, flex rent base price and trigger mechanism, total leased acres, payment schedule (annual/semi-annual/quarterly), auto-renewal flag, right-of-first-refusal flag, lease document reference, FSA farm number, and lease status (active/expired/terminated/pending/under negotiation). Links to parcel and farm_unit for legal and operational context. Note: lease payment transactions and accounts payable are owned by the finance/invoice domains — this product captures the lease agreement terms only, not financial transactions. SSOT for land tenure agreements and rental obligation terms.' .

ind:SoilProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Soil Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authoritative soil health profile for a defined soil mapping unit or management zone within a field. Stores USDA NRCS soil series name, soil texture class (USDA triangle), soil order/suborder, drainage class, available water capacity (AWC), organic matter percentage (OM), cation exchange capacity (CEC meq/100g), electrical conductivity (EC dS/m), bulk density, soil depth to restrictive layer, NRCS hydric soil flag, prime farmland designation, and profile creation/update dates. SSOT for baseline soil physical and chemical characteristics.' .

ind:LandSoilSample rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Land Soil Sample' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual soil sampling event record capturing laboratory-analyzed nutrient and chemical results for a specific field zone or GPS-referenced sample point. Stores sample date, lab submission date, lab report date, lab name, sample depth (inches), GPS coordinates, management zone ID, pH (1:1 water), buffer pH, organic matter (%), nitrate-N (ppm), phosphorus (P Bray/Mehlich-3 ppm), potassium (K ppm), calcium (Ca ppm), magnesium (Mg ppm), sulfur (S ppm), zinc (Zn ppm), CEC (meq/100g), EC (dS/m), percent base saturation, and COA reference number. Core to NPK fertilizer prescription and VRA planning.' .

ind:ManagementZone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Management Zone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Spatially defined sub-field management zone used for variable rate application (VRA) prescriptions, precision nutrient management, and yield zone analysis. Captures zone name, zone code, zone type (soil type, EC zone, yield zone, topographic zone), delineation method (EC scanning, yield history, satellite NDVI, manual), zone area (acres), GIS polygon geometry, NDVI index value, EC shallow/deep readings, zone classification (high/medium/low productivity), and active flag. Integrates with Trimble Ag and John Deere Operations Center for VRA prescription generation.' .

ind:FieldBoundary rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Field Boundary' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Versioned GIS boundary geometry record for each field, supporting boundary change history as fields are split, merged, or re-surveyed. Stores boundary version number, effective start date, effective end date, geometry type (polygon/multipolygon), coordinate reference system (CRS/EPSG code), boundary source (RTK GPS survey, drone imagery, ArcGIS digitized), total calculated area (acres), perimeter (feet/meters), boundary accuracy class (RTK/sub-meter/meter), ArcGIS feature class reference, and John Deere Operations Center field ID. Enables temporal boundary tracking for FSA compliance and crop insurance.' .

ind:UsePlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Use Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual or multi-year land use planning record assigning intended crop rotation, land use type, and conservation designations to each field for a given crop year. Captures crop year, planned crop (commodity), planned rotation sequence, land use type (row crop, pasture, hay, fallow, cover crop, CRP, wetland), conservation reserve program (CRP) enrollment flag, CRP contract number, planned tillage system (no-till, strip-till, conventional), irrigation plan flag, and plan status (draft/approved/active/completed). Supports FSA farm program compliance and crop insurance acreage reporting.' .

ind:ConservationPractice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Conservation Practice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of conservation and BMP (Best Management Practice) practices implemented on a field or parcel. Captures USDA NRCS practice code (e.g., 340 Cover Crop, 412 Grassed Waterway, 590 Nutrient Management), practice name, installation date, practice area (acres/linear feet), cost-share program (EQIP, CSP, RCPP), cost-share amount ($), practice lifespan (years), certification date, certifying agency, ISO 14001 environmental management reference, and practice status (planned/installed/certified/expired). Supports USDA NRCS program compliance and environmental stewardship reporting.' .

ind:IrrigationZone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Irrigation Zone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Spatial and operational record for all field-level water management infrastructure — the single source of truth for both irrigation delivery systems and subsurface tile drainage systems within a field. For irrigation: captures zone name, system type (center pivot, drip, flood, subsurface drip, linear move, traveling gun), water source (well, river, reservoir, canal), water right permit reference, permitted volume (acre-feet), irrigated acres, application efficiency (%), design application rate (in/hr), soil moisture sensor locations, and ET-based scheduling parameters. For subsurface drainage: captures tile system type (pattern, random, interceptor), tile material (clay, concrete, corrugated plastic/HDPE), tile diameter (inches), tile depth (inches), outlet location GPS, drainage area (acres), drainage coefficient (inches/day), tile map GIS reference, installation contractor, installation year, estimated cost, system condition (good/fair/poor), and drainage district permit reference. Integrates with John Deere Operations Center for precision water management. Links to field for spatial context and to water_right for entitlement compliance. SSOT for all field-level water infrastructure including both irrigation and drainage.' .

ind:FarmUnit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Farm Unit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational farm unit grouping fields and parcels under a single management structure — typically corresponding to a USDA FSA farm number and tract number. Captures farm name, FSA farm number, FSA tract number, operating entity name, farm manager, total operated acres (owned + leased), county, state, primary commodity, farm type (grain, livestock, mixed, specialty crop), and operational status (active/inactive). Serves as the top-level aggregation point in the land domain hierarchy: farm_unit → parcel → field. Links to parcels for legal land identity and to fields for operational management. Used for FSA program enrollment, crop insurance unit structuring, enterprise budgeting, and USDA program payment tracking. One farm_unit may span multiple parcels and contain multiple fields. SSOT for the operational hierarchy that links fields and parcels to their managing entity.' .

ind:Easement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Easement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legal easement and encumbrance record for parcels — capturing rights-of-way, utility easements, drainage easements, conservation easements, and access agreements that affect land use. Stores easement type, grantor name, grantee name (utility company, government agency, neighbor), easement area (acres) or corridor width (feet), easement length (feet), recorded document reference, recording date, expiration date (if term easement), compensation paid ($), restrictions imposed, and GIS geometry reference. Critical for land use planning and title due diligence.' .

ind:WaterRight rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Water Right' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legal water right and permit record documenting authorized water use entitlements associated with parcels or farm units. Captures permit number, issuing agency, priority date, right type (surface, groundwater, riparian, appropriative), permitted use, volume (acre-feet/year), flow rate (CFS/GPM), source water body, well registration, aquifer, status (active/inactive/transferred/forfeited), and transfer history. SSOT for water entitlement compliance — critical for western-state prior appropriation doctrine and state water resource regulation.' .

ind:Employee rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Employee' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all agricultural enterprise personnel — permanent staff, seasonal farm workers, agronomists, equipment operators, livestock technicians, processing facility workers, and administrative staff. Captures full identity, employment classification (H-2A visa, migrant, domestic, salaried, hourly), job title, department, hire date, termination date, employment status, work authorization type, I-9 verification status, emergency contact, and SAP SuccessFactors employee ID. SSOT for all workforce identity data across farm operations and processing facilities. Supports E-Verify compliance, MSPA worker disclosure, and seasonal rehire tracking.' .

ind:Position rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authorized headcount positions within the agricultural enterprise organizational structure, including job classification taxonomy. Defines each budgeted role — field crew supervisor, pesticide applicator, irrigation technician, livestock handler, grain elevator operator, food safety auditor — including position code, job family (agronomy, livestock, equipment operations, food processing, administration), pay grade band, FTE allocation, FLSA exemption status, DOL occupational classification (SOC code), H-2A eligible flag, minimum wage tier, physical demands rating, required certifications (pesticide applicator license, OSHA 10/30, HACCP), organizational unit assignment, and the farm operation or processing facility to which the position belongs. SSOT for position definition and job classification taxonomy. Supports workforce planning, DOL H-2A job order filings, USDA labor compliance, and labor cost allocation.' .

ind:LaborContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Labor Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employment and labor agreements governing workforce engagement — individual employment contracts, collective bargaining agreements (CBA), H-2A temporary agricultural worker contracts, and seasonal labor agreements with farm labor contractors (FLC). Captures contract type, effective dates, wage rates, housing and transportation obligations (H-2A), work location, hours guarantees, and DOL job order reference number. Critical for H-2A compliance and FSMA worker protection rule adherence.' .

ind:Payroll rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Payroll' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic payroll processing records for all agricultural employees. Captures pay period start/end dates, gross wages, piece-rate earnings (harvest pay), overtime hours (FLSA), H-2A adverse effect wage rate (AEWR) compliance flag, deductions (taxes, housing, transportation), net pay, payment method, and SAP payroll document reference. Supports DOL wage and hour compliance, H-2A three-fourths guarantee tracking, and labor cost allocation to crop enterprise budgets.' .

ind:TimeEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Time Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual time and attendance records for agricultural workers capturing daily clock-in/clock-out, field assignment, task type (planting, spraying, harvesting, livestock feeding), hours worked, break time, overtime flag, piece-rate units completed, and supervisor approval status. Integrates with SAP SuccessFactors time management and supports FLSA compliance, H-2A three-fourths guarantee calculations, and labor cost allocation to specific fields and crop operations.' .

ind:WorkAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Work Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational assignment and shift scheduling of employees and crews to specific farm tasks, fields, equipment, or livestock operations. Captures assignment type (field crew, equipment operator, spray crew, harvest crew, livestock handler), assigned field or facility, assigned employee or crew, start and end dates, shift start/end times, shift pattern (rotating, fixed, split), days of week, crew size, supervisor, seasonal validity, schedule name, and assignment status. SSOT for all labor scheduling and field assignment data. Supports workforce planning, labor scheduling across planting and harvest seasons, REI (Restricted Entry Interval) compliance by scheduling field re-entry after pesticide applications, and full traceability of who performed which agricultural operation and when.' .

ind:WorkforceCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Workforce Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master registry of all professional certifications, licenses, and compliance credentials held by agricultural workers. Covers pesticide applicator licenses (EPA private/commercial/public categories, state license number, issuing state agency, certification categories for field crops, ornamental, right-of-way), OSHA 10/30-hour safety cards, HACCP certification, GAP training completion, forklift operator certification, CDL (commercial driver license), food handler permits, GLOBALG.A.P. worker training certificates, and continuing education units (CEU). Tracks certification type, issuing authority, issue date, expiration date, renewal status, license number, CEU hours completed, state agency reference, and license category. SSOT for ALL worker credential and license data — including pesticide applicator licenses. Supports EPA pesticide applicator compliance, state department of agriculture audits, OSHA verification, GLOBALG.A.P. certification readiness, and CDL/DOT compliance.' .

ind:TrainingEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Training Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Training sessions and per-employee attendance/completion records for the agricultural workforce. Covers GAP awareness, HACCP food safety, pesticide safety (WPS/REI/PHI compliance), OSHA hazard communication, H-2A worker rights orientation, sexual harassment prevention, equipment operation, and emergency response training. Captures training type, delivery method (classroom, field, online), trainer, location, date, duration, and per-attendee enrollment date, completion status, assessment score, certificate issued flag, and resulting qualification expiration date. SSOT for all training delivery, enrollment, and completion evidence. Supports FSMA worker training requirements, GLOBALG.A.P. audit documentation, EPA Worker Protection Standard (WPS) compliance, SQF/BRC certification, and pesticide applicator license CEU renewal tracking.' .

ind:SafetyEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Safety Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'OSHA-reportable incidents, near-miss events, safety observations, and associated workers compensation claims for agricultural operations. Captures incident date/time, location (field, grain bin, processing facility, livestock barn), event type (pesticide exposure, equipment injury, heat illness, fall, animal handling injury, near-miss), affected employee(s), severity classification (first aid, OSHA recordable, lost-time, fatality), root cause analysis, corrective actions, OSHA 300 log entry reference, and — when a claim is filed — workers comp claim number, insurance carrier, claim amount, medical treatment type, lost workdays, subrogation flag, return-to-work date, and claim status. SSOT for the full safety lifecycle from incident through workers compensation resolution. Supports OSHA 300/300A annual reporting, experience modification rate (EMR) management, BMP safety programs, agricultural insurance premium optimization, and return-to-work program management.' .

ind:LaborCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Labor Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'H-2A temporary agricultural worker visa compliance, MSPA migrant labor protection, and employer-provided housing management records. Tracks DOL job order number, visa petition status, worker country of origin, arrival/departure dates, three-fourths guarantee hours tracking, AEWR wage compliance verification, MSPA disclosure records, housing facility assignments (facility, unit, assigned workers, occupancy dates, housing type, capacity, rent deductions, inspection dates, OSHA/EPA housing standard compliance status). SSOT for all DOL-regulated worker welfare obligations including housing provision and assignment, transportation, wage guarantees, and migrant worker protections. Critical for DOL audit readiness, APHIS/USCIS compliance, state migrant labor housing inspections, and seasonal agricultural labor program management.' .

ind:BenefitEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Benefit Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee benefit plan enrollment records covering health insurance (medical, dental, vision), life insurance, disability, 401(k)/retirement plans, FSA/HSA accounts, and agricultural worker-specific benefits (employer-provided housing allowance, transportation subsidy, H-2A mandated housing and meals provision, tool/equipment allowance). Captures plan type, coverage tier (employee-only, employee+spouse, family), enrollment date, effective date, termination date, dependent coverage details, employee contribution amount, employer contribution amount, benefit carrier reference, and ACA eligibility determination. Tracks seasonal worker benefit eligibility based on hours worked and lookback period, agricultural cooperative benefit pool participation, and COBRA continuation rights. SSOT for all employee benefit enrollment and eligibility data. Integrates with SAP SuccessFactors Benefits Administration and supports ACA employer mandate reporting (Forms 1095-C), H-2A housing/meals benefit compliance, and seasonal workforce benefit administration.' .

ind:PerformanceReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee performance evaluation and disciplinary action records for the agricultural workforce. Covers annual reviews, mid-season assessments, probationary evaluations, and progressive discipline (verbal warning, written warning, suspension, termination recommendation). Captures record type (review or disciplinary), review period, reviewer/HR representative, overall rating, competency ratings (agronomic knowledge, equipment operation, safety compliance, productivity), goal achievement, policy violation type (safety, attendance, conduct, food safety protocol), disciplinary level, corrective action plan, employee acknowledgment, appeal outcome, and calibration status. SSOT for all employee performance and conduct records. Supports talent management, promotion decisions, seasonal rehire prioritization, union grievance documentation, OSHA anti-retaliation compliance, and wrongful termination risk mitigation in SAP SuccessFactors.' .

ind:LeaveRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Leave Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Employee leave and absence management records covering FMLA (including intermittent leave for chronic conditions), state-mandated paid sick leave, personal leave, vacation/PTO, bereavement, jury duty, military leave, agricultural seasonal layoff periods, and H-2A worker early departure or contract completion requests. Captures leave type, requested start/end dates, approved start/end dates, leave reason, FMLA eligibility flag (12-month/1,250-hour lookback), intermittent leave flag, approval status, approving supervisor, return-to-work date, and medical clearance flag. Tracks harvest-critical leave restriction windows where operational necessity may limit discretionary leave approvals, H-2A early departure impact on three-fourths guarantee calculations, and seasonal layoff-to-rehire cycles. SSOT for all employee absence and leave data. Integrates with SAP SuccessFactors Absence Management and supports FMLA compliance, labor scheduling during critical planting and harvest windows, and seasonal workforce availability forecasting.' .

ind:Plan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Seasonal and annual workforce planning records projecting headcount requirements by farm operation, facility, position type, and time period — with integrated recruitment pipeline tracking. Planning attributes: planning cycle (annual, seasonal, ad-hoc), farm operation or facility reference, position reference, planned headcount by role, actual headcount, H-2A worker count, domestic worker count, planned labor hours, planned labor cost, variance to actuals, and plan approval status. Recruitment pipeline attributes: requisition number, recruitment channel (direct hire, farm labor contractor, H-2A agent, job fair, referral), applicant count by stage, interview stages, offer status, offer acceptance rate, time-to-fill, and start date. SSOT for workforce demand planning and recruitment pipeline data. Supports H-2A job order preparation (DOL requires documented domestic recruitment effort before H-2A petition), seasonal hiring campaign management, farm labor contractor (FLC) engagement planning, CAPEX/OPEX labor budgeting, and headcount variance analysis. Integrates with SAP SuccessFactors Recruiting Management and Granular Farm Management for crop-driven labor demand forecasting.' .

ind:Invoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core accounts receivable invoice header representing the primary billing document issued to food manufacturers, distributors, cooperatives, and agricultural buyers. Captures invoice number, billing date, due date, total amount, tax, currency, payment terms, invoice status (draft/issued/partially_paid/paid/void/disputed), invoice type (commodity sale, service, weight-ticket settlement, contract settlement, advance billing, intercompany transfer, cooperative patronage), and source transaction references (sales order, delivery, contract). Serves as the SSOT for all outbound billing documents including intercompany transactions between farms, elevators, processing plants, and distribution subsidiaries. Links to invoice_line for item detail, payment_allocation for cash application, and billing_account for customer financial relationship.' .

ind:Line rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Line-item detail for each AR invoice, representing individual commodity lots, crop products, livestock, or service charges billed. Captures line number, commodity code, crop/livestock description, quantity (BU, CWT, MT, head), unit of measure, unit price, pricing basis (spot, futures, contract), gross amount, discount, net amount, tax amount, GLN/lot reference, weight-ticket reference, and revenue recognition category. Supports commodity-based pricing and weight-ticket reconciliation per agricultural billing standards.' .

ind:Payment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all inbound payment transactions applied against AR invoices from agricultural customers including food manufacturers, cooperatives, and distributors. Captures payment date, payment method (ACH, wire, check, EFT, commodity offset), payment amount, currency, bank reference, remittance advice number, payer account, applied invoice references, unapplied balance, payment type (standard, advance/prepayment, deposit, installment), payment purpose for advances (crop pre-purchase, seed advance, input supply advance, storage deposit), linked contract reference for advance payments, and payment status (pending/cleared/returned/voided). Supports seasonal payment terms, deferred payment arrangements, and advance payment programs common in agricultural commodity sales.' .

ind:PaymentAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Payment Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity linking payments to specific invoices and invoice lines, enabling partial payment tracking, multi-invoice settlement, and split-payment reconciliation. Captures allocation date, allocated amount, discount taken, early payment discount, write-off amount, allocation type (full/partial/advance/credit_offset/netting), reconciliation status, and variance amount. Critical for weight-ticket settlement reconciliation, commodity contract payment matching, and cooperative patronage distribution application in agricultural billing workflows.' .

ind:CreditMemo rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Credit Memo' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Credit memo documents issued to agricultural customers to reverse or reduce previously billed amounts. Captures credit memo number, originating invoice reference, credit reason (price adjustment, quality rejection, weight discrepancy, return of produce, MRL non-compliance deduction, grading dispute), credit amount, tax credit, issue date, expiry date, and application status. Supports agricultural-specific credit scenarios including post-harvest quality adjustments and commodity grade disputes.' .

ind:DebitMemo rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Debit Memo' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Debit memo documents issued to agricultural customers to increase previously billed amounts or recover underbillings. Captures debit memo number, originating invoice reference, debit reason (price escalation, additional freight charges, storage fees, fumigation charges, quality premium adjustment, weight-ticket correction), debit amount, tax, issue date, and status. Supports post-settlement adjustments common in grain elevator and commodity trading billing.' .

ind:WeightTicket rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Weight Ticket' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Certified scale weight records for commodity deliveries (grain, oilseed, cotton, livestock) serving as the authoritative quantity source for invoice line reconciliation. Captures ticket number, scale date/time, commodity type, gross weight, tare weight, net weight, moisture content, test weight, dockage percentage, grade factor adjustments (broken kernels, foreign material, damage), scale operator certification, facility/elevator location, truck/trailer ID, driver, and settlement status. Must reconcile to invoice lines per USDA FGIS grain inspection standards and state weights-and-measures regulations. Supports split-load tickets and multi-commodity loads.' .

ind:BillingAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Billing Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts receivable account master for each billing customer entity, representing the financial relationship between the agricultural enterprise and its buyers. Captures AR account number, customer reference, credit limit amount, credit risk category (low/medium/high/watch), credit scoring basis, collateral type (crop lien, equipment lien, letter of credit, surety bond), collateral value, credit review date, credit hold status, credit hold reason, current balance, aging buckets (current/30/60/90/120+ days), payment terms code, currency, last payment date, average days to pay, dispute balance, and account manager. Integrates with SAP FI-AR subledger and Oracle NetSuite AR module.' .

ind:PaymentTerm rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Payment Term' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master defining payment term configurations applicable to agricultural billing including standard net terms, seasonal deferred payment programs, and commodity-specific settlement schedules. Captures term code, term description, net days, discount days, early payment discount percentage, seasonal deferral rules (e.g., post-harvest payment windows), installment schedule flag, installment count, and applicable commodity types. Supports agricultural-specific terms such as deferred grain payment programs and livestock settlement windows.' .

ind:Dispute rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Dispute' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks formal disputes raised by agricultural customers against issued invoices, managing the dispute lifecycle from initiation through resolution. Captures dispute number, disputed invoice reference, dispute date, dispute type (price discrepancy, weight variance, quality rejection, grade dispute, MRL exceedance deduction, duplicate billing, contract terms disagreement), disputed amount, customer claim amount, dispute status (open/under_review/resolved/escalated/withdrawn), resolution date, resolution type (credit issued, price adjusted, claim denied, partial settlement), adjusted settlement amount, assigned reviewer, and escalation history. Supports USDA grain grading dispute workflows and commodity quality arbitration processes.' .

ind:RevenueRecognition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Revenue Recognition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records revenue recognition events triggered by invoice milestones per GAAP ASC 606 and IFRS 15 standards, capturing when and how agricultural revenue is recognized. Captures recognition event date, recognition type (point-in-time delivery, over-time contract, bill-and-hold, consignment release, commodity transfer of title), recognized amount, deferred amount, performance obligation reference, contract modification flag, variable consideration estimate, and GL posting reference. Critical for crop commodity sales where title transfer and revenue recognition timing may differ.' .

ind:BillingSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Billing Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines recurring or milestone-based billing schedules for long-term agricultural contracts including grain storage agreements, crop input supply contracts, and livestock management service agreements. Captures schedule code, billing frequency (weekly/monthly/quarterly/seasonal/milestone), next billing date, billing amount or formula, contract reference, commodity reference, billing start date, billing end date, auto-invoice flag, and schedule status. Supports seasonal billing cycles aligned with crop harvest and livestock production calendars.' .

ind:DunningNotice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Dunning Notice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks dunning (collections) notices issued to agricultural customers with overdue AR balances. Captures dunning notice number, customer AR account reference, dunning level (1st reminder/2nd reminder/final notice/legal action), notice date, overdue amount, oldest invoice date, dunning method (email/mail/phone/legal), response deadline, customer response, and escalation status. Supports collections management for seasonal agricultural buyers who may experience cash flow constraints post-harvest.' .

ind:PriceBasis rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Price Basis' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference table defining commodity pricing bases used in agricultural invoice calculations including futures-based pricing, basis contracts, spot pricing, and formula pricing. Captures basis code, commodity type (corn, soybeans, wheat, cotton, cattle, hogs), pricing method (CBOT futures, CME futures, spot market, DTN market data, WASDE-referenced), basis amount (premium/discount over futures), effective date, expiry date, delivery location, and applicable contract types. Essential for accurate commodity invoice pricing in grain and livestock billing.' .

ind:AdvancePayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Advance Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records advance payments and prepayments received from agricultural buyers prior to commodity delivery or service completion. Captures advance payment number, customer reference, advance amount, currency, receipt date, purpose (crop pre-purchase, seed advance, input supply advance, storage deposit), linked contract reference, expected delivery date, application status (unapplied/partially_applied/fully_applied), and applied invoice references. Common in agricultural commodity markets where buyers secure supply through advance payment programs.' .

ind:WriteOff rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Write Off' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records bad debt write-off transactions for uncollectable AR balances from agricultural customers. Captures write-off number, customer AR account reference, written-off invoice references, write-off amount, write-off date, write-off reason (bankruptcy, insolvency, crop failure hardship, dispute settlement, statute of limitations), approval authority, GL account reference, tax impact, and recovery tracking flag. Supports GAAP bad debt expense recognition and SOX-compliant write-off approval workflows.' .

ind:SettlementStatement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Settlement Statement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic settlement statements issued to agricultural producers, cooperatives, grain elevators, and commodity buyers summarizing all billing transactions within a settlement period. Captures statement number, period type (daily/weekly/monthly/seasonal/crop-year), customer/producer reference, opening balance, invoiced amount, credits issued, payments received, deductions (storage, drying, handling fees), net settlement amount, statement date, and delivery method. Serves as the definitive reconciliation document for grain elevator settlements (per state grain dealer licensing requirements), livestock auction settlements, and cooperative patronage distributions.' .

ind:PriceAdjustment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Price Adjustment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records post-invoice price adjustments applied to commodity billing due to market price changes, quality re-grading, final weight reconciliation, or contract price true-up events. Captures adjustment number, originating invoice reference, adjustment type (final price true-up, quality premium/discount, moisture dockage correction, futures price settlement, basis adjustment, freight differential), original unit price, adjusted unit price, quantity affected, adjustment amount, effective date, and approval status. Common in grain and oilseed billing where provisional invoices are issued pending final commodity pricing.' .

ind:Account rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all customer accounts served by the agricultural enterprise — including food manufacturers, distributors, wholesalers, retailers, cooperatives, and direct consumers. Captures account type (B2B enterprise, B2C individual), legal entity name, tax identification, DUNS number, credit rating, account status, assigned sales territory, Salesforce CRM account ID, SAP customer master number, GLOBALG.A.P. buyer certification status, COOL (Country of Origin Labeling) compliance flag, preferred commodity categories, and account tier classification. This is the SSOT for WHO the business serves.' .

ind:Contact rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Contact' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual contact persons associated with a customer account — including procurement managers, food safety officers, agronomists, and buying agents at food manufacturers, distributors, and retail chains. Stores full name, job title, department, primary phone, email, preferred communication channel, LinkedIn profile, Salesforce CRM contact ID, FSMA point-of-contact flag, HACCP coordinator flag, and opt-in/opt-out marketing consent status per GDPR requirements for international operations.' .

ind:AccountHierarchy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Account Hierarchy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines all inter-account relationships within the customer network — including parent-child corporate structures (global parent to regional subsidiary), cooperative membership networks, buying group affiliations, co-packer relationships, toll processing partnerships, broker-buyer relationships, and franchise networks. Captures both hierarchical (vertical) and lateral (peer-to-peer) relationships with relationship type, direction, hierarchy level, effective and expiry dates, contractual basis flag, hierarchy path, consolidation flag for enterprise-wide credit limit and volume discount aggregation, relationship manager, and both account party references. Supports multi-tier food manufacturer account structures, cooperative grain marketing networks, and network-level analysis of customer interdependencies critical for agricultural commodity trading. This is the single authoritative source (SSOT) for ALL inter-account relationships — vertical hierarchies, lateral affiliations, cooperative memberships, co-packer partnerships, and broker-buyer linkages. No other product in this domain models inter-account relationships.' .

ind:Address rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Address' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical and mailing addresses associated with customer accounts and contacts — including billing addresses, shipping/delivery locations, farm gate pickup points, cold storage facility addresses, and registered business addresses. Stores address type (billing, shipping, registered, farm gate), street lines, city, state/province, postal code, country, GIS coordinates (latitude/longitude from Esri ArcGIS), COOL country of origin code, address validation status, and primary address flag. Supports multi-location customers such as retail chains and distribution networks.' .

ind:Segment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Segment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Market segmentation classifications applied to customer accounts for targeted sales, pricing, and agronomic support strategies. Defines segment name (e.g., Large Food Manufacturer, Regional Cooperative, Direct Farm Consumer, Export Distributor), segment criteria (revenue band, commodity focus, geography, certification tier), applicable pricing tier, assigned account manager pool, GLOBALG.A.P. or SQF certification requirement flag, segment-to-account assignment tracking (assigned segment, assignment date, expiry date, assignment method — manual, rule-based, or ML-scored — segment score, and assignment history). Used by Salesforce CRM for pipeline targeting and SAP SD for pricing condition determination. Enables historical tracking of segment migrations and supports CRM-driven campaign targeting and tiered agronomic service allocation.' .

ind:Preference rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Preference' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures all customer-level preferences governing how the agricultural enterprise engages with and delivers to each account. Includes commodity preferences (preferred crop types, grain grades, organic vs. conventional), packaging preferences (bulk, bagged, containerized), delivery preferences (FOB farm gate, CIF destination, preferred carrier), COOL (Country of Origin Labeling) preferences (required origin countries per commodity, labeling format — full origin, mixed origin, derived from — acceptable and restricted origin country lists, COOL audit frequency, last COOL compliance review date, COOL documentation requirement flag), GMO tolerance flag, certification requirements (USDA Organic, GLOBALG.A.P., SQF, BRC), preferred communication language, invoice delivery method (EDI, email, portal), and payment method preference. This is the single authoritative source (SSOT) for ALL customer preferences — including COOL regulatory compliance preferences. No other product in this domain models customer preferences. Supports USDA COOL regulatory compliance, commodity-specific origin tracking, and customer-specific order configuration.' .

ind:Lead rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Lead' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Prospective customer records captured from agricultural trade shows (e.g., Commodity Classic, World Ag Expo), agronomic field days, USDA market development programs, digital campaigns, and referral networks before formal account qualification. Stores lead source, prospect company name, contact name, commodity interest (grain, produce, livestock products), estimated annual purchase volume (BU or MT), geographic region, lead status (new, contacted, qualified, converted, disqualified), assigned sales representative, Salesforce CRM lead ID, lead score, and conversion date to account. Supports the agricultural sales pipeline from prospect identification through qualification to paying customer activation. Owned by the customer domain as the SSOT for pre-account prospect identity — the sales domain references converted leads via account_id after activation.' .

ind:Case rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Case' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Customer service and support case records capturing complaints, quality disputes, delivery issues, COA (Certificate of Analysis) discrepancies, MRL (Maximum Residue Limit) exceedance claims, FSMA traceability requests, and general inquiries raised by food manufacturers, distributors, and retail customers. Stores case number, case type, priority, status, associated account and contact, commodity lot (LOT) reference, COA reference, root cause category, resolution description, SLA breach flag, and Salesforce CRM case ID. Supports HACCP corrective action tracking and GFSI audit readiness. Owned by the customer domain as the SSOT for customer-facing service interactions — distinct from the quality domain\'s non-conformance records which track internal production quality events, and distinct from the sales domain\'s order dispute records which track commercial transaction disputes.' .

ind:CreditProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Credit Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Credit and financial risk profile for each customer account governing trade credit terms, credit limits, and payment risk classification. Stores credit limit (in base currency), current outstanding balance, available credit, credit rating (internal and external — e.g., Dun & Bradstreet), payment terms (Net 30, Net 60, COD), credit hold flag, credit review date, last payment date, days sales outstanding (DSO), and credit analyst notes. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA FI/AR and Oracle NetSuite AR for real-time credit exposure management.' .

ind:CertificationRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Certification Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks food safety, sustainability, and agricultural certifications held by customer accounts that are required for trade eligibility or preferential pricing. Captures certification type (GLOBALG.A.P., SQF, BRC, IFS, USDA Organic NOP, FSMA compliance, ISO 22000, ISCC, Fair Trade USA, HACCP), certifying body, certificate number, issue date, expiry date, scope of certification, audit grade, and certificate document reference. Critical for COOL compliance, MRL verification, and GFSI-aligned supply chain qualification of buyers.' .

ind:AccountRelationship rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Account Relationship' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures lateral and cross-account relationships between customer entities beyond parent-child hierarchy — including cooperative membership networks, buying group affiliations, co-packer relationships, toll processing partnerships, and broker-buyer relationships. Stores relationship type, both account parties, relationship direction, effective and expiry dates, contractual basis flag, and relationship manager. Enables network-level analysis of customer interdependencies critical for agricultural commodity trading and cooperative grain marketing.' .

ind:CoolPreference rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Cool Preference' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Country of Origin Labeling (COOL) preference and compliance record for customer accounts — particularly food manufacturers, retailers, and distributors subject to USDA COOL regulations. Captures required origin countries per commodity type, labeling format preference (full origin, mixed origin, derived from), COOL audit frequency, last COOL compliance review date, acceptable origin country list, restricted origin country list, and COOL documentation requirement flag. Directly supports USDA COOL regulatory compliance for agricultural commodity sales.' .

ind:Onboarding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Onboarding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Customer account onboarding workflow record tracking the end-to-end process of activating a new customer from lead conversion through first order readiness. Captures onboarding stage (KYC verification, credit assessment, contract execution, EDI setup, SAP customer master creation, Salesforce account activation, COOL preference capture, certification verification), stage completion dates, responsible team member, blocking issues, target go-live date, actual activation date, and onboarding status (in-progress, blocked, completed, cancelled). Ensures all compliance, credit, and system setup steps are completed before first commodity shipment. Critical for agricultural enterprises where new customer activation requires FSMA facility verification, COOL preference capture, and credit limit establishment before any commodity can ship.' .

ind:ConsentRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Consent Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks customer and contact consent for data processing, marketing communications, and third-party data sharing in compliance with GDPR (for international operations) and applicable US privacy regulations. Captures consent type (marketing email, SMS, data sharing with logistics partners, agronomic advisory communications), consent status (granted, withdrawn, pending), consent date, withdrawal date, consent collection method (web form, signed document, verbal with recording reference), and data processing legal basis. Essential for GDPR-compliant international agricultural trade operations.' .

ind:DeliveryLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Delivery Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authorized delivery and receiving locations registered for customer accounts — including grain elevator receiving points, cold storage facilities, food manufacturing plant docks, distribution center addresses, and retail distribution hubs. Captures location name, location type, physical address, GIS coordinates, receiving hours, dock capacity, commodity types accepted, temperature control capability (for perishables), FSMA facility registration number, USDA establishment number (for meat/poultry), preferred carrier, and BOL delivery instructions. Distinct from the address entity — this is an operational receiving point with logistics and compliance attributes.' .

ind:Trial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all agricultural field trials, R&D experiments, and technology evaluations conducted by the research organization. Captures trial name, type (variety/soil_amendment/IPM/GMO_trait/precision_ag), objective, hypothesis, status (planned/active/completed/cancelled), start and end dates, lead researcher, sponsoring program, and trial phase. Type-specific attributes are captured per trial type: for variety trials, links to evaluated variety records; for GMO trait evaluations, captures trait event name, transformation event code, trait type, regulatory submission status, containment protocol, stewardship requirements, and evaluation phase; for IPM efficacy studies, captures pest target organism, efficacy rating, economic threshold, resistance management classification, and MRL compliance; for precision ag pilots, captures technology type, vendor/partner, target KPI, pilot scale, and integration system reference. Tracks key lifecycle milestones (protocol approval, planting, mid-season review, harvest, data lock, report submission). SSOT for all experimental programs, IPM studies, GMO trait evaluations, and precision ag pilots in the research domain.' .

ind:TrialPlot rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Plot' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Represents individual experimental plot units assigned within a field trial. Captures plot identifier, trial reference, field/parcel reference, plot size (acres/hectares), GPS boundary coordinates (GIS polygon), treatment assignment, replication number, block number, row and range position, soil series, and plot-level baseline measurements (pH, EC, OM, CEC). Enables spatial and statistical analysis of trial results at the sub-field level.' .

ind:Treatment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Treatment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines experimental treatments applied within trials, including seed variety, fertilizer formulation (NPK rates), crop protection chemical (AI, MRL), irrigation regime, tillage method, or precision ag technology configuration. Captures treatment code, description, treatment type, application rate, unit of measure (BU/MT/CWT), active ingredient (AI), target trait or outcome, and whether the treatment is a control group. Supports variable rate application (VRA) and replicated experimental design.' .

ind:ExperimentalDesign rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Experimental Design' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures the statistical design, standardized operating protocol (SOP), and execution procedures for each trial. Includes design type (RCBD, CRD, Latin Square, Split-Plot, Strip Trial), number of replications and treatments, blocking structure, randomization seed, statistical power target, alpha level, and design generation software. Governs trial execution protocols: planting date windows, seeding rate specifications, fertilizer application schedules, irrigation management rules, scouting frequency, data collection methods, harvest procedures, and data quality acceptance criteria. Captures protocol version, effective date, approval status, approving agronomist, SOP reference, and GMP/GAP compliance flags. Links to the parent trial and governs how trial_plot assignments and treatment randomization are structured. SSOT for trial methodology, protocol, and standard operating procedures in the research domain.' .

ind:Variety rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Variety' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of crop varieties, germplasm accessions, breeding material, and gene bank holdings evaluated or maintained by the research organization. For released and candidate varieties: variety name, crop species, variety code, maturity group, GMO trait status, trait stack description, breeder, seed company, registration status, USDA APHIS deregulation status, plant patent or PVP certificate number, and key agronomic characteristics. For germplasm accessions and gene bank entries: accession number, crop species, collection origin (country, GPS), collection date, storage location (cold storage/cryogenic), viability status, last germination test date, germination rate %, available seed quantity (grams), donor organization, and CGIAR/USDA GRIN cross-reference. Captures entry stage (accession/wild_relative/landrace/elite_line/experimental_hybrid/pre-commercial/released) to distinguish pipeline position. SSOT for variety, germplasm, and accession identity in the research domain.' .

ind:TrialObservation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Observation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all field observations, scouting measurements, and IoT sensor/telemetry data collected during trials. For manual observations: crop growth stage (BBCH scale), stand count, canopy cover, NDVI reading, pest or disease incidence rating, weed pressure score, lodging score, and observer notes. For IoT and precision ag telemetry: GPS-tagged equipment position, soil moisture sensor readings, EC and temperature probes, NDVI drone scan results, VRA controller logs, and RTK positioning accuracy records. Captures observation date/timestamp, plot reference, observer or device/sensor ID, observation method (manual/drone/sensor/IoT), GPS coordinates, reading type, value, unit, and data quality flag. Supports IPM efficacy analysis, crop scouting workflows, and real-time and post-season precision ag technology performance evaluation. SSOT for all field-collected and sensor-collected trial data in the research domain.' .

ind:YieldMeasurement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Yield Measurement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures plot-level and field-level yield data collected at harvest for each trial plot, including harvested weight, moisture content at harvest, test weight, adjusted yield (BU/acre or MT/ha at standard moisture), harvest date, combine or harvester equipment ID, and harvest method. Supports YPM (Yield Per Acre Metric) benchmarking, variety performance ranking, and statistical yield analysis across treatments and replications.' .

ind:ResearchSoilSample rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Research Soil Sample' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records soil sampling events and laboratory analysis results specifically for trial plots and research fields. Captures sample ID, sampling date, depth (cm), GPS coordinates, lab submission reference, and analytical results including pH, EC, OM%, CEC, macro-nutrients (N, P, K), micro-nutrients, texture class, bulk density, and water-holding capacity. Supports soil amendment experiment design, baseline characterization for trial plots, and research-specific soil health tracking. Research-domain SSOT for trial-linked soil data — distinct from the land domain which owns operational soil health records for production fields.' .

ind:TreatmentApplication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Treatment Application' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of each treatment application event on a trial plot, including full input material traceability and consumption tracking. Captures application date and time, applied treatment reference, actual application rate, unit of measure, application method (broadcast/banded/foliar/drip), equipment used, operator ID, weather conditions at application (temperature, wind speed, humidity), PHI (Pre-Harvest Interval) compliance flag, and REI (Restricted Entry Interval) end datetime. Captures protocol deviation notes. Includes complete input material records: seed lot, fertilizer batch, crop protection product reference (LOT/GRN), soil amendment batch, quantity consumed, cost per unit, total cost, and inventory drawdown reference. Supports regulatory traceability of materials used in USDA APHIS-regulated trials, research COGS tracking, input efficacy correlation analysis, and research-specific input consumption reporting.' .

ind:StatisticalResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Statistical Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores all statistical analysis outputs, performance benchmarks, and derived metrics generated from trial data. For individual trial analyses: ANOVA tables, LSD/HSD mean separation results, regression coefficients, treatment means, standard errors, CV%, p-values, and significance codes. For multi-environment trial (MET) analyses and performance benchmarks: aggregated variety performance including mean yield (BU/acre or MT/ha), yield stability index (Finlay-Wilkinson, GGE biplot), disease resistance performance ratings, standability score, geographic region, crop year, and comparison to check variety. Captures analysis run date, statistical method, software reference (SAS/R/JMP), response variable, trial and experimental design reference, and analyst ID. Supports publication-ready trial reporting, seed selection recommendations, commercial variety release decisions, and internal crop improvement decision-making. SSOT for all analytical outputs, derived performance benchmarks, and MET summary statistics in the research domain.' .

ind:IpmStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Ipm Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures the results of Integrated Pest Management (IPM) efficacy studies, recording pest or disease target organism, efficacy rating (% control), treatment product and rate, application timing relative to pest threshold, economic threshold comparison, resistance management classification, and MRL compliance status. Links to trial_plot and treatment_application records. Supports EPA registration data submissions and internal IPM program optimization.' .

ind:TraitEvaluation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trait Evaluation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for GMO biotech trait evaluation studies, capturing trait event name, transformation event code, trait type (herbicide tolerance, insect resistance, drought tolerance, yield enhancement), regulatory submission status (USDA APHIS petition number, EPA registration, FDA consultation), containment protocol reference, stewardship requirements, and evaluation phase (greenhouse/confined field/non-regulated). Supports USDA APHIS biotech regulatory submissions and internal biotech pipeline tracking.' .

ind:IpRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Ip Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages intellectual property and patent records associated with agricultural research outputs, including plant variety protection (PVP) certificates, utility patents, provisional applications, trade secrets, and licensing agreements. Captures IP type, filing date, grant date, expiration date, jurisdiction, patent number, PVP certificate number, inventor list, assignee, licensing status, royalty terms, and freedom-to-operate (FTO) assessment status. Supports internal innovation pipeline and IP portfolio management.' .

ind:Program rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines overarching R&D programs, breeding pipelines, and innovation initiatives that govern collections of related trials. For research programs: program name, strategic objective, crop focus, funding source, budget allocation, program lead, start and end dates, sponsoring division, external partner organizations, and alignment to USDA NIFA or industry grant references. For breeding pipelines: breeding cycle year, current pipeline stage (F2/F3/BC/PYT/AYT/EYT/pre-commercial), advancement decision and date, decision maker, selection criteria met, estimated commercial release year, and linked variety records. Captures program type (research/breeding/precision_ag/sustainability) to distinguish program categories. Supports strategic R&D portfolio management, crop improvement tracking, breeding pipeline advancement, and innovation pipeline visibility. SSOT for all research programs and breeding pipelines in the research domain.' .

ind:TrialSite rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Site' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for physical locations where field trials are conducted, including research stations, cooperator farms, and university extension sites. Captures site name, site code, address, GPS centroid coordinates, total trial area (acres), climate zone, USDA hardiness zone, primary soil series, irrigation availability, containment classification (for GMO trials), site manager contact, and cooperator agreement reference. Distinct from the land domain\'s field/parcel records as it captures research-specific site metadata.' .

ind:PerformanceBenchmark rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Benchmark' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Aggregated seed and variety performance benchmarks derived from multi-environment trial (MET) data, capturing variety reference, crop year, geographic region, mean yield (BU/acre or MT/ha), yield stability index, disease resistance performance ratings, standability score, and comparison to check variety. Represents the authoritative benchmark record used for seed selection recommendations and commercial variety release decisions. Distinct from raw yield_measurement records.' .

ind:BiotechSubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Biotech Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all regulatory submissions made to governing bodies (USDA APHIS, EPA, FDA, FSIS) in support of research activities, including biotech deregulation petitions, pesticide registration data packages, new variety registrations, and FSMA research exemption filings. Captures submission type, agency, submission date, docket or petition number, submission status (pending/under review/approved/rejected), response due date, assigned regulatory affairs contact, and linked trial or GMO trait evaluation.' .

ind:PrecisionAgPilot rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Precision Ag Pilot' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for precision agriculture technology pilot programs evaluating new tools such as RTK-guided variable rate application (VRA), drone-based NDVI sensing, IoT soil moisture networks, AI-driven planting prescriptions, and autonomous equipment trials. Captures pilot name, technology type, vendor/partner, pilot objective, target KPI (OEE, yield uplift, input reduction %), pilot scale (acres), start and end dates, and integration system reference (John Deere Operations Center, Climate FieldView).' .

ind:TelemetryEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Telemetry Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures IoT and telematics data events generated during precision agriculture pilot operations, including GPS-tagged equipment position, sensor readings (soil moisture, EC, temperature), NDVI drone scan results, VRA controller logs, and RTK positioning accuracy records. Captures event timestamp, device or sensor ID, pilot reference, plot reference, reading type, value, unit, and data quality flag. Supports real-time and post-season analysis of precision ag technology performance.' .

ind:Cooperator rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Cooperator' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for external cooperating entities that participate in agricultural field trials and research programs, including cooperator farms, universities, extension services, and research institutions. Captures cooperator name, organization type, contact details, address, GPS location, cooperator agreement reference and terms, material transfer agreement (MTA) status, active trial count, historical participation years, preferred crop focus, data sharing consent status, and confidentiality agreement reference. Research-domain SSOT for partner entities engaged in R&D activities — distinct from the customer domain which manages commercial customer relationships. Cross-domain boundary: if a cooperator is also a commercial customer, the customer domain owns the commercial identity; this domain owns the research partnership identity.' .

ind:TrialProtocol rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Protocol' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the standardized operating procedures and protocols governing how a trial is conducted, including planting date windows, seeding rate specifications, fertilizer application schedules, irrigation management rules, scouting frequency, data collection methods, harvest procedures, and data quality acceptance criteria. Captures protocol version, effective date, approval status, approving agronomist, SOP reference, and GMP/GAP compliance flags. Ensures reproducibility and regulatory defensibility of trial results.' .

ind:Accession rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Accession' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for germplasm accessions held in the research gene bank or breeding program, including wild relatives, landraces, elite lines, and experimental hybrids. Captures accession number, crop species, collection origin (country, GPS), collection date, storage location (cold storage/cryogenic), viability status, last germination test date, germination rate %, available seed quantity (grams), donor organization, and CGIAR/USDA GRIN cross-reference. Supports crop improvement and biodiversity conservation programs.' .

ind:BreedingPipeline rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Breeding Pipeline' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the internal crop improvement and breeding pipeline stages from early-generation selection through commercial variety release. Captures pipeline entry name, crop, breeding cycle year, current pipeline stage (F2/F3/BC/PYT/AYT/EYT/pre-commercial), advancement decision, advancement date, decision maker, selection criteria met, estimated commercial release year, and linked variety and germplasm accession records. Supports strategic R&D portfolio management and innovation pipeline visibility.' .

ind:InputUsage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Input Usage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of research-specific input materials consumed during trials, including seed lots, fertilizer batches, crop protection products, and soil amendments. Captures input material reference (LOT/GRN), quantity used, unit of measure, trial plot reference, application date, cost per unit, total cost, and inventory drawdown reference. Supports research COGS tracking, input efficacy correlation, and regulatory traceability of materials used in USDA APHIS-regulated trials.' .

ind:Shipment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Shipment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for every agricultural shipment — grain, produce, livestock feed, and processed food movements from farm to food manufacturer or retailer. Master record capturing shipment identity, BOL/AWB legal documentation (shipper, consignee, freight terms, seal numbers, electronic signatures per 49 CFR), origin and destination facility, commodity lot (LOT), carrier assignment, transport mode (road, rail, air, sea), shipment status lifecycle, scheduled and actual departure/arrival dates, total weight (MT/CWT/BU), temperature requirements for cold chain, FSMA Sanitary Transportation rule compliance flag, container identifiers, delivery milestone events (pickup confirmation, in-transit checkpoints, border crossing, proof of delivery with GPS coordinates, photo evidence, and electronic signature capture), and exception events (delay, damage, refusal). Single authoritative record for shipment identity, legal shipping documentation, execution tracking, and delivery event history within the supply domain. Subsumes BOL document data and delivery event tracking — no separate products exist for these concepts.' .

ind:ShipmentLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Shipment Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for line-level detail within each agricultural shipment, representing individual commodity lots loaded on a single shipment. Records commodity SKU, lot number (LOT), quantity (BU/MT/CWT), unit of measure, gross and net weight, pallet count, RFID tag identifiers, temperature zone assignment, COA reference, MRL compliance status, country of origin (COOL), and organic/non-GMO certification reference. Enables lot-level traceability from farm field through delivery to food manufacturer for FSMA Section 204 compliance and one-up/one-back recall response. Single authoritative record for shipment line-item detail within the supply domain.' .

ind:TransportOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Transport Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for TMS-generated transportation orders authorizing and managing the full lifecycle of agricultural commodity movements — from order creation through carrier booking, load planning, and dispatch execution. Captures order type (inbound/outbound/inter-facility), requested and confirmed pickup/delivery windows, priority level, freight terms (FOB/CIF), carrier or 3PL assignment, route plan reference, load type (FTL, LTL, intermodal), FSMA compliance checklist status, equipment type (reefer, dry van, flatbed, hopper), freight rate applied, booking confirmation details (booked capacity, appointment times, cancellation terms, booking status), and load planning details (loading sequence, commodity lot assignments per position, weight distribution, center-of-gravity compliance, temperature zone mapping, dock assignment, vehicle/container ID, planned load start/completion times). Single authoritative record for carrier dispatch authorization, freight capacity commitment, booking management, and load execution planning within the supply domain. Subsumes freight booking and load plan data — no separate products exist for these concepts.' .

ind:Carrier rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Carrier' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all approved freight carriers and 3PL providers in the agricultural supply chain. Master record storing carrier legal name, SCAC code, DOT/MC number, carrier type (trucking, rail, air freight, ocean), service modes, insurance certificate expiry, FSMA Sanitary Transportation certification status, cold chain capability, RFID tracking capability, preferred lane assignments, and rolling performance metrics (on-time pickup/delivery rates, damage claim rate, temperature excursion rate, compliance score, performance tier by evaluation period, total shipments executed, rejected loads count). Single authoritative record for carrier identity, qualification, and operational performance within the supply domain. Subsumes carrier performance tracking — no separate product exists for this concept.' .

ind:Route rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Route' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for planned transportation routes used in agricultural commodity and input movements across the supply chain network. Defines origin facility node, destination facility node, intermediate waypoints, distance (miles/km), estimated transit time by transport mode, preferred carrier assignments, seasonal road restriction flags (spring weight limits, harvest season congestion), cold chain corridor designation, toll and border crossing points, bridge weight limit constraints, and GPS/RTK route geometry reference. Used by TMS for route optimization, freight cost estimation, and VRA delivery planning for precision agriculture inputs. Single authoritative record for transportation route definitions within the supply domain.' .

ind:FreightBooking rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Freight Booking' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the confirmed booking of freight capacity with a carrier or 3PL for a specific transport order. Captures booking confirmation number, carrier assignment, booked capacity (weight/volume), equipment type (reefer, dry van, flatbed, hopper), pickup appointment date/time, delivery appointment date/time, freight rate applied, accessorial charges, booking status, and cancellation terms. Bridges transport order to actual carrier execution and BOL issuance.' .

ind:BillOfLading rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Bill Of Lading' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legal shipping document (BOL) issued for each agricultural shipment, serving as contract of carriage, receipt of goods, and title document. Stores BOL number, shipper and consignee details, carrier name, origin and destination addresses, commodity description, lot numbers (LOT), total weight and piece count, freight terms (FOB/CIF), special handling instructions (temperature, fragile, hazmat), seal numbers, driver and vehicle details, and electronic signature capture. Mandatory for FSMA food safety traceability and COOL compliance.' .

ind:ColdChainReading rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Cold Chain Reading' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for continuous temperature and humidity monitoring data across cold chain shipments of perishable agricultural commodities (fresh produce, dairy, meat, seafood, cut flowers). Records shipment reference, IoT sensor/RFID device ID, timestamp, temperature (°C/°F), humidity (%), GPS coordinates, excursion flag (breach of commodity-specific temperature threshold), alert severity, corrective action taken, and chain-of-custody transfer events. Critical for HACCP compliance, GFSI certification audit evidence, and food safety incident root cause investigation. Single authoritative record for cold chain telemetry within the supply domain.' .

ind:LotTrace rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Lot Trace' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for end-to-end traceability of agricultural commodity lots (LOT) moving through the supply chain from farm origin through storage, processing, and delivery to final customer. Captures lot number, commodity type, originating field/farm, harvest date, GRN reference, current custody facility, chain-of-custody transfer events with timestamps, RFID tag history, split/merge lot events, COA linkage, MRL test results, PHI compliance status, and final disposition (sold, consumed, destroyed). Single authoritative record for lot-level supply chain traceability supporting FSMA Section 204 food traceability rule, GLOBALG.A.P. chain of custody, and one-up/one-back recall response.' .

ind:DeliveryEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Delivery Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures discrete delivery milestone events during shipment execution — including pickup confirmation, in-transit checkpoints, border crossing, customs clearance, delivery attempt, proof of delivery (POD), and exception events (delay, damage, refusal). Records event type, event timestamp, GPS coordinates, driver/carrier agent ID, facility or waypoint, event notes, and electronic signature or photo evidence reference. Feeds real-time shipment visibility and FSMA transportation compliance audit trail.' .

ind:FreightRate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Freight Rate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for freight rate schedules negotiated with carriers and 3PLs for agricultural commodity transportation. Stores rate type (per mile, per CWT, per MT, per BU, flat rate), origin-destination lane, commodity class (NMFC), equipment type, effective and expiry dates, base rate, fuel surcharge formula (DOE index-linked), accessorial rate schedule (including detention/demurrage, lumper, stop-off charges), minimum charge, currency, and contracted volume tier with commitment discount. Used for freight cost estimation, carrier selection optimization, and freight audit variance analysis against actual invoices. Single authoritative record for contracted freight pricing within the supply domain.' .

ind:CarrierPerformance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Carrier Performance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks operational performance metrics for each carrier across agricultural shipment lanes. Records carrier ID, evaluation period, on-time pickup rate, on-time delivery rate, damage claim rate, temperature excursion rate (cold chain), FSMA compliance score, total shipments executed, rejected loads count, average transit time vs. contracted, and overall performance tier (preferred/approved/probation/suspended). Drives carrier selection decisions and 3PL contract renewals.' .

ind:FreightInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Freight Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for carrier-issued freight invoices covering transportation services on agricultural shipments. Captures invoice number, carrier ID, shipment/BOL references, invoice date, payment due date, line-item charges (base freight, fuel surcharge, accessorials, detention/demurrage, lumper fees, stop-off charges), total amount, currency, freight audit status (matched/disputed/approved), variance from contracted rate, three-way match status (rate vs. BOL vs. invoice), and payment status. Single authoritative record for payable-side freight cost documentation within the supply domain — distinct from customer sales invoices in the sales/invoice domains.' .

ind:ServiceContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for supply chain service contracts with carriers, 3PLs, cold storage operators, and logistics service providers. Captures contract number, counterparty legal name and type, contract effective and expiry dates, service scope (lanes, modes, commodity types covered), committed volume (MT/loads per period), SLA terms (transit time targets, on-time delivery percentage, temperature compliance thresholds), penalty and incentive clauses, FSMA compliance obligations, insurance requirements (cargo, liability, workers comp), and contract status (draft/active/expired/terminated). Single authoritative record for logistics service agreements within the supply domain — distinct from procurement input supply contracts owned by the procurement domain.' .

ind:Facility rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Facility' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all supply chain network nodes used in agricultural logistics — grain elevators, cold storage warehouses, processing plants, distribution centers, port terminals, cross-dock facilities, and fumigation stations. Stores facility name, type, physical address, GPS coordinates, storage capacity (MT/BU by commodity), temperature zone configuration, USDA/FDA facility registration number, FSMA facility registration status, operating hours, dock count and type (inbound/outbound/cross-dock), RFID reader infrastructure, weighbridge availability, and facility manager contact. Single authoritative record for logistics network node identity within the supply domain.' .

ind:CustomsDeclaration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Customs Declaration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for import/export customs declarations on cross-border agricultural commodity shipments. Captures declaration number, shipment reference, commodity HS tariff code, country of origin (COOL compliance), declared value, gross weight, phytosanitary certificate number (APHIS PPQ 586/587), import/export permit number, customs broker details, duty and tariff amounts, anti-dumping duty flag, inspection hold status (USDA/CBP), clearance date, and port of entry/exit. Required for APHIS import compliance, USDA export certification, FDA prior notice, and international agricultural trade documentation. Single authoritative record for customs and trade compliance within the supply domain.' .

ind:LoadPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Load Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational load planning record that defines how agricultural commodities are physically loaded onto a transport vehicle or container. Captures transport order reference, vehicle/container ID, loading sequence, commodity lot assignments per position, weight distribution, center-of-gravity compliance flag, temperature zone mapping, maximum load weight vs. actual, loading dock assignment, planned load start and completion times, and loader crew reference. Ensures safe and compliant loading for road weight limits and cold chain integrity.' .

ind:InboundPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Inbound Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Forward-looking inbound logistics plan coordinating the scheduled arrival of agricultural inputs (seeds, fertilizers, crop protection chemicals, feed ingredients) and harvested commodities at receiving facilities. Captures expected supplier/farm origin, commodity or input type, planned quantity (MT/BU), scheduled arrival window, assigned receiving dock, pre-arrival quality inspection requirement, cold chain pre-conditioning requirement, and WMS receiving task pre-creation status. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA MM inbound delivery and Manhattan Associates WMS appointment scheduling.' .

ind:LogisticsPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Logistics Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all forward-looking logistics plans coordinating both inbound arrivals and outbound dispatches of agricultural commodities and inputs at supply chain facilities. Captures plan direction (inbound/outbound), origin and destination, commodity or input type (seeds, fertilizers, crop protection chemicals, feed ingredients, harvested commodities), planned quantity (MT/BU), scheduled arrival/dispatch window, assigned receiving or shipping dock, carrier assignment, transport mode, cold chain requirements, pre-arrival quality inspection requirement, pre-conditioning requirement, export documentation requirements (COOL, phytosanitary), sales order or PO reference, and WMS task pre-creation status. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA MM/SD delivery documents and Manhattan Associates WMS appointment scheduling and wave planning. Single authoritative record for logistics planning in both directions — no separate inbound or outbound plan products exist.' .

ind:FsmaCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Fsma Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for operational compliance records documenting adherence to FSMA Sanitary Transportation of Human and Animal Food rule (21 CFR Part 1, Subpart O). Captures shipment reference, vehicle/container sanitation verification status (wash ticket reference), previous cargo declaration, temperature control plan reference, shipper-carrier written agreement status per §1.908(a), training record reference for driver/carrier per §1.910, inspection findings, non-conformance notes, corrective action taken, CAPA reference, and regulatory audit trail with timestamps. Single authoritative record for FSMA transportation compliance within the supply domain — mandatory for FDA enforcement readiness and food safety audit response.' .

ind:Commodity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Commodity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference catalog of all agricultural commodities traded and produced by the enterprise — the raw, unprocessed agricultural outputs before they become sellable products. Includes grains (corn, wheat, soybeans, rice, barley), oilseeds (canola, sunflower), fiber crops (cotton), produce categories, and livestock commodity classes. Captures USDA commodity codes, HS (Harmonized System) tariff codes for international trade classification, commodity class, unit of measure (BU, CWT, MT), GMO status flag, organic eligibility, and commodity exchange ticker symbols (CBOT, CME). Linked to grading_standard and mrl_threshold for quality and compliance reference. Distinct from product_master: commodity defines WHAT is grown/raised; product_master defines HOW it is packaged and sold.' .

ind:Master rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Master' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Central master catalog and SSOT for all sellable, transferable, and internally consumed agricultural products. Every product in the enterprise — whether a raw commodity packaged for sale, a processed good, a seed variety, a livestock-derived item, or an agricultural input — has exactly one product_master record. Captures SKU, PLU, UPC, GTIN codes, product hierarchy classification, brand, product line, net weight, packaging type, shelf life, storage requirements (temperature range, humidity, light sensitivity), and product lifecycle status (active, discontinued, seasonal). Distinguishes between conventional, organic (NOP-certified), and non-GMO product lines. Type-specific detail is held in linked detail tables (seed_variety, livestock_product, processed_good, input_product). Aligned with SAP S/4HANA Material Master (MM module).' .

ind:Hierarchy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Hierarchy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the multi-level classification hierarchy for all agricultural products — from enterprise product division down through category, sub-category, product family, and individual SKU. Supports USDA commodity groupings, internal merchandising hierarchies, and retail category management structures. Enables roll-up reporting across crop commodities, livestock products, processed goods, seed/input products, and value-added lines. Used in SAP S/4HANA SD and MM modules for pricing and reporting hierarchies.' .

ind:SeedVariety rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Seed Variety' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all seed varieties and cultivars used in crop production and sold as input products. Captures variety name, crop species, breeder/licensor, trait package (herbicide tolerance, insect resistance), GMO status, non-GMO verification status, relative maturity rating, yield potential rating, disease resistance profile, and seed treatment applied. Tracks NOP organic seed eligibility and APHIS biotech regulatory status. Sourced from Trimble Ag Software and Climate FieldView variety databases.' .

ind:LivestockProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Livestock Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all livestock-derived products including meat cuts, carcasses, dairy products (milk, cheese, butter), eggs, wool, and hides. Captures species, breed source, USDA grade (Prime, Choice, Select), FSIS inspection status, lot number (LOT), slaughter/processing date, aging requirements, cold chain temperature requirements, and COOL (Country of Origin Labeling) designation. Tracks organic and antibiotic-free certification flags. Aligned with FSIS and USDA AMS grading standards.' .

ind:ProcessedGood rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Processed Good' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all value-added and processed agricultural goods including flour, oil, feed pellets, canned produce, frozen vegetables, dried grains, and packaged food products. Captures bill of materials (BOM) reference, processing method, GMP compliance flag, HACCP plan reference, allergen declarations, nutritional profile, net content, packaging format, and shelf life under specified storage conditions. Tracks GFSI certification scheme (SQF, BRC, IFS) applicable to the product. Sourced from SAP S/4HANA PP module.' .

ind:InputProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Input Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all agricultural input products procured and applied in farm operations — fertilizers (NPK formulations, micronutrients, lime), crop protection chemicals (herbicides, fungicides, insecticides, nematicides), adjuvants, soil amendments, biological inoculants, and seed treatments. Captures active ingredient (AI), EPA registration number, SDS reference, MRL thresholds (linked to mrl_threshold), PHI (Pre-Harvest Interval), REI (Restricted Entry Interval), restricted use pesticide (RUP) flag, signal word, formulation type, application rate range, and organic-approved status (OMRI listing). Aligned with EPA FIFRA registration and USDA NOP compliance requirements. Links to product_master for SKU/procurement identity.' .

ind:OrganicCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Organic Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks USDA National Organic Program (NOP) organic certification records for products, product lines, and production operations. Captures certifying agent name, certificate number, certification scope (crops, livestock, handling/processing), certification effective date, expiration date, annual renewal status, allowed materials list, and any suspension or revocation events. Links products to their certified organic status and supports COOL and organic labeling compliance. Required for organic premium pricing and retail organic claims.' .

ind:GmoDeclaration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Gmo Declaration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records GMO status declarations and non-GMO verification records for agricultural products and commodities. Captures GMO trait description, transformation event identifier (APHIS petition number), approved market status by jurisdiction (US, EU, China), non-GMO verification body (Non-GMO Project, USDA Organic), identity preservation (IP) protocol reference, and testing/verification date. Supports USDA BE (Bioengineered Food Disclosure) labeling compliance and export market GMO documentation requirements.' .

ind:GradingStandard rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Grading Standard' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference catalog of all applicable grading standards and grade specifications for agricultural commodities and products. Captures USDA grade designation (e.g., US No. 1, US Extra Fancy, USDA Prime), commodity type, grading criteria (moisture content, test weight, foreign material tolerance, defect limits), applicable regulation citation, effective date, and administering agency (AMS, FSIS, GIPSA). Supports quality inspection workflows and COA generation. Aligned with USDA AMS and GIPSA official grade standards.' .

ind:MrlThreshold rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Mrl Threshold' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference table of Maximum Residue Limits (MRL) for pesticide active ingredients (AI) on specific agricultural commodities by regulatory jurisdiction. Captures active ingredient name, EPA registration number, commodity or commodity group, MRL value (ppm), regulatory jurisdiction (US EPA, EU, Codex Alimentarius, importing country), effective date, and tolerance type (established, exemption, import tolerance). Critical for pre-harvest interval (PHI) compliance, export documentation, and COA verification. Sourced from EPA and Codex Alimentarius databases.' .

ind:Label rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Label' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages all regulatory and commercial labeling content and compliance records for agricultural products. Covers COOL (Country of Origin Labeling) designations, USDA organic seal authorization, non-GMO label claims, USDA grade shield usage, allergen declarations (FDA Big 9: milk, eggs, fish, shellfish, tree nuts, peanuts, wheat, soybeans, sesame — including intentional inclusion flags, cross-contact risk levels, and allergen control measure references), nutrition facts panel data (macronutrients, micronutrients, caloric value, serving size, analysis method), net weight declarations, and label artwork file references. Captures label version, effective date, regulatory approval reference, applicable markets/jurisdictions, and HACCP allergen control plan linkage. Tracks FDA FSMA labeling and Preventive Controls allergen management compliance, USDA AMS label approval status, and supports SAP S/4HANA QM module label management.' .

ind:Bundle rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Bundle' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines bundled product offerings combining multiple agricultural products or inputs sold as a single commercial package — such as seed + crop protection programs, starter fertilizer + seed treatment packages, feed + supplement rations, or commodity + logistics service bundles. Captures bundle name, bundle type (fixed, configurable), bundle pricing method (sum of components, discounted package, flat rate), minimum order quantity, availability period, and target customer segment. Includes component-level detail: individual component products (FK to product_master), quantity per bundle, unit of measure, substitution allowed flag, component-level pricing contribution, and component sequence/priority. Supports decomposition of bundle orders into individual product fulfillment lines and component-level inventory reservation. Enables value-added selling programs, input supply dealer agreements, and crop input financing packages.' .

ind:BundleComponent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Bundle Component' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association table capturing the individual component products within each product bundle, including component product reference, quantity per bundle, unit of measure, substitution allowed flag, and component-level pricing contribution. Enables decomposition of bundle orders into individual product fulfillment lines and supports component-level inventory reservation. Carries its own business data (quantity, pricing contribution) beyond the simple M:N relationship.' .

ind:SubstitutionRule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Substitution Rule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines approved product substitution and equivalency rules specifying which products can replace another in order fulfillment, procurement, or formulation scenarios due to supply constraints, grade equivalency, seasonal unavailability, or customer-approved alternatives. Captures primary product, substitute product, substitution type (equivalent grade, approved alternative, emergency, seasonal), approval authority, customer acceptance required flag, effective date range, and priority ranking when multiple substitutes exist. Supports supply chain resilience, order fulfillment flexibility, and feed formulation ingredient substitution. Aligned with SAP S/4HANA MM material substitution configuration.' .

ind:ProductCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Consolidated SSOT for all third-party, regulatory, and program certifications and declarations held by agricultural products. Covers: (1) USDA NOP organic certification — certifying agent, certificate number, scope (crops/livestock/handling), effective and expiration dates, annual renewal status, allowed materials list, suspension/revocation events; (2) GMO/bioengineered food declarations — transformation event identifiers (APHIS petition numbers), approved markets by jurisdiction (US, EU, China), Non-GMO Project Verified status, identity preservation (IP) protocol reference, USDA BE labeling compliance; (3) Food safety and sustainability certifications — GLOBALG.A.P., SQF, BRC, IFS, Fair Trade, Rainforest Alliance, Kosher, Halal, ISCC. Captures certification body, certificate number, certification type, certified product scope, issue date, expiration date, audit cycle, verification/testing date, and certificate document reference. Supports organic premium pricing, non-GMO market access, export documentation, and retail label claims.' .

ind:RegulatoryStatus rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Status' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the regulatory approval and market authorization status of agricultural products by jurisdiction — including USDA, FDA, EPA, and international market approvals. Captures product registration number, regulatory agency, approval type (food use, feed use, export approved), approved markets/countries, registration expiration date, pending renewal flag, and any import/export restriction flags. Critical for export compliance, APHIS phytosanitary documentation, and market access management.' .

ind:GlAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Gl Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'General Ledger (GL) chart of accounts master — the authoritative SSOT for all GL account definitions across the agricultural enterprise. Captures account number, account type (asset, liability, equity, revenue, expense), account group, cost element classification, P&L vs balance sheet indicator, currency, consolidation account mapping, IFRS/GAAP dual-ledger flags, and active status. Supports EBITDA reporting by crop enterprise, commodity-level COGS tracking, and SOX financial controls. Referenced by all financial postings across AP, AR, fixed assets, and period-end close.' .

ind:CostCenter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Cost Center' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Cost center and profit center master data representing organizational units and profitability segments used for cost allocation, internal management accounting, and segment reporting across the agricultural enterprise. Captures cost center code, name, hierarchy level (including profit center hierarchy nodes), responsible manager, controlling area, company code, valid-from/to dates, cost center category (production, administration, R&D, field operations), profit center assignment and attributes (commodity/crop segment, livestock operation, supply chain segment), and project cost collection flags. Supports OPEX tracking, crop enterprise budgeting, overhead allocation, COGS allocation by commodity, EBITDA reporting by crop enterprise or livestock operation per GAAP/IFRS segment reporting requirements.' .

ind:CompanyCode rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Company Code' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legal entity and company code master representing individual legal entities within the agricultural enterprise for consolidated financial statements. Captures company code, legal entity name, country, currency, fiscal year variant, chart of accounts assignment, consolidation group, tax jurisdiction, and regulatory filing identifiers (USDA, FDA, SEC). Supports SOX financial controls, multi-entity consolidation, and GAAP/IFRS segment reporting.' .

ind:JournalEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'General ledger journal entry representing all accounting documents including standard postings, intercompany transactions, accruals, reversals, and manual entries with embedded line-level detail. Header captures document number, document type, posting date, document date, fiscal year/period, company code, reference document, posting user, reversal indicator, and approval status. Line-level detail captures GL account, debit/credit indicator, amounts in transaction and company code currencies, cost center, profit center, WBS element, tax code, assignment field, and line item text. For intercompany postings: sending/receiving company code, elimination status, reconciliation status, and netting agreement reference. SSOT for all GL postings across the agricultural enterprise. Supports COGS allocation by commodity, crop enterprise cost tracking, intercompany elimination for consolidated financial statements, and SOX-compliant audit trails for GAAP/IFRS reporting.' .

ind:JournalEntryLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual line items within a GL journal entry capturing debit/credit postings to specific GL accounts. Captures line item number, GL account, debit/credit indicator, amount in transaction currency, amount in company code currency, cost center, profit center, WBS element, tax code, assignment field, and line item text. Supports COGS allocation by commodity, crop enterprise cost tracking, and SOX-compliant audit trails.' .

ind:FinanceApInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Finance Ap Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable invoice representing vendor invoices for agricultural inputs (seeds, fertilizers NPK, crop protection chemicals, feed, equipment parts) with embedded line-level detail. Header captures vendor invoice number, vendor ID, invoice date, posting date, payment terms, gross amount, tax amount, net amount, currency, payment block status, three-way match status (PO/GRN/invoice), and approval workflow status. Line-level detail captures material/service description, quantity, unit of measure (MT, BU, CWT), unit price, line amount, GL account assignment, cost center, purchase order reference, goods receipt reference (GRN), tax code, and commodity classification. Supports COGS allocation by commodity, crop enterprise budget variance analysis, and seasonal input cost tracking.' .

ind:ApInvoiceLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Invoice Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Line-level detail for accounts payable invoices capturing individual line items for agricultural input purchases. Captures line number, material/service description, quantity, unit of measure (MT, BU, CWT), unit price, line amount, GL account assignment, cost center, purchase order reference, goods receipt reference (GRN), tax code, and commodity classification. Supports COGS allocation by commodity and crop enterprise budgeting.' .

ind:ApPayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable payment transaction recording actual disbursements to agricultural input suppliers and service vendors. Captures payment document number, vendor ID, payment date, payment method (ACH, wire, check), bank account, payment amount, currency, cleared invoice references, discount taken, payment run ID, and bank clearing status. Supports seasonal payment cycles aligned with planting and harvest, early-pay discount optimization for input purchases, and cash flow management.' .

ind:CropEnterpriseBudget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Crop Enterprise Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Crop enterprise budget master with embedded line-level detail representing planned financial performance for a specific crop, field, and growing season. Header captures budget ID, crop type, field/farm unit, growing season, budget version (original, revised, final), planned revenue per acre/hectare, planned yield, planned price per unit, and approval status. Line-level detail captures individual cost and revenue categories (seed, fertilizer NPK, crop protection, custom hire, labor, equipment, irrigation, land rent, crop insurance, revenue) with planned quantity, unit cost, planned total, actual amount, and variance. Core to agricultural financial planning, break-even analysis, and ROI analysis per crop enterprise.' .

ind:CapitalProject rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Capital Project' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Capital and project expenditure request, approval, and cost collection record for agricultural investments and operational projects. Covers CAPEX items (tractors, combines, planters, irrigation systems, land improvements, facility construction, technology infrastructure) and OPEX project tracking (field renovation, crop trials, marketing campaigns). Captures request number, asset/project description, category (CAPEX/OPEX), requesting cost center, estimated cost, funding source, business justification, ROI calculation, approval workflow status, approved amount, budget vs actual costs, commitment costs, settlement rule, and project status. Supports CAPEX/OPEX tracking, project cost management, and SOX financial controls.' .

ind:FixedAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Fixed Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Fixed asset master representing capitalized agricultural assets with embedded depreciation schedule, run history, and disposal records. Covers farm equipment (tractors, combines, sprayers, planters), irrigation infrastructure, grain storage facilities (bins, elevators), livestock facilities, land improvements, and technology assets. Captures asset number, description, asset class, acquisition date, acquisition cost, useful life, depreciation method (straight-line, MACRS, Section 179), depreciation area (book, tax, IFRS), accumulated depreciation, net book value, location (farm/field), cost center, insurance coverage, disposal status, periodic depreciation run records (fiscal period, depreciation posted, run status), and disposal proceeds. Supports GAAP/IFRS asset accounting, MACRS tax depreciation for farm equipment, and Section 179 expensing elections common in agricultural operations.' .

ind:PeriodClose rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Period Close' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Period-end financial close task and status record tracking the completion of month-end, quarter-end, and year-end close activities across the agricultural enterprise. Captures close period, company code, close task (accruals posting, depreciation run, inventory valuation at harvest, intercompany reconciliation, grain inventory mark-to-market, financial statement preparation), task owner, due date, completion date, status, dependencies, and sign-off approver. Manages the close calendar including seasonal peaks around harvest settlement and crop year-end. Supports SOX financial controls and GAAP/IFRS reporting timelines.' .

ind:IntercompanyTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Intercompany Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Intercompany financial transaction record capturing cross-entity transactions between legal entities within the agricultural enterprise group (e.g., commodity transfers between farming subsidiaries, management fee charges, intercompany loans). Captures transaction ID, sending company code, receiving company code, transaction type, posting date, amount, currency, elimination status, reconciliation status, and netting agreement reference. Supports GAAP/IFRS consolidated financial statement elimination.' .

ind:TaxRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tax transaction and compliance record capturing tax postings, filings, and obligations for the agricultural enterprise including sales tax, use tax, excise tax on agricultural chemicals, property tax on farmland, income tax provisions, and agricultural-specific exemptions (farm fuel tax credits, ag sales tax exemptions). Captures tax document number, tax type, tax jurisdiction, taxable base amount, tax rate, tax amount, tax period, filing status, payment due date, and regulatory authority (IRS, state revenue department). Supports GAAP/IFRS tax accounting, deferred tax calculations, and regulatory compliance.' .

ind:CommodityHedge rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Commodity Hedge' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commodity price hedging instrument record capturing futures contracts, options, and forward contracts used to manage price risk for agricultural commodities including grain (corn, wheat, soybeans), oilseeds, cotton, sugar, and livestock (feeder cattle, lean hogs). Captures hedge ID, commodity type, instrument type (futures, options, forward), exchange (CME, CBOT, ICE), contract month, notional quantity (BU/MT/CWT), strike/forward price, premium paid, hedge designation (fair value, cash flow per ASC 815/IFRS 9), effectiveness test result, mark-to-market value, margin requirements, and settlement status. Essential for managing basis risk between local cash prices and exchange-traded futures in agricultural marketing.' .

ind:GovernmentProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Government Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'USDA and government agricultural program enrollment and payment record capturing participation in federal and state farm programs. Covers commodity programs (ARC-CO, ARC-IC, PLC), conservation programs (CRP, EQIP, CSP), crop insurance (FCIC/RMA policies), disaster assistance (WHIP+, ERP, ELAP), and state-level agricultural incentives. Captures program name, administering agency (USDA FSA, NRCS, RMA), enrollment period, enrolled acres/base acres/livestock units, payment rate, estimated and actual payments received, compliance requirements (conservation compliance, HELC/WC), and payment limitation status. Supports farm revenue planning, ROI analysis, and regulatory reporting to USDA.' .

ind:Inspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all quality inspections across field, post-harvest, storage, processing, and supply chain operations. Captures inspection type (GAP, GMP, HACCP verification, FSMA, GLOBALG.A.P., pre-operational, receiving, GAP compliance assessment), scope, facility or field location, scheduled and actual dates, inspector identity, overall pass/fail outcome, and score or grade. For GAP compliance assessments: standard version, module-level scoring (worker health, agricultural water, soil amendments, field sanitation, traceability), and certification eligibility. Regulatory body association (USDA, FDA, FSIS, APHIS). SSOT for all inspection events in the quality domain.' .

ind:InspectionFinding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection Finding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual findings, observations, and deficiencies identified during quality inspections or formal audits (internal, second-party, third-party certification). Records parent event reference and type (inspection or audit), finding classification (critical, major, minor, observation, opportunity for improvement), applicable standard clause reference (FSMA 21 CFR Part 117, GLOBALG.A.P. control point, SQF Element, BRC Clause, IFS requirement), description of non-conformance or observation, objective evidence, risk severity rating, required response timeline, and disposition. Unified SSOT for ALL quality findings regardless of detection context — replaces separate audit finding tracking. Drives corrective action generation and certification status updates.' .

ind:CorrectiveAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Corrective Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'CAPA (Corrective and Preventive Action) records generated in response to inspection findings, nonconformances (including MRL exceedances and food safety incidents), audit findings, or environmental monitoring positives. Tracks root cause analysis method (5-Why, fishbone, fault tree), corrective action description, preventive action description, responsible party, target completion date, actual closure date, verification method and date, effectiveness review outcome and review date. Supports FSMA, SQF, BRC, and IFS CAPA requirements. Integrates with SAP S/4HANA QM notification workflows. Links to originating finding or nonconformance for full traceability.' .

ind:Nonconformance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Nonconformance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified master record for all quality failures, deviations, and food safety incidents across crop production, livestock operations, processing, and supply chain. Captures nonconformance type (product, process, system, MRL_exceedance, food_safety_incident), severity level (minor, major, critical, food_safety_crisis), affected lot, commodity or product SKU, detection point and source. For standard nonconformances: disposition decision, financial impact estimate, regulatory notification flag. For MRL-type: pesticide active ingredient, detected residue level, applicable MRL standard (EPA, EU, Codex), exceedance magnitude, affected export market. For food safety incidents: incident subtype (contamination, foreign material, allergen, pathogen, chemical), hazard classification, recall class (I, II, III), mock recall flag, affected quantity and value, regulatory agencies notified, root cause category, and incident closure status. SSOT for ALL quality failures from minor process deviations through food safety crises, recalls, and market withdrawals.' .

ind:CertificateOfAnalysis rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Certificate Of Analysis' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Certificate of Analysis (COA) master records for agricultural commodities, processed products, and inputs. Captures issuing laboratory, sample lot reference (LOT), commodity type, test date, analytical parameters tested (moisture, protein, mycotoxin, pesticide residue, heavy metals, microbial counts), pass/fail status per parameter, MRL compliance flags, and customer-facing release status. Integrates with SAP QM usage decision and supports GFSI certification documentation.' .

ind:LabSample rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Lab Sample' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Laboratory sample submission and tracking records for all quality testing activities. Captures sample collection point (field, bin, processing line, receiving dock), sample type (grain, soil, water, tissue, feed, environmental swab), collection date/time, chain of custody, assigned laboratory, requested test panel, sample condition at receipt, and disposition after testing. Includes testing protocol metadata: sampling plan reference, sampling frequency, approved analytical methods, test parameters, and acceptance criteria. Supports field-to-COA traceability, FSMA sampling plan compliance, and HACCP verification sampling.' .

ind:TestResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Test Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual analytical test results associated with a lab sample. Records test parameter name (e.g., aflatoxin, glyphosate residue, Salmonella, moisture content, pH, EC), measured value, unit of measure (ppb, ppm, CFU/g, %), method reference (AOAC, ISO, EPA method), detection limit, MRL threshold, pass/fail determination, and laboratory analyst sign-off. Provides granular traceability for COA generation and regulatory reporting to USDA, FDA, and FSIS.' .

ind:HaccpPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Haccp Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Points) plan master records with embedded CCP monitoring logs for each production process, commodity, or facility. Plan-level: defines process scope, hazard analysis summary, identified biological/chemical/physical hazards, critical control points (CCPs), critical limits, monitoring procedures, corrective action procedures, verification activities, and record-keeping requirements. CCP monitoring log detail: captures real-time or periodic measurements at each CCP including monitoring parameter (temperature, pH, chlorine concentration, metal detector sensitivity), measured value, critical limit, monitoring frequency, operator identity, timestamp, deviation flag, and immediate corrective action taken. Provides both the plan framework and continuous compliance evidence required by FDA FSMA Preventive Controls rule and GFSI scheme auditors (SQF, BRC, IFS).' .

ind:QualityCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all quality and food safety certifications held by the enterprise, including GFSI scheme certifications (SQF, BRC, IFS), GLOBALG.A.P., USDA Organic (NOP), ISCC, Fair Trade, and ISO 22000/14001. Captures certification body, scheme name, scope of certification, certificate number, issue date, expiry date, surveillance audit schedule, current status (active, suspended, withdrawn), and facility or operation covered. Drives certification readiness dashboards and renewal workflows.' .

ind:QualityAudit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all formal quality and food safety audits including internal audits, second-party customer audits, and third-party certification audits (SQF, BRC, IFS, GLOBALG.A.P., USDA Organic). Captures audit type, auditing body or auditor name, audit scope, facility or operation audited, scheduled and actual audit dates, audit standard and version, overall grade or score, and certification outcome. Distinct from operational inspections — audits are formal system-level assessments against a defined standard.' .

ind:FacilityMonitoring rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Facility Monitoring' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified facility monitoring records covering IPM pest scouting, sanitation execution, and hygiene verification for fields, storage facilities, processing areas, and equipment. For pest monitoring: captures monitoring location, pest species, population count, trap type and placement, scouting date, economic threshold comparison, action threshold status, and scout identity. For sanitation: captures sanitation event type (pre-operational, operational, post-harvest, allergen changeover), cleaning agent and concentration, contact time, rinse verification, ATP swab or microbial test result, responsible operator, and quality supervisor sign-off. Supports GAP compliance, GMP compliance, EPA pesticide use justification, FSMA sanitation preventive controls, and GFSI audit evidence.' .

ind:SupplierAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Supplier and input quality assessment records evaluating quality performance of seed suppliers, agrochemical vendors, feed ingredient suppliers, contract growers, and packaging material providers. Captures supplier identity reference, assessment type (pre-qualification, periodic review, for-cause, FSMA supply chain verification), assessment criteria scores (documentation completeness, facility standards, product conformance history, regulatory compliance, COA consistency), overall rating, approved/conditional/disqualified status, and reassessment due date. Supports procurement quality gate decisions, FSMA Foreign Supplier Verification Program (FSVP), and supply chain preventive controls.' .

ind:HoldRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Hold Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Product and lot hold records placing agricultural commodities, processed products, or inputs under quality hold pending investigation or disposition. Captures hold type (quality, regulatory, food safety, MRL, customer complaint), affected lot (LOT/GRN), commodity, quantity held, hold initiation reason with source reference (nonconformance ID, test result ID, customer complaint), hold location (bin, warehouse, field, processing line), responsible quality manager, hold start and release dates, duration tracking, and final disposition (release, rework, destroy, return to supplier, downgrade). Integrates with SAP QM usage decision and warehouse management. Critical for FSMA recall readiness and food safety incident response.' .

ind:RegulatorySubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of regulatory submissions, notifications, and filings made to governing bodies including USDA, FDA, FSIS, EPA, and APHIS. Captures submission type (FSMA facility registration, Reportable Food Registry entry, pesticide use report, organic certification application, export health certificate), regulatory agency, submission date, submission reference number, submission status (pending, accepted, rejected, under review), response received date, and compliance deadline. SSOT for regulatory reporting obligations in the quality and food safety domain.' .

ind:EnvironmentalMonitoring rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Environmental Monitoring' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Environmental monitoring program records for pathogen and indicator organism surveillance in processing facilities, storage areas, and agricultural water sources. Captures monitoring zone classification (Zone 1-4), sample site identifier, target organism (Listeria spp., Salmonella, E. coli, coliforms), sampling frequency, collection method (sponge, swab, water grab), test result, trend analysis flag, corrective action trigger status, and responsible quality manager. Supports FSMA Preventive Controls environmental monitoring requirements, GFSI audit evidence, and proactive contamination prevention programs critical to food safety in agriculture.' .

ind:ReceivableFinancing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Invoice ;
    rdfs:label 'Receivable Financing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks receivables financing, factoring, and assignment transactions where the agricultural enterprise sells or pledges AR invoices to financial institutions for early cash conversion. Captures financing arrangement reference, factored invoice references, advance rate, factoring fee, recourse type (with/without recourse), financing institution, disbursement date, maturity date, and settlement status. Common in agricultural commodity trading where seasonal cash flow gaps require receivables monetization between harvest delivery and customer payment.' .

ind:ReturnClaim rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Return Claim' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of a return or claim raised against a vendor for defective, off-spec, or non-conforming agricultural inputs. Captures claim reference number, PO and GRN reference, vendor reference, claim type (quality rejection, short shipment, damaged goods, germination failure, off-spec fertilizer grade, contaminated feed ingredient), affected quantity, claim value, supporting evidence (COA failure, lab test results, field observation), claim status (open, vendor-acknowledged, credit-issued, closed), credit note reference, and root cause category. Supports vendor performance tracking and recovery of costs for non-conforming inputs. Critical for seed germination guarantee claims and agrochemical efficacy disputes.' .

ind:BankAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Bank Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Bank account master representing enterprise banking relationships and cash management accounts used for agricultural operations. Captures bank account number, bank name, bank routing/SWIFT/BIC, account type (operating, savings, escrow, money market), currency, company code, GL reconciliation account, signatory authorities, daily balance, credit facility linkage, and active status. Critical for seasonal cash flow management, crop revenue deposits, input payment disbursements, and operating line of credit draws in agricultural enterprises.' .

ind:Loan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Loan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Loan and credit facility master tracking all debt instruments held by the agricultural enterprise including operating lines of credit, term loans for equipment/land, FSA guaranteed loans, and seasonal crop production loans. Captures loan ID, lender (Farm Credit, commercial bank, FSA), loan type, principal amount, outstanding balance, interest rate (fixed/variable), maturity date, collateral (land, equipment, crop), covenant requirements, payment schedule, and draw/repayment history. Essential for ag financial planning where seasonal borrowing against future crop revenue is standard practice.' .

ind:Crew rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Crew' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for agricultural work crews and gangs — the fundamental operational unit for field labor deployment in row crop, specialty crop, and livestock operations. Captures crew code, crew name, crew type (planting crew, harvest crew, spray crew, irrigation team, livestock handling team, packing line crew, equipment maintenance team), assigned supervisor/crew leader (employee reference), home farm operation or facility, default shift pattern, target crew size, current active member count, active status, seasonal validity start/end dates, and primary language spoken. Crews are the primary unit of labor scheduling, field assignment, productivity tracking, and piece-rate pay calculation in agricultural operations. SSOT for crew identity and composition. Supports H-2A crew-based housing and transportation management, piece-rate pay calculations by crew, DOL crew disclosure requirements under MSPA, and crew-level safety briefing documentation. Crew membership is tracked via employee-to-crew assignment with effective dates to support seasonal rotation and mid-season crew reassignment.' .

ind:GenomicTest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Genomic Test' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of DNA-based genetic tests performed on individual animals for parentage verification, breed composition analysis, and genomic-enhanced EPD (Expected Progeny Difference) calculation. Captures test date, animal ID, testing laboratory, sample type (hair, blood, tissue), test panel (parentage, breed composition, trait markers, full genomic profile), SNP chip platform (e.g., GGP-LD, GGP-HD, Illumina 50K), parentage verification result (confirmed sire/dam or exclusion), genomic-enhanced EPD values (calving ease, birth weight, weaning weight, yearling weight, milk, marbling, tenderness, feed efficiency), breed association registration number, genomic merit index scores (e.g., $B, $M, $W, TPI, NM$), genetic condition carrier status (e.g., AM, NH, CA, DD), coat color genotype, polled/horned genotype, test cost, and result date. Supports genetic selection decisions, mating program optimization, breed association registration, and genomic-based marketing premiums. Critical for modern beef and dairy operations using marker-assisted selection and genomic prediction.' .

ind:CarbonFootprint rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Carbon Footprint' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for enterprise-level and farm-unit-level carbon footprint assessments. Captures total GHG emissions inventory (Scope 1, 2, 3) per farm unit, growing season, or enterprise reporting period. Includes baseline year, measurement methodology (GHG Protocol, ISO 14064), total CO2e tonnes, emission intensity per hectare and per tonne of commodity produced, third-party verification status, and certification body. Serves as the SSOT for carbon accounting across the agricultural enterprise.' .

ind:GhgEmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Ghg Emission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of individual greenhouse gas emission events and calculated emission quantities at the source level. Captures emission source type (enteric fermentation, manure management, synthetic fertilizer N2O, fuel combustion, rice cultivation, land use change), emission date or period, gas type (CO2, CH4, N2O, HFCs), quantity in native units and CO2e, emission factor applied, calculation methodology, and associated farm unit or field. Supports Scope 1/2/3 disaggregation and IPCC Tier 1/2/3 reporting.' .

ind:EmissionFactor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Emission Factor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference catalog of GHG emission factors used in agricultural emission calculations. Captures factor name, gas type, source category (IPCC Activity Data category), geographic applicability (country/region), value and unit, IPCC tier level, data source (IPCC 2006, USDA, EPA), effective date range, and uncertainty range. Provides the authoritative lookup table for all emission calculations across the sustainability domain.' .

ind:WaterUsage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Water Usage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of water consumption and withdrawal events across farm operations. Captures water source type (groundwater, surface water, municipal, rainwater harvesting), withdrawal volume (megalitres), consumptive use volume, return flow volume, water use category (irrigation, livestock watering, processing, domestic), field or facility identifier, measurement method (meter, estimate, model), and reporting period. Supports water stewardship accounting per AWS Standard and CDP Water disclosure.' .

ind:WaterStewardshipPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Water Stewardship Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for farm-unit or watershed-level water stewardship plans. Captures plan name, planning period, target watershed or catchment, baseline water stress index (WRI Aqueduct), water reduction targets (volume and percentage), conservation measures planned, irrigation efficiency improvement targets, water recycling commitments, responsible agronomist, approval status, and certification program alignment (AWS, USDA NRCS). Governs the enterprise water management strategy.' .

ind:SoilCarbonSequestration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Soil Carbon Sequestration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of soil organic carbon (SOC) sequestration measurements and estimates at the field or management zone level. Captures measurement date, field identifier, management zone, SOC stock (tonnes C/ha), SOC change from baseline, measurement method (direct sampling, modelling via DNDC/RothC/CENTURY), sampling depth, bulk density, carbon credit eligibility flag, verified carbon units (VCUs) generated, and registry submission reference (Verra VCS, Gold Standard, CAR Soil Enrichment Protocol). Core to carbon credit monetization.' .

ind:CarbonCredit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Carbon Credit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for carbon credits generated, purchased, retired, or transferred by the agricultural enterprise. Captures credit type (soil carbon, avoided deforestation, methane reduction, renewable energy), registry (Verra VCS, Gold Standard, CAR, ACR), serial number, vintage year, quantity (tonnes CO2e), project identifier, issuance date, retirement date, retirement reason (voluntary offset, compliance, internal neutralization), buyer entity, and price per tonne. Enables carbon market participation and net-zero accounting.' .

ind:BiodiversityAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Biodiversity Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of biodiversity surveys and ecological assessments conducted on farm land. Captures assessment date, field or parcel identifier, assessment type (habitat survey, species inventory, pollinator count, wetland delineation), methodology (USDA NRCS, IUCN, BirdLife), species richness count, threatened species identified, habitat quality score, pollinator index, assessment organization, and recommended conservation actions. Supports biodiversity net gain commitments and TNFD disclosure.' .

ind:ConservationEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Conservation Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record tracking the agricultural enterprise\'s enrollment in government and voluntary conservation programs. Captures program name (USDA CRP, EQIP, CSP, RCPP, USDA NRCS), enrollment date, expiration date, enrolled field or parcel identifiers, enrolled acreage, conservation practice codes (NRCS Practice Standards), annual payment amount, compliance status, practice implementation deadlines, and program contact. Distinct from land.conservation_practice which records the physical practice implementation.' .

ind:EsgReport rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Esg Report' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for formal ESG (Environmental, Social, Governance) disclosure reports published by the agricultural enterprise. Captures report title, reporting period, reporting framework (GRI Standards, SASB Ag & Food, TCFD, CDP, CSRD, SEC Climate Rule), publication date, assurance level (limited/reasonable), assurance provider, key performance indicators included, materiality assessment reference, report URL, and regulatory filing status. Serves as the SSOT for ESG disclosure governance.' .

ind:EsgMetric rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Esg Metric' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of individual ESG performance metric values reported for a specific period and organizational scope. Captures metric name, ESG pillar (Environmental/Social/Governance), reporting framework and disclosure code (e.g., GRI 305-1, SASB FB-AG-110a.1), reporting period, organizational scope (enterprise/farm unit/facility), metric value, unit of measure, data quality flag, restatement indicator, and prior period comparative value. Enables structured ESG data collection feeding into esg_report.' .

ind:SustainabilityCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Sustainability Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for sustainability and environmental certifications held by the agricultural enterprise, farm units, or specific commodities. Captures certification scheme (Rainforest Alliance, RSPO, ISCC, SCS Sustainably Grown, Certified Naturally Grown, USDA Organic, ProTerra, RTRS), certified entity scope (enterprise/farm/product), certificate number, issuing body, issue date, expiry date, audit cycle, certification status, and scope of certification (crop types, acreage, supply chain stage). Distinct from product.organic_certification which is product-level.' .

ind:SustainabilityAudit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Sustainability Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of sustainability and environmental compliance audits conducted against the enterprise or farm units. Captures audit date, audit type (internal/second-party/third-party), certification scheme audited, auditor name and organization, farm unit or facility scope, findings count by severity (major/minor/observation), overall audit outcome (pass/conditional/fail), corrective action requirements, follow-up audit date, and audit report reference. Distinct from quality.audit which covers food safety and quality audits.' .

ind:RegenerativePractice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Regenerative Practice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining regenerative agriculture practices adopted and tracked across farm units and fields. Captures practice type (cover cropping, no-till/reduced-till, crop rotation diversity, agroforestry, composting, integrated pest management, managed grazing), practice name, implementation standard or protocol, eligible carbon program alignment, expected SOC benefit (tonnes C/ha/yr), expected yield impact, cost per acre, and practice status. Serves as the practice catalog for regenerative agriculture program management.' .

ind:PracticeAdoption rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Practice Adoption' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the adoption and implementation of a regenerative or conservation practice on a specific field or farm unit in a given season. Captures adoption date, field identifier, farm unit, practice identifier, implementation area (acres/hectares), implementation method, input quantities used (e.g., cover crop seed rate), operator responsible, verification method (remote sensing, field inspection, self-reported), verification date, and carbon program enrollment linkage. Bridges regenerative_practice catalog to field-level execution.' .

ind:Target rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Target' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for enterprise sustainability commitments and science-based targets. Captures target name, target category (net-zero, carbon neutral, water positive, deforestation-free, biodiversity net gain, renewable energy), baseline year, baseline value, target year, target value, target unit, alignment framework (SBTi, RE100, CDP, TCFD, TNFD, UN SDGs), approval status, board endorsement date, public commitment date, and progress tracking frequency. Governs the enterprise sustainability roadmap.' .

ind:TargetProgress rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Target Progress' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking periodic progress against each sustainability target. Captures reporting period, target identifier, current period value, cumulative progress value, percentage of target achieved, trajectory status (on-track/at-risk/off-track), contributing initiatives, data source, and narrative commentary. Enables time-series tracking of sustainability target attainment for board reporting and external disclosure.' .

ind:DeforestationRisk rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Deforestation Risk' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for deforestation and land conversion risk assessments associated with farm units, supply sheds, and sourcing geographies. Captures assessment date, geographic scope (farm/region/country), risk classification (high/medium/low per EUDR, Trase, Global Forest Watch), forest cover baseline year, deforestation alert count (Global Forest Watch GLAD alerts), commodity linkage (soy, palm, cattle, cocoa), EUDR compliance status, due diligence system reference, and remediation plan. Supports EU Deforestation Regulation (EUDR) compliance.' .

ind:EnergyConsumption rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Energy Consumption' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of energy consumption across farm operations, processing facilities, and logistics. Captures consumption period, facility or farm unit, energy source type (diesel, natural gas, LPG, grid electricity, solar, wind, biogas), consumption quantity and unit, renewable energy percentage, associated Scope 1 or Scope 2 GHG emissions, energy intensity (GJ per tonne of output), meter or invoice reference, and renewable energy certificate (REC) linkage. Supports RE100 and Scope 2 market-based accounting.' .

ind:WasteEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Waste Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of agricultural waste generation and disposal events. Captures waste event date, farm unit or facility, waste type (crop residue, packaging waste, agrochemical containers, food processing waste, manure, biosolids, plastic mulch), quantity generated, disposal method (composting, anaerobic digestion, landfill, incineration, recycling, land application), waste contractor, regulatory permit reference, and diversion rate from landfill. Supports circular economy and zero-waste-to-landfill commitments.' .

ind:SupplierSustainability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Sustainability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for sustainability performance assessments of agricultural input suppliers and supply chain partners. Captures supplier identifier, assessment period, sustainability questionnaire framework (EcoVadis, CDP Supply Chain, SEDEX, SAC Higg Index), overall sustainability score, environmental score, social score, governance score, deforestation-free commitment status, living wage compliance, child labor risk rating, corrective action plan status, and re-assessment due date. Supports Scope 3 supply chain sustainability management.' .

ind:ClimateRiskAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Climate Risk Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for physical and transition climate risk assessments conducted at the enterprise, farm unit, or asset level. Captures assessment date, risk horizon (short/medium/long-term), risk type (physical: acute/chronic; transition: policy/technology/market/reputational), climate scenario (IPCC RCP 2.6/4.5/8.5, IEA NZE), risk description, likelihood rating, financial impact estimate, affected assets or operations, adaptation measure planned, and TCFD disclosure alignment. Supports TCFD and CSRD climate risk disclosure. Distinct from weather.climate_risk_indicator which is a weather-driven meteorological metric.' .

ind:EnvironmentalIncident rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Environmental Incident' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of environmental incidents, spills, and regulatory violations occurring in agricultural operations. Captures incident date, incident type (chemical spill, nutrient runoff, air emission exceedance, water discharge violation, soil contamination, pesticide drift), location (field/facility), severity classification, regulatory body notified, notification date, root cause, immediate response actions taken, remediation plan, regulatory penalty amount, and closure date. Supports environmental compliance management and regulatory reporting.' .

ind:Scope3Category rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Scope3 Category' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference catalog defining Scope 3 GHG emission categories applicable to the agricultural enterprise\'s value chain. Captures GHG Protocol Scope 3 category number and name (e.g., Category 1: Purchased Goods & Services, Category 4: Upstream Transportation, Category 11: Use of Sold Products), agricultural relevance description, primary data collection method, emission factor source, materiality classification (material/not material), and reporting obligation (mandatory/voluntary). Provides the classification framework for Scope 3 inventory management.' .

ind:LandUseChange rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Land Use Change' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of land use change events that affect GHG emissions, carbon stocks, and biodiversity. Captures change date, parcel or field identifier, previous land use type (forest, grassland, wetland, cropland, pasture), new land use type, change area (hectares), driver of change (agricultural expansion, conservation set-aside, reforestation, rewilding), carbon stock change (tonnes CO2e), EUDR compliance flag, satellite verification reference (Global Forest Watch, Planet Labs), and regulatory permit status.' .

ind:Initiative rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sustainability ;
    rdfs:label 'Initiative' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for sustainability programs and initiatives managed by the agricultural enterprise. Captures initiative name, initiative type (carbon reduction, water conservation, biodiversity enhancement, renewable energy, regenerative agriculture, social equity), sponsoring business unit, start date, planned end date, target sustainability metric impacted, planned emission reduction or resource saving, budget allocated, implementation status, partner organizations, and linkage to sustainability targets. Enables portfolio management of sustainability investments.' .

ind:Permit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Permit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all environmental, operational, and regulatory permits held by the agricultural enterprise — including EPA NPDES discharge permits, air quality permits, CAFO permits, water withdrawal permits, pesticide applicator licenses, and state-issued agricultural operating permits. Captures permit number, permit type, issuing authority, issue date, expiration date, renewal deadline, permitted activity scope, facility or farm unit covered, permit conditions and limits, bond/insurance requirements, and current permit status. Tracks the full permit lifecycle from application through renewal or revocation.' .

ind:License rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'License' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all professional licenses and certifications required to conduct regulated agricultural activities — including pesticide applicator licenses (private and commercial), veterinary licenses, certified crop advisor (CCA) credentials, food handler certifications, CDL licenses for transport, and state-issued agricultural dealer licenses. Captures license number, license type, licensing body, holder (individual or entity), issue date, expiration date, renewal requirements, continuing education (CEU) requirements, and license status. Distinct from permits (which cover facilities/operations) — licenses cover individuals and professional qualifications.' .

ind:RegulatoryFiling rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Filing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of every regulatory filing, report, and submission made to governing bodies — including USDA NASS crop reports, EPA Tier II chemical inventory reports, FSIS HACCP plan submissions, state pesticide use reports, FSMA food safety plan filings, OSHA 300 logs, and cross-border phytosanitary certificates. Captures filing ID, filing type, regulatory requirement reference, governing body, filing period (start/end), submission date, submission method (electronic/paper), filing status (draft, submitted, accepted, rejected, under review), preparer, approver, and any acknowledgment or confirmation numbers received.' .

ind:Obligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational compliance obligation record linking a specific regulatory requirement to a farm unit, facility, or operational entity within the enterprise. Represents the enterprise\'s specific duty to comply — capturing obligation ID, regulatory requirement reference, obligated entity (farm unit, facility, legal entity), obligation type, due date, recurrence rule (annual, quarterly, event-triggered), assigned compliance owner, current fulfillment status (pending, in-progress, fulfilled, overdue, waived), and last fulfilled date. Serves as the compliance calendar backbone — the actionable task layer derived from the regulatory requirement master.' .

ind:Event rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each discrete compliance activity or fulfillment event executed against a compliance obligation — including inspections completed, filings submitted, trainings delivered, audits conducted, and certifications renewed. Captures event ID, obligation reference, event type, event date, location, responsible party, outcome (pass, fail, conditional, deferred), evidence reference, notes, and next action required. Provides the audit trail of compliance activity execution and serves as the primary evidence log for regulatory readiness.' .

ind:InspectionRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all regulatory inspections conducted by external government agencies at farm units, processing facilities, grain elevators, and storage sites — including USDA FSIS plant inspections, FDA food safety inspections, EPA environmental compliance inspections, state department of agriculture inspections, and OSHA workplace safety inspections. Captures inspection ID, inspection type, inspecting agency, inspector name and badge, inspection date, facility/farm unit inspected, scope of inspection, findings summary, deficiency count, corrective action required flag, inspection outcome (satisfactory, conditional, unsatisfactory), and follow-up inspection date. Distinct from quality.inspection which covers internal QA inspections.' .

ind:RegulatoryFinding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Finding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual deficiency, observation, or citation identified during a regulatory inspection. Captures finding ID, parent inspection record reference, finding code, finding description, regulatory citation violated (CFR part/section), severity classification (critical, major, minor, observation), corrective action required, corrective action deadline, responsible party, resolution status, and resolution date. Enables granular tracking of each regulatory deficiency through to closure and supports repeat-finding trend analysis for audit readiness.' .

ind:CorrectiveActionPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Corrective Action Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal corrective action plan (CAP) record generated in response to regulatory inspection findings, agency citations, or compliance failures. Captures CAP ID, triggering inspection finding or citation reference, root cause analysis summary, corrective actions defined, preventive measures, responsible owner, target completion date, actual completion date, verification method, regulatory agency acknowledgment status, and CAP closure status. Distinct from quality.corrective_action which covers internal CAPA for food safety — this entity specifically manages regulatory agency-facing corrective action commitments.' .

ind:PesticideUseRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pesticide Use Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Regulatory pesticide use record (PUR) required by EPA and state departments of agriculture for all commercial and private pesticide applications. Captures PUR ID, application date, applicator license number, pesticide product name, EPA registration number, active ingredient (AI), application rate, total quantity applied, application method, target pest, crop treated, field/parcel reference, pre-harvest interval (PHI) compliance flag, restricted-entry interval (REI) compliance flag, weather conditions at application, and state-specific reporting fields. Serves as the SSOT for pesticide use regulatory reporting — distinct from crop.protection_event which is the operational agronomic record.' .

ind:FoodSafetyPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Food Safety Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for FSMA-mandated food safety plans including Preventive Controls for Human Food (PCHF), Preventive Controls for Animal Food (PCAF), and Produce Safety Rule (PSR) food safety plans. Captures plan ID, plan type, facility covered, plan version, effective date, qualified facility exemption status, hazard analysis summary, preventive controls defined, monitoring procedures, corrective action procedures, verification activities, recall plan reference, plan approval date, approver credentials, and FDA submission status. Serves as the regulatory SSOT for FSMA food safety plan management.' .

ind:PermitCondition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Permit Condition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for individual conditions, limits, and monitoring requirements attached to environmental permits (NPDES, air quality, CAFO, water withdrawal). Captures condition ID, parent permit reference, condition number, condition type (effluent limit, monitoring frequency, reporting requirement, operational restriction), parameter monitored (e.g., nitrogen, phosphorus, BOD, TSS), limit value, limit unit, monitoring frequency, sampling method, reporting deadline, and current compliance status. Enables granular tracking of each permit condition independently — critical for NPDES and CAFO compliance management.' .

ind:MonitoringResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Monitoring Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of environmental monitoring measurements taken to demonstrate compliance with permit conditions — including water quality sampling (effluent, runoff, groundwater), air emissions monitoring, soil nutrient loading measurements, and manure management monitoring. Captures result ID, permit condition reference, sample date, sample location, parameter measured, measured value, unit of measure, analytical method, laboratory reference, detection limit, permit limit value, exceedance flag, and reporting period. Provides the compliance evidence record for environmental permit condition monitoring.' .

ind:TradeComplianceRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Trade Compliance Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record managing cross-border agricultural trade compliance for import and export shipments — covering phytosanitary certificates, USDA APHIS export certificates, FDA Prior Notice filings, CITES permits for regulated species, country-of-origin documentation, and import/export license compliance. Captures record ID, shipment reference, trade direction (import/export), destination/origin country, commodity, applicable trade agreement (USMCA, CPTPP), certificate type, issuing authority, certificate number, issue date, expiration date, compliance status, and any holds or detentions by customs or border inspection. Complements supply.customs_declaration with the regulatory compliance dimension.' .

ind:RegulatoryChange rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Change' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record tracking regulatory changes, new rule publications, and amendments to existing regulations that affect agricultural operations. Captures change ID, regulation name, regulatory body, Federal Register or state register citation, change type (new rule, amendment, repeal, guidance update), effective date, comment period deadline, compliance deadline, impact assessment summary, affected operations (crop, livestock, processing, export), assigned regulatory affairs owner, internal review status, and required enterprise response actions. Enables proactive regulatory change management and compliance calendar updates.' .

ind:ComplianceAudit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all internal and external compliance audits conducted against the agricultural enterprise\'s regulatory obligations — including USDA GAP/GMP audits, EPA compliance audits, FSMA readiness audits, state department of agriculture audits, and third-party regulatory compliance audits. Captures audit ID, audit type, audit scope, auditing body (internal, second-party, third-party, regulatory), lead auditor, audit date range, facilities/operations covered, regulatory frameworks assessed, overall audit outcome, number of findings, and audit report reference. Distinct from quality.audit which covers food safety and quality management system audits.' .

ind:AuditFinding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Finding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual finding, nonconformance, or observation identified during a compliance audit. Captures finding ID, parent compliance audit reference, finding number, finding type (major nonconformance, minor nonconformance, observation, opportunity for improvement), regulatory clause or standard violated, finding description, evidence reviewed, risk rating, corrective action required flag, corrective action deadline, responsible owner, and finding closure status. Provides granular audit finding management and tracks each finding through to verified closure.' .

ind:ViolationRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Violation Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of formal regulatory violations, citations, notices of violation (NOV), and enforcement actions issued against the agricultural enterprise by regulatory agencies. Captures violation ID, issuing agency, violation date, regulation violated (CFR citation), violation description, facility or operation cited, violation severity (criminal, civil, administrative), proposed penalty amount, final penalty amount, payment status, consent order reference, compliance schedule imposed, and violation resolution status. Serves as the SSOT for all formal enforcement actions and regulatory penalties.' .

ind:RecallEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Recall Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record managing food product recall events initiated voluntarily or mandated by FDA/USDA FSIS — covering Class I, II, and III recalls of agricultural commodities, processed foods, and livestock products. Captures recall ID, recall class, initiating trigger (consumer complaint, lab result, regulatory directive), recalled product and lot numbers, quantity recalled, distribution scope, recall notification date, FDA/FSIS notification status, press release issued flag, consignee notification status, effectiveness check results, product disposition (destruction, reconditioning, return), and recall closure date. Serves as the SSOT for recall event management.' .

ind:RecallLot rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Recall Lot' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association record linking specific commodity lots, product lots, or inventory positions to an active recall event. Captures recall lot ID, recall event reference, lot number, commodity or product reference, quantity affected, storage location, current disposition status (quarantined, returned, destroyed, reconditioned, cleared), customer notification status, and lot recovery confirmation. Enables granular lot-level traceability management during a recall and supports FDA/FSIS effectiveness check reporting.' .

ind:WorkerProtectionRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Worker Protection Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional compliance record for EPA Worker Protection Standard (WPS) obligations covering agricultural workers and pesticide handlers on farms and in greenhouses. Captures record ID, farm unit, compliance year, WPS training completion status, safety data sheet (SDS) availability confirmation, decontamination supplies provision status, pesticide application and hazard information posting status, restricted-entry interval (REI) posting compliance, emergency medical care access documentation, and annual WPS audit date. Serves as the SSOT for WPS compliance documentation distinct from workforce training records.' .

ind:OrganicComplianceRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Organic Compliance Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional compliance record tracking USDA National Organic Program (NOP) compliance activities for certified organic operations — including organic system plan updates, prohibited substance use investigations, split operation management, buffer zone monitoring, and organic integrity database submissions. Captures record ID, farm unit or facility, certifying agent, compliance year, organic system plan version, prohibited substance incident flag, buffer zone assessment date, parallel production flag, split operation controls documented, and annual certification renewal status. Complements product.organic_certification (which is the certification master) by capturing the ongoing compliance activity record.' .

ind:CalendarEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Calendar Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational compliance calendar entry representing a scheduled compliance deadline, filing due date, permit renewal, license expiration, or regulatory reporting milestone. Captures entry ID, compliance obligation reference, entry title, due date, reminder lead time (days before due), assigned owner, associated regulatory body, entry type (filing, renewal, inspection, training, reporting), recurrence pattern, completion status, and completion date. Serves as the operational scheduling layer for compliance management — enabling proactive deadline tracking and workload planning across all regulatory obligations.' .

ind:RegulatoryAgency rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Agency' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for all regulatory agencies and governing bodies with jurisdiction over the agricultural enterprise\'s operations — including USDA (APHIS, AMS, FSIS, FSA, NRCS), FDA, EPA, OSHA, state departments of agriculture, state environmental agencies, and international bodies (CODEX, IPPC). Captures agency ID, agency name, agency acronym, parent agency, jurisdiction level (federal, state, county, international), primary regulatory domain (food safety, environmental, labor, trade, animal health, plant health), primary contact information, online portal URL, and applicable CFR titles. Serves as the reference SSOT for agency identity used across all compliance records.' .

ind:Document rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all compliance-related documents managed by the regulatory compliance function — including permits, licenses, inspection reports, corrective action plans, food safety plans, organic system plans, consent orders, and regulatory correspondence. Captures document ID, document type, document title, associated compliance obligation or event, issuing or receiving party, document date, effective date, expiration date, document version, storage location (DMS path or URL), confidentiality classification, and document status (draft, active, superseded, archived). Serves as the document registry for the compliance domain — enabling audit-ready document retrieval.' .

ind:BioterrorismRegistration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Bioterrorism Registration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for FDA Bioterrorism Act facility registrations required for food facilities that manufacture, process, pack, or hold food for human or animal consumption in the United States. Captures registration ID, FDA registration number, facility name, facility type, food categories handled, registration effective date, biennial renewal date, renewal status, emergency contact information, US agent information (for foreign facilities), and registration suspension status. Manages the full lifecycle of FDA facility registration compliance including biennial renewal tracking.' .

ind:CoverCrop rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Cover Crop' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for cover crop plantings used in conservation and soil health programs between primary cash crop seasons. Captures cover crop species or mix, seeding rate, planting date, termination date and method, biomass estimate, and associated field and growing season references.' .

ind:HarvestEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Harvest Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an actual harvest operation executed on a field, capturing harvest date, operator, equipment used, crop harvested, field area harvested, moisture at harvest, yield weight, and grain quality observations. Links to yield_record for final reconciled yield data.' .

ind:VendorProductApproval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Product Approval' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal approval contract between an agricultural input product and a qualified vendor. It captures the operational Approved Vendor List (AVL) entry that procurement teams actively create, maintain, and revoke as part of supplier qualification processes. Each record links one input_product to one vendor with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific vendor-product qualification pairing — including approval status, preferred rank, negotiated pricing, lead time, and quality performance history.. Existence Justification: In agricultural procurement, an approved vendor list (AVL) is a formally managed operational construct where each input product (fertilizer, pesticide, seed treatment) is qualified against multiple approved vendors, and each vendor is approved to supply multiple input products. The business actively creates, maintains, and revokes these vendor-product approvals with specific terms (pricing, lead time, preferred rank, approval status) that belong to neither the input product nor the vendor alone. This is a classic supply agreement / vendor qualification pattern that is operationally managed, not analytically derived.' .

ind:SeedSupplyAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Seed Supply Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between seed_variety and vendor. It captures the formal supply arrangement under which a specific vendor is authorized to supply a specific seed variety for a given growing season and region. Each record links one seed_variety to one vendor with attributes — pricing, contracted volume, supply region, exclusivity, and certification status — that exist only in the context of this vendor-variety supply relationship and cannot be attributed to either the seed variety catalog or the vendor master alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural seed procurement, a seed variety can be supplied by multiple vendors (seed companies, licensed distributors, regional dealers), and a single vendor typically supplies many seed varieties across their product portfolio. The business actively manages these supply relationships as formal agreements — tracking contracted volumes, pricing, supply regions, and growing seasons — making this a genuine operational M:N relationship, not an analytical correlation. Agriculture businesses explicitly manage \'which vendors are authorized to supply which varieties, under what terms\' as a named procurement concept (Seed Supply Agreement).' .

ind:AccountCommodityProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Account Commodity Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Procurement Agreement (Contract) between a customer account and an agricultural commodity. It captures the operational terms under which a specific account sources a specific commodity — including volume commitments, negotiated pricing tiers, GMO and organic compliance requirements, and the effective period of the agreement. Each record links one account to one commodity with attributes that exist only in the context of this account-commodity procurement relationship. Replaces the denormalized preferred_commodity_categories string field on the account record.. Existence Justification: In agricultural commodity trading, a buyer account actively purchases and maintains procurement relationships with multiple commodities (e.g., a food manufacturer buys corn, soybeans, and wheat), and each commodity is purchased by many different accounts. This relationship is operationally managed as a named business concept — a \'Commodity Preference\' or \'Procurement Agreement\' — with its own attributes including volume commitments, pricing tiers, GMO/organic requirements, and effective date ranges that belong to neither the account nor the commodity alone.' .

ind:BundleEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Bundle Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Enrollment event between account and product_bundle. It captures the operational record of a customer account subscribing to a specific product bundle program for a given crop season — including contracted volume commitments, account-specific pricing overrides, early-order incentive participation, and enrollment lifecycle status. Each record links one account to one product_bundle for one season_year, with attributes that exist only in the context of this enrollment relationship. Supports ag retail sales program management, early-order incentive tracking, and seasonal input supply planning.. Existence Justification: In agricultural retail, customer accounts actively enroll in multiple product bundle programs per season (e.g., a grain farmer subscribes to a seed+crop protection program AND a starter fertilizer+seed treatment package simultaneously), and each bundle program is subscribed to by many accounts across different territories and tiers. This relationship is operationally managed as a \'Sales Program Enrollment\' or \'Bundle Subscription\' — a recognized business concept in ag retail with its own lifecycle, contracted volumes, pricing overrides, and season-year tracking. Business stakeholders actively create, modify, and close these enrollment records as part of the sales campaign and early-order program process.' .

ind:DualRolePartnership rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Dual Role Partnership' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between account and vendor where a single real-world business entity simultaneously holds both a customer relationship and a vendor/supplier relationship with the agricultural enterprise. It captures the operational terms governing this dual-role arrangement — including commodity scope, volume commitments, exclusivity, and effective date range — that exist only in the context of this specific account-vendor pairing. Each record links one customer account to one vendor master record and is actively managed by both commercial and procurement teams.. Existence Justification: In agriculture, entities such as grain cooperatives, food manufacturers, and vertically integrated agribusinesses routinely operate as BOTH a customer (purchasing processed commodities or finished goods) AND a vendor/supplier (selling raw inputs, co-products, or agricultural commodities) to the same enterprise. This dual-role relationship is an actively managed business concept — procurement and commercial teams explicitly track which entities hold both roles, under what commodity scope, with what volume commitments, exclusivity terms, and effective date ranges. The relationship itself is a recognized operational construct that humans create, update, and expire as part of supplier qualification and customer onboarding processes.' .

ind:VarietyLicense rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Variety License' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal licensing Contract between a customer account and a research variety. It captures the commercial terms under which an account is authorized to use, sell, or distribute a specific crop variety, including royalty obligations, geographic scope, exclusivity rights, and license duration. Each record links one account to one variety and carries attributes that exist only in the context of that specific licensing relationship — they cannot reside on the account or variety alone.. Existence Justification: In the agricultural seed industry, customer accounts (food manufacturers, distributors, cooperatives) actively license specific crop varieties from the research organization under formal licensing agreements that carry distinct commercial terms per account-variety pair. A single account may license multiple varieties (e.g., a food manufacturer licensing several soybean and corn varieties), and a single variety may be licensed to multiple accounts under different royalty rates, geographies, and exclusivity arrangements. This is an operationally managed business relationship — licensing teams create, negotiate, renew, and terminate these agreements as a core commercial process.' .

ind:CustomHireContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Custom Hire Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between an agricultural equipment asset and a customer account in custom hire operations. It captures the formal service engagement whereby a specific piece of equipment is contracted to a specific customer account for a defined period and scope of work. Each record links one asset to one account and carries the contractual terms (acreage, rate, service type) and operational performance data that exist only in the context of this specific asset-customer engagement.. Existence Justification: In agricultural custom hire operations, a single piece of equipment (e.g., a combine harvester) is contracted out to multiple customer accounts across a season, and a single customer account may contract multiple assets (combine, grain cart, tractor, sprayer) for their farming operations. The business actively manages these service contracts with specific terms including contracted acreage, hourly rates, service type, and performance tracking — this is a recognized operational concept called a \'Custom Hire Contract\' or \'Equipment Service Agreement\' that humans create, update, and close throughout the crop season.' .

ind:CarrierLocationApproval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Carrier Location Approval' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal approval contract between a freight carrier and an authorized delivery location in the agricultural supply chain. It captures which carriers are approved to serve which receiving facilities, under what service terms, commodity authorizations, and temperature zone agreements. Each record links one carrier to one delivery location and carries attributes that exist only in the context of this approval relationship — such as service level, approved commodity types, temperature zone capability, and approval validity dates. Managed by logistics compliance and transportation teams.. Existence Justification: In agricultural logistics, specific carriers must be formally approved to serve specific delivery locations based on facility-level requirements such as temperature capability, vehicle weight limits, FSMA certification, and dock compatibility. A carrier can be approved to serve many delivery locations, and a delivery location can accept many approved carriers — this approval relationship is actively managed by logistics and compliance teams, not derived from transactional data. The business explicitly tracks which carriers are authorized for which locations, under what service terms, and for which commodity types.' .

ind:VendorCommodityApproval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Commodity Approval' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal approval contract between a vendor and a commodity within the agricultural procurement domain. It captures the Approved Supplier List (ASL) entry that the procurement team actively manages — recording which vendors are approved to supply which commodities, under what grade standards, at what price basis, with what lead times, and at what preferred rank. Each record links one commodity to one approved vendor and carries attributes that exist only in the context of that specific vendor-commodity supply relationship. This is the operational record that governs sourcing decisions and supplier qualification at the commodity level.. Existence Justification: In agricultural procurement, vendors are formally approved to supply specific commodities under defined terms — a vendor supplies multiple commodities (corn, soybeans, wheat) and each commodity is sourced from multiple approved vendors. The business actively manages this relationship as a \'Vendor-Commodity Approval\' or \'Approved Supplier List\' entry, tracking grade standards, pricing basis, lead times, preferred rank, and organic supply eligibility per vendor-commodity pair. These attributes cannot reside on either the vendor or commodity master alone because they are specific to the intersection of a particular vendor supplying a particular commodity.' .

ind:RationIngredient rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Ration Ingredient' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Ration Ingredient role between feed_ration and material_master. It captures the bill-of-materials composition of each feed ration formulation — specifically, which ingredients (material_master records) are included in a given ration, at what inclusion rate, in what quantity per batch, and at what cost. Each record links one feed_ration formulation to one material_master ingredient with attributes that exist only in the context of that specific ration-ingredient combination. Serves as the SSOT for ration composition, supporting NRC nutritional compliance calculations, feed cost allocation, and feed mill mixing operations.. Existence Justification: A feed ration formulation is composed of multiple feed ingredients (material_master records such as corn silage, soybean meal, mineral premix), and each ingredient appears across many different ration formulations. Nutritionists and feed mill operators actively manage this composition daily — creating, adjusting, and versioning ingredient inclusions with specific rates, quantities, and costs per ration-ingredient combination. This is a classic bill-of-materials / recipe composition relationship that the livestock feed industry universally recognizes as \'ration ingredients\' or \'feed formulation lines\'.' .

ind:ApprovedVendorMaterial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Approved Vendor Material' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Approved Vendor List (AVL) contract between material_master and vendor. It captures the operational qualification and commercial terms governing each approved vendor-material sourcing relationship in agricultural procurement. Each record links one material to one approved vendor and carries attributes — qualification status, preferred rank, contracted price, lead time, and minimum order quantity — that exist only in the context of this specific vendor-material pairing and cannot reside on either the material master or the vendor master alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural procurement, a single material (e.g., glyphosate herbicide, hybrid corn seed, urea fertilizer) is routinely sourced from multiple approved vendors at different contracted prices, lead times, and minimum order quantities — and each vendor supplies many different materials. The business actively manages an Approved Vendor List (AVL) per material, tracking qualification status, preferred ranking, contracted pricing, and lead times for each vendor-material combination. This is a well-recognized operational concept in agriculture procurement that procurement teams create, update, and retire as supply agreements change.' .

ind:ApprovedVendorItem rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Approved Vendor Item' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Approved Vendor Item (AVI) contract between a vendor and an input catalog entry in the procurement domain. It captures the operational sourcing agreement that procurement teams actively manage — recording which vendors are approved to supply which agricultural inputs, under what commercial terms, and with what certification and approval status. Each record links one vendor to one input catalog item and carries attributes that exist only in the context of this specific vendor-input sourcing relationship, including negotiated price, lead time, minimum order quantity, approval lifecycle, and certification verification.. Existence Justification: In agricultural procurement, vendors are approved to supply multiple inputs and each input can be sourced from multiple vendors — this is the well-established Approved Vendor List (AVL) or Vendor-Item Master concept actively managed by procurement teams. Each vendor-input combination carries its own negotiated price, lead time, minimum order quantity, approval status, and certification verification, which cannot reside on either the vendor or input catalog record alone. Procurement stakeholders explicitly manage this as a named business entity, querying \'which vendors are approved for this input?\' and \'which inputs can this vendor supply?\'' .

ind:VendorCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Vendor Certification contract between a vendor and a sustainability certification scheme. It captures the specific instance of a vendor holding a particular sustainability or food-safety certification, including the certificate number, scope of coverage, certified crop types, supply chain stage, audit outcomes, and validity dates. Each record links one vendor to one sustainability certification and carries attributes that exist only in the context of that specific vendor-certification relationship — data that cannot reside on either the vendor master or the certification scheme master without duplication or loss of fidelity.. Existence Justification: In agriculture, a single vendor (e.g., a seed company or agrochemical supplier) actively holds multiple sustainability certifications simultaneously — GLOBALG.A.P., RSPO, Rainforest Alliance, USDA Organic — each with its own scope, audit cycle, and expiry. Conversely, a single certification scheme (e.g., Rainforest Alliance) is issued to many vendors across the supply chain. The business actively manages this relationship as a \'Vendor Certification\' record, tracking which certifications a vendor holds, under what scope, for which crop types, and with what audit outcomes — data that belongs to neither the vendor master nor the certification scheme master alone.' .

ind:PartsIssue rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Parts Issue' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Parts Issue (Material Reservation) event between work_order and parts_inventory. It captures each line-item-level consumption of a spare part or consumable against a specific maintenance work order, as recorded in the CMMS (SAP PM goods issue / IBM Maximo material usage). Each record links one work_order to one parts_inventory item and carries the quantity issued, unit cost at time of issue, issue date, reservation status, and return quantity — data that exists only in the context of this specific work-order-to-part consumption event. Serves as the SSOT for actual material consumption supporting OPEX cost tracking, inventory replenishment triggers, and maintenance cost analysis by asset and crop enterprise.. Existence Justification: In agricultural CMMS operations, a single work order consumes multiple spare parts from inventory (e.g., a combine harvester repair may require an air filter, hydraulic seal, and drive belt simultaneously), and each part number is consumed across many different work orders over time. This is a textbook operational M:N: the \'parts issue\' or \'material reservation\' is a well-established CMMS business concept actively created, updated, and closed by maintenance planners and technicians. The relationship carries its own data — quantity issued, unit cost at time of issue, issue date, reservation status, and return quantity — none of which belong solely to the work order header or the parts inventory master.' .

ind:GrainDelivery rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Grain Delivery' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Grain Delivery event between a yield_record and a delivery_location. It captures the operational record of a specific quantity of harvested grain being allocated and physically delivered from a harvest operation to an authorized customer receiving location. Each record links one yield_record to one delivery_location and carries delivery-specific attributes — quantity, date, load ticket, quality grade at delivery, moisture at delivery, and COOL compliance — that exist only in the context of this specific delivery transaction and cannot reside on either the yield record or the delivery location alone.. Existence Justification: In grain merchandising operations, a single harvest load (yield_record) is routinely split across multiple delivery destinations — a grain elevator, an export terminal, and a food plant dock may all receive portions of the same harvest. Conversely, a customer delivery location receives commodity from many yield records across multiple fields, operators, and seasons. The business actively manages these allocations as \'grain deliveries\' or \'load allocations\', tracking quantity delivered, moisture at delivery, quality grade, load ticket number, and COOL (Country of Origin Labeling) verification — data that belongs to neither the yield record nor the delivery location alone.' .

ind:CropLabelRegistration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Crop Label Registration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal EPA Crop Label Registration (Contract) between agrochemical_product and commodity. It captures the regulatory approval of a specific agrochemical product for use on a specific commodity crop, including the label-defined application parameters that are unique to each agrochemical-commodity pairing. Each record links one agrochemical_product to one commodity and carries the application rate, pre-harvest interval, seasonal application limits, and approved method that govern compliant use under FSMA, EPA, and GLOBALG.A.P. requirements.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, the EPA formally registers specific pesticide-crop combinations, meaning a single agrochemical product is approved for use on multiple commodity crops, and a single commodity crop has multiple agrochemical products registered for use on it. This regulatory approval — known as a crop label registration or crop use registration — carries its own data (application rate, PHI days, seasonal application limits, application method) that belongs to neither the agrochemical product nor the commodity alone, but to the specific pairing. The business actively manages these registrations for FSMA, EPA, and GLOBALG.A.P. compliance, making this a genuine operational M:N relationship.' .

ind:TrialTreatment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Treatment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Treatment Application event between agrochemical_product and trial. It captures the operational record of a specific agrochemical product being applied as a treatment arm within a field trial or IPM efficacy study. Each record links one agrochemical product to one trial and carries the treatment-specific application rate, timing, observed efficacy, PHI compliance status, and resistance management classification — data that exists only in the context of this specific product-trial combination and cannot reside on either master record alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural research operations, a single field trial evaluates multiple agrochemical products across different treatment arms (e.g., a fungicide efficacy trial may test 4-6 different products at varying rates), and a single agrochemical product is evaluated across many trials over its registration lifecycle and across different crops, geographies, and pest targets. The relationship itself is a recognized operational concept — a \'Treatment Application\' or \'Trial Treatment\' — that carries its own data: the specific application rate used in that trial, application timing, observed efficacy rating, PHI compliance status, and resistance management classification. These attributes belong neither to the agrochemical product master nor to the trial master alone, but to the specific combination.' .

ind:LotAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Lot Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between commodity_lot and account in the agricultural commodity trading process. It captures the operational commitment of a specific quantity from a commodity lot to a customer account, typically governed by a forward contract or sales order. Each record links one commodity_lot to one account with attributes — allocated quantity, price, status, and contract reference — that exist only in the context of this allocation relationship and cannot reside on either the lot or the account alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural commodity trading, a single commodity lot is routinely split and allocated to multiple customer accounts (e.g., a 50,000 bu corn lot sold in portions to three food manufacturers under separate forward contracts), and a customer account simultaneously holds allocations across many commodity lots. The business actively manages these allocations as operational records — creating, updating, and cancelling them — with quantity, price, status, and contract reference data that belongs to neither the lot nor the account alone. This is a recognized operational concept in grain trading known as a \'Lot Allocation\' or \'Commodity Allocation\'.' .

ind:LotFulfillment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Lot Fulfillment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the fulfillment event between a commodity_lot and a delivery_order in the agricultural supply chain. It captures the operational allocation of a specific commodity lot (or portion thereof) to a specific delivery order, recording quantity allocated, quantity actually delivered, lot split percentage, and quality measurements (grade and moisture) confirmed at the time of delivery. Each record links one commodity_lot to one delivery_order and carries attributes that exist only in the context of this specific lot-to-delivery pairing, supporting FSMA Section 204 traceability, quality settlement, and FIFO/FEFO rotation compliance.. Existence Justification: In grain trading and agricultural supply chain operations, a single delivery order is routinely fulfilled by blending or splitting multiple commodity lots (e.g., combining two partial bins of corn to meet a 50,000 BU delivery order), and a single commodity lot can be allocated across multiple delivery orders over time (e.g., a large 100,000 BU lot split across three separate customer deliveries). The business actively manages this lot-to-delivery allocation as an operational record — tracking quantity allocated, quality at delivery, and moisture per lot-delivery combination — for FSMA Section 204 traceability, quality settlement, and regulatory compliance. This is a recognized operational concept in grain merchandising known as \'lot allocation\' or \'lot fulfillment\', with its own data (quantity_allocated_bu, moisture_at_delivery, quality_grade_at_delivery) that belongs to neither the lot nor the delivery order alone.' .

ind:LotPesticideExposure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Inventory ;
    rdfs:label 'Lot Pesticide Exposure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the PHI Compliance Linkage event between a commodity_lot and a pesticide_use_record. It captures the regulatory determination of whether a specific pesticide application affects a specific commodity lot\'s pre-harvest interval compliance status. Each record links one commodity_lot to one pesticide_use_record and carries the compliance attributes that exist only in the context of this specific lot-application pairing — including the PHI compliance outcome, the area of the lot affected, and the active ingredient exposure details. Required for FSMA Section 204 traceability, EPA pesticide use reporting, and pre-harvest clearance workflows.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, a single commodity lot (harvested from a field over a season) is subject to multiple pesticide applications, each generating its own PUR — and a single pesticide application event can affect multiple commodity lots harvested from the same field across different harvest windows. The business actively manages this relationship to determine PHI compliance status for each lot, which is a regulatory obligation under EPA and FSMA rules. This is not an analytical correlation — it is an operational compliance record that agronomists and compliance officers create, query, and audit as part of pre-harvest clearance workflows.' .

ind:LocationCommodityAuthorization rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Location Commodity Authorization' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Authorization contract between delivery_location and commodity. It captures the operational capability and compliance authorization for a specific delivery location to receive, handle, and store a specific agricultural commodity. Each record links one delivery_location to one commodity with attributes — handling capability, temperature class, volume limits, and effective dating — that exist only in the context of this location-commodity pair and drive order routing, carrier assignment, and logistics compliance validation.. Existence Justification: In agricultural logistics, a delivery location (grain elevator, cold storage, food plant dock) is physically equipped and certified to receive specific commodity types — a grain elevator may accept corn, soybeans, and wheat but NOT livestock; a cold storage facility accepts perishable produce but NOT dry grains. Conversely, each commodity (e.g., Yellow Corn No. 2) can be delivered to many authorized receiving locations across the supply chain. The business actively manages this capability matrix to drive order routing, carrier assignment, and compliance validation — it is not derivable from transactional history alone.' .

ind:FacilityCommodityCapability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Facility Commodity Capability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational capability configuration between a supply chain facility and an agricultural commodity. It captures the specific storage capacity allocation, temperature zone assignment, organic segregation capability, and handling certifications that exist only in the context of a particular facility handling a particular commodity. Each record defines what a facility can do for a specific commodity — enabling logistics planning, compliance verification, and capacity allocation decisions across the agricultural supply network.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, a single facility (e.g., a grain elevator) actively handles multiple commodities simultaneously — corn, soybeans, and wheat may all be stored in segregated bins with different capacity allocations, temperature requirements, and handling certifications. Conversely, a single commodity like Yellow Corn No. 2 is stored and processed across many facilities in the logistics network. The business actively manages this relationship through commodity-specific storage configurations, organic segregation capabilities, and handling certifications that are unique to each facility-commodity pairing — this is not derivable from transactional data alone.' .

ind:FarmVendorApproval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Farm Vendor Approval' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between farm_unit and vendor. It captures the formal approval of a specific vendor to supply designated agricultural input categories to a specific farm unit, including farm-level pricing agreements, preferred supplier status, and approval validity periods. Each record links one farm_unit to one vendor and carries attributes that exist only in the context of this farm-unit-specific vendor authorization — data that belongs neither to the farm unit master nor to the vendor master alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, a farm unit actively approves and manages multiple vendors for input supply (seed, fertilizer, agrochemicals, fuel), and a single vendor supplies inputs to multiple farm units across a region or enterprise. This is not an analytical correlation — procurement teams explicitly create, maintain, and expire farm-unit-level vendor approvals with farm-specific pricing agreements, approved input categories, and validity periods. The relationship is operationally managed as a \'Vendor Approval\' or \'Supply Agreement\' record that procurement and farm managers actively govern.' .

ind:LandFieldOperation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Land Field Operation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational role relationship between a field and a customer account. It captures who operates a given field, in what capacity, and for what period — supporting FSA farm records, crop insurance operator declarations, lease management, and custom farming billing. Each record links one field to one account with a specific operator role and effective date range. A field may have multiple simultaneous records (e.g., one landowner + one tenant + one custom operator), and one account may have many such records across its entire field portfolio.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, a single field can be simultaneously operated by multiple accounts in different capacities — a landowner account holds title, a cash-rent tenant account farms the ground, and a custom operator account may perform specific operations (e.g., harvesting). Conversely, one account (e.g., a large farming operation or custom operator) manages many fields across multiple farm units. The business actively tracks these operator relationships for FSA farm records, crop insurance eligibility, and operational billing — this is not a derived correlation but an actively managed operational record.' .

ind:FieldInputRestriction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Field Input Restriction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the regulatory and operational restriction Contract between a field and an agricultural input product. It captures the specific restriction governing whether and how a given input product may be applied to a given field, driven by organic certification, groundwater advisories, conservation program enrollment, GMO restrictions, or other regulatory requirements. Each record links one field to one input_product and carries the restriction type, regulatory basis, effective period, and reason — data that exists only in the context of this specific field-product pairing.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, a field can have multiple input product restrictions simultaneously (e.g., an organic-certified field restricts all synthetic pesticides, while a field near a waterway restricts specific herbicides, and a conservation-enrolled field restricts certain soil amendments). Conversely, a single input product (e.g., a restricted-use herbicide) is restricted on many different fields across the farm for different regulatory reasons. The business actively manages these restrictions — creating, updating, and expiring them — as a compliance and operational control mechanism with its own regulatory basis, effective dates, and restriction type.' .

ind:FieldCertificationScope rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Land ;
    rdfs:label 'Field Certification Scope' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between a specific agricultural field and a sustainability certification. It captures the operational scope record that defines which fields are covered under each certification, the certified area applicable to that field, the per-field certification status, audit findings, and the effective and expiry dates of coverage. Each record links one field to one sustainability_certification with attributes that exist only in the context of this field-level certification scope — data that belongs neither to the field master record nor to the certification master record alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, a single field genuinely holds multiple simultaneous certifications (e.g., USDA Organic + GlobalG.A.P. + Rainforest Alliance applied to the same paddock at the same time), and a single certification (e.g., a farm-level USDA Organic certificate) covers multiple fields within that farm unit. The business actively manages this relationship — compliance teams track which fields are in scope for each certification, what certified area applies per field, and the per-field audit status. This is not an analytical derivation; it is an operational record that auditors, certification bodies, and farm managers create, update, and query directly.' .

ind:ProtocolDrugAuthorization rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Protocol Drug Authorization' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Authorization (role) between health_protocol and input_catalog. It captures the veterinarian-approved authorization of a specific drug or biological product from the input catalog for use within a defined health protocol, including the prescribed dosage, administration route, treatment step sequence, and applicable withdrawal periods. Each record links one health_protocol to one input_catalog entry and carries attributes that exist only in the context of this specific protocol-drug combination — a core veterinary formulary concept in livestock health management.. Existence Justification: A health protocol (e.g., a BRD treatment ladder or arrival processing protocol) specifies multiple drug products and vaccines drawn from the input catalog in a defined treatment sequence, and each input catalog item (drug, vaccine, antiparasitic) appears across multiple protocols for different species, production classes, and protocol types. The veterinarian actively manages this relationship by defining which specific catalog inputs are authorized for each protocol, at what dosage, via which administration route, and in what step sequence — data that belongs neither to the protocol master record nor to the catalog item alone. This is a recognized operational concept in livestock health management, commonly called a \'Protocol Formulary\' or \'Protocol Drug Authorization\'.' .

ind:MaintenancePlanBom rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Maintenance Plan Bom' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Bill of Materials (BOM) contract between a preventive maintenance plan and a parts inventory item. It captures the planned parts list for each PM plan cycle, specifying which parts are required, in what quantity, in what role, and at what estimated cost. Each record links one maintenance_plan to one parts_inventory item with attributes that exist only in the context of this plan-part combination. Actively managed by maintenance planners in CMMS systems to ensure parts availability before work order execution and to drive automated procurement replenishment ahead of planting and harvest seasons.. Existence Justification: In agricultural equipment maintenance management, a preventive maintenance (PM) plan defines a Bill of Materials (BOM) specifying exactly which parts and consumables are required for each service interval — one plan requires many parts, and one part (e.g., an oil filter or hydraulic fluid) appears across many plans. This is a well-recognized operational concept in CMMS systems called a \'PM BOM\' or \'maintenance plan parts list\', actively created and managed by maintenance planners. The relationship carries its own data (required quantity, part role, mandatory flag, estimated cost, consumption UOM) that belongs to neither the plan nor the part inventory record alone.' .

ind:RouteStop rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Route Stop' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Route Stop — the operational assignment of a customer delivery location as a designated stop on a planned transportation route within the agricultural supply chain TMS. It captures the specific stop-level planning data that exists only in the context of a route-to-delivery-location relationship: stop sequence, arrival windows, commodity types served, and service frequency. Each record links one route to one delivery location and is actively created, updated, and deleted by TMS planners as route networks evolve seasonally or as customer delivery points are added or removed.. Existence Justification: In agricultural TMS operations, a single route corridor (e.g., Midwest Grain Corridor) genuinely serves multiple customer delivery locations along its path — grain elevators, food processing plants, and distribution hubs are all stops on the same route. Conversely, a delivery location such as a major grain elevator or food manufacturing plant dock is realistically served by multiple routes originating from different farm regions or origins. The business actively manages this as a \'Route Stop\' or \'Route-to-Location Assignment\' — a TMS planning concept with its own operational data including stop sequence, arrival windows, commodity types served, and service frequency.' .

ind:ContractCommodityCoverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Commodity Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Coverage Contract between service_contract and commodity. It captures the commodity-specific terms negotiated within a logistics service contract — including committed volumes, freight rates, and temperature/transit SLA targets that apply to a specific commodity under a specific carrier or 3PL agreement. Each record links one service_contract to one commodity with attributes that exist only in the context of this pairing and cannot reside on either parent entity alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural logistics, a single service contract with a carrier or 3PL explicitly covers multiple commodity types (e.g., a contract covering corn, soybeans, and wheat simultaneously), each with distinct committed volumes, freight rates, and temperature compliance targets. Conversely, a single commodity like Yellow Corn No. 2 is covered by many different service contracts across different carriers, lanes, and contract periods. The business actively manages these commodity-specific terms within each contract — this is not an analytical derivation but an operational record that logistics and supply chain teams create and maintain.' .

ind:TrialStaffAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Research ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Staff Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Role-based assignment between a research trial and an employee. It captures the operational record of each person\'s specific role, date range, allocated hours, and contribution type on a given trial. Each record links one trial to one employee in one role, with attributes that exist only in the context of this assignment — not on the trial or the employee alone. Used for labor cost allocation, publication authorship attribution, and regulatory submission personnel records.. Existence Justification: In agricultural research organizations, a single field trial requires multiple personnel in distinct, simultaneous roles — a principal investigator, co-investigators, field technicians, data managers, and statisticians — all actively working on the same trial at the same time. Conversely, each employee participates in multiple trials across seasons and years. The existing trial.employee_id FK captures only the lead PI, which is structurally insufficient to represent the full staffing reality of a research program.' .

ind:PrescriptionZoneRate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Crop ;
    rdfs:label 'Prescription Zone Rate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the zone-level input rate specification between a vra_prescription and an input_product. It captures the operational precision agriculture record that defines exactly how much of a specific input product is prescribed for a specific management zone within a VRA prescription. Each record links one vra_prescription to one input_product for one management zone, carrying the prescribed rate, area, and application method that exist only in the context of this zone-input-prescription combination. Sourced from Trimble Ag Software and Climate FieldView prescription workflows.. Existence Justification: A VRA prescription is specifically designed to apply multiple input products (e.g., N, P, K fertilizers simultaneously) at spatially variable rates across management zones, and each input product appears in many prescriptions across fields, seasons, and farms. The business actively manages this relationship as a \'prescription line item\' or \'zone-rate specification\' — a recognized operational concept in precision agriculture that carries zone-specific rate, area, and method data. This is not an analytical correlation; agronomists and equipment controllers actively create, update, and execute these zone-rate records as part of the VRA workflow.' .

ind:AuditParticipation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Customer ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Participation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Role-based participation of a customer account in a compliance audit. It captures the specific scope, role, and outcome applicable to each account-audit pairing in the agricultural enterprise\'s compliance program. Each record links one account to one compliance_audit with attributes that exist only in the context of this participation relationship — including the account\'s role in the audit, the scope of audit activities applicable to that account, and the outcome relevant to that account.. Existence Justification: In agricultural supply chains, customer accounts (food manufacturers, processors, distributors) are directly subject to compliance audits — a single audit may cover multiple customer accounts (e.g., a GFSI audit covering several co-packers or buyer-facing facilities), and a single customer account may participate in multiple compliance audits over time (USDA GAP, FSMA, GlobalG.A.P., SQF). The business actively tracks each account\'s participation in each audit, including their specific role (auditee, observer, co-auditee), the scope applicable to that account, and the outcome relevant to that account. This is an operationally managed relationship — compliance teams create, update, and close these participation records as part of audit lifecycle management.' .

ind:AgrochemicalPracticeCompatibility rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Agrochemical Practice Compatibility' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Compatibility Contract between agrochemical_product and regenerative_practice. It captures the operational compatibility and restriction rules that govern whether and how a specific agrochemical product may be used in the context of a specific regenerative agriculture practice. Each record links one agrochemical_product to one regenerative_practice with attributes — compatibility status, restriction type, applicable crop type, and effective date — that exist only in the context of this pairing and are actively managed by agronomists and compliance teams to satisfy EPA label requirements, carbon program rules, and GLOBALG.A.P. standards.. Existence Justification: In regenerative agriculture programs, agrochemical products and regenerative practices have explicit compatibility and restriction relationships that are actively managed by agronomists and compliance teams. A single regenerative practice (e.g., pollinator habitat establishment, cover cropping) restricts or conditionally permits multiple agrochemical products, while a single agrochemical product (e.g., a broad-spectrum herbicide) may be restricted or conditionally compatible with multiple regenerative practices. This relationship is operationally managed — agronomists create, update, and retire these compatibility rules as label registrations change, new practices are adopted, or carbon program requirements evolve.' .

ind:AnimalHold rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Livestock ;
    rdfs:label 'Animal Hold' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational hold event between an individual animal and a hold record in livestock quality management. It captures the specific placement of an individual animal under a quality, regulatory, food-safety, or withdrawal-period hold. Each record links one animal to one hold_record and carries per-animal attributes — withdrawal end date, per-animal disposition, and hold initiation timestamp — that exist only in the context of this specific animal-hold pairing and cannot be stored on either the animal master or the group hold record alone.. Existence Justification: In livestock operations, a single hold event routinely covers an entire group or pen of animals (e.g., a withdrawal-period hold after a group antibiotic treatment), meaning one hold_record applies to many animals. Simultaneously, an individual animal accumulates multiple hold records across its lifecycle — different drug withdrawal holds, regulatory holds, food-safety holds — each with its own initiation date, release date, and disposition outcome. The business actively manages which specific animals are under which specific hold, and each animal-hold pairing carries its own per-animal disposition and withdrawal clearance data that belongs neither to the animal master nor to the hold record alone.' .

ind:AssetContractAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Contract Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational Allocation of a specific agricultural equipment asset to a specific sales contract. It captures the business record of which assets are deployed to fulfill which contract obligations across the crop marketing season, including hours consumed, acreage covered, compliance certification status for GlobalGAP/FSMA audit purposes, and the utilization cost allocated to the contract for financial reporting. Each record links one asset to one sales contract and carries attributes that exist only in the context of that specific asset-contract pairing — they cannot reside on the asset (which serves many contracts) or the contract (which uses many assets).. Existence Justification: In large-scale grain operations, agricultural equipment assets (harvesters, grain carts, transport vehicles) are actively allocated to specific sales contracts to fulfill delivery obligations — a single harvester services multiple contracts across a season, and a single contract may require multiple pieces of equipment simultaneously. The business operationally tracks this allocation for cost allocation (CAPEX/OPEX per contract), GlobalGAP audit compliance, and utilization reporting. This is not an analytical correlation derivable from transactional joins — it is an actively managed operational record with its own attributes (allocated hours, acreage, compliance status, utilization cost) that belong to neither the asset nor the contract alone.' .

ind:InputCompatibility rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Input Compatibility' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal compatibility certification between an agricultural equipment asset and an agricultural input product. It captures which input products a given asset is approved or certified to apply, and under what conditions (rate capability, formulation type, certification status, effective date). Each record links one asset to one input_product with attributes that exist only in the context of this compatibility relationship — such as the approved application rate range achievable by that specific asset for that specific input, and whether a formal certification is required and on file.. Existence Justification: In agricultural operations, specific equipment assets (sprayers, spreaders, planters) are certified or rated for compatibility with specific input products based on material compatibility, nozzle specifications, EPA label requirements, and equipment capabilities. A single sprayer asset can be approved for many herbicide/fungicide formulations, and a single input product can be applied by many different equipment assets across a farm fleet. This compatibility relationship is actively managed by agronomists and equipment managers as a formal certification or approval record — it is not derivable from transactional application data alone.' .

ind:AssetCertificationScope rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Equipment ;
    rdfs:label 'Asset Certification Scope' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal inclusion of a specific agricultural asset within the scope of a sustainability certification. It captures which assets are registered under each certification, the per-asset compliance verification status, and the audit evidence linking individual equipment to certification requirements. Each record links one asset to one sustainability_certification with attributes that exist only in the context of this asset-certification pairing — such as the date compliance was verified for that asset, the asset\'s individual status within the certification, and the standard version under which the asset was assessed.. Existence Justification: In certified agricultural supply chains, a single farm asset (e.g., a sprayer or tractor) can be in-scope for multiple sustainability certifications simultaneously (e.g., ISCC for biofuel traceability, GlobalG.A.P. for food safety, and USDA Organic for crop inputs), and a single certification covers a portfolio of assets across the farm operation. The business actively manages which specific assets are within each certification\'s scope, tracks per-asset compliance verification dates and statuses, and must demonstrate this linkage to auditors and buyers. This is a named, operationally managed concept in certified supply chain practice.' .

ind:ContractCertificationVerification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Sales ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Certification Verification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Verification Event between a customer certification_record and a sales contract. It captures the operational compliance-verification process by which a specific certification is confirmed as satisfying a specific contract\'s certification requirements. Each record links one certification_record to one contract and carries attributes that exist only in the context of this verification: when it was verified, by whom, what certification type was required by the contract, and whether the certification was deemed compliant. Critical for GFSI-aligned supply chain qualification, FSMA audit trails, and GLOBALG.A.P. contract compliance tracking.. Existence Justification: In agricultural commodity trading, a single sales contract routinely requires multiple certifications (e.g., GLOBALG.A.P. + FSMA + Organic NOP simultaneously), and a single certification record (e.g., a buyer\'s USDA Organic certificate) can satisfy compliance requirements across multiple contracts within its validity period. The business actively manages which certifications have been verified against which contracts, tracking verification date, compliance status, and the specific cert type required by each contract — this is an operational compliance-verification process, not a derived analytical correlation.' .

ind:CommodityBrokerAuthorization rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Commodity Broker Authorization' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal Commodity Brokerage Authorization contract between a commodity and a broker. It captures the specific terms under which a broker is authorized to facilitate sales of a particular agricultural commodity on behalf of the enterprise. Each record links one commodity to one broker and carries the commodity-specific commission rate, volume target, exclusivity arrangement, and authorization period — attributes that exist only in the context of this specific broker-commodity pairing and cannot reside on either the commodity or broker master record alone.. Existence Justification: In agricultural commodity brokerage, a broker specializes in and is authorized to sell multiple commodities (e.g., corn, soybeans, wheat), and each commodity is facilitated by multiple brokers across different territories and channels. This is an operationally managed relationship: the enterprise actively creates, maintains, and terminates broker-commodity authorization agreements that carry their own terms — commodity-specific commission rates, volume targets, exclusivity arrangements, and effective dates. The denormalized `commodity_specializations` field on the broker record is direct evidence that this M:N reality exists and is currently modeled incorrectly as a multi-value string.' .

